{"type":"message","id":"48fe2c12","parentId":"1f00eded","timestamp":"2026-03-30T14:29:55.224Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_KinZQpJiaMb7CcfJ18qGuge0|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169ca88e2885c8195bff4c6e2f6e85457","toolName":"memory_get","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"text\": \"  - a long-run validation script failed due to Python encoding / syntax issues, so the validation test was not valid.\\n- A stale zombie task named `Claude Code sidecar viability research (retest)` remained marked as running in `active_tasks.json` even though it had completed, causing false Telegram updates on 2026-03-29; Lucca was disturbed by these ghost notifications.\\n- Lucca wants truly separate conversations/sessions by subject. Research conclusion: Telegram private DM is poor for this; a private Telegram group with Topics is the best route if he wants visible separation inside Telegram.\\n- For Telegram topics/groups with OpenClaw, the key config findings were:\\n  - parent group allowlisting covers all topics by default\\n  - `requireMention` must be `false` if Lucca does not want to mention the bot each time\\n  - BotFather privacy must be disabled (Lucca says it already is)\\n  - current config likely still blocks topic replies because `groupPolicy` is `allowlist` and `groups.*.requireMention` had been true; group/topic response remains unresolved.\\n- Lucca is considering/likes the idea of a dedicated independent Research Agent with preset subagents (different models, skills, search goals) so Tobias can trigger it instead of improvising research ad hoc each time.\\n- Research on Claude Code sidecar usage concluded: using Claude Code subscription locally as a premium sidecar/worker for OpenClaw is viable for strong long-form tasks (e.g., script writing), but should be treated as a local premium worker with fallback, not as the universal backbone, due to auth/headless/operational fragility.\\n\",\n  \"path\": \"memory/2026-03-29.md\"\n}"}],"details":{"text":"  - a long-run validation script failed due to Python encoding / syntax issues, so the validation test was not valid.\n- A stale zombie task named `Claude Code sidecar viability research (retest)` remained marked as running in `active_tasks.json` even though it had completed, causing false Telegram updates on 2026-03-29; Lucca was disturbed by these ghost notifications.\n- Lucca wants truly separate conversations/sessions by subject. Research conclusion: Telegram private DM is poor for this; a private Telegram group with Topics is the best route if he wants visible separation inside Telegram.\n- For Telegram topics/groups with OpenClaw, the key config findings were:\n  - parent group allowlisting covers all topics by default\n  - `requireMention` must be `false` if Lucca does not want to mention the bot each time\n  - BotFather privacy must be disabled (Lucca says it already is)\n  - current config likely still blocks topic replies because `groupPolicy` is `allowlist` and `groups.*.requireMention` had been true; group/topic response remains unresolved.\n- Lucca is considering/likes the idea of a dedicated independent Research Agent with preset subagents (different models, skills, search goals) so Tobias can trigger it instead of improvising research ad hoc each time.\n- Research on Claude Code sidecar usage concluded: using Claude Code subscription locally as a premium sidecar/worker for OpenClaw is viable for strong long-form tasks (e.g., script writing), but should be treated as a local premium worker with fallback, not as the universal backbone, due to auth/headless/operational fragility.\n","path":"memory/2026-03-29.md"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774880995087}}
{"type":"message","id":"494ec24e","parentId":"48fe2c12","timestamp":"2026-03-30T14:30:04.197Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Sim — fui buscar a memória antes de te responder.\n\nEstávamos sobretudo em torno de 3 frentes:\n- **separação real de conversas por assunto**: a conclusão foi que **DM do Telegram é fraco para isso** e que o melhor caminho seria um **grupo privado com Topics**. Source: memory/2026-03-29.md#L18-L26\n- **configuração do OpenClaw para responder nesses tópicos**: os pontos críticos eram `requireMention=false`, privacy do BotFather desligada, e havia suspeita de bloqueio por causa de `groupPolicy=allowlist` + `groups.*.requireMention=true`. Isso ainda estava **por resolver**. Source: memory/2026-03-29.md#L18-L26\n- **ideia de arquitetura**: tu gostaste da possibilidade de um **Research Agent dedicado**, com subagentes/modelos pré-definidos, em vez de eu improvisar research sempre do zero. Também discutimos que **Claude Code como sidecar premium local é viável**, mas não deve ser o backbone universal por fragilidade operacional. Source: memory/2026-03-29.md#L18-L26\n\nEm paralelo, também houve o problema do **watchdog / zombie tasks** a mandar notificações fantasmas, o que te incomodou bastante.\n\nSe quiseres, eu posso retomar já de onde faz mais sentido:\n1. **resolver a parte de Telegram Topics/OpenClaw**,  \n2. **desenhar o Research Agent dedicado**, ou  \n3. **limpar a arquitetura do watchdog/notificações**.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0047bd771936d8e20169ca88e64d8081958da75fb1e9689236\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":458,"output":344,"cacheRead":16768,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":17570,"cost":{"input":0.0011450000000000002,"output":0.0051600000000000005,"cacheRead":0.0041919999999999995,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.010497}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774880995712,"responseId":"resp_0047bd771936d8e20169ca88e5b4408195828f5388a37e42a7"}}
{"type":"message","id":"42c4cafc","parentId":"494ec24e","timestamp":"2026-03-30T14:31:15.994Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Mon 2026-03-30 11:31 GMT-3] isso tudo ja fizemos ja. Que pensa vc não salvou o que estávamos falando sobre o departamento de edição da content factory com openclaw. Vc lembra dos agentes que vc lançou sobre C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\reviews\\tobias_review_29mar?"}],"timestamp":1774881075924}}
