nds, then stop and alert.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\KnowledgeBase\\MattGanzak\\HeygenWorkflowLesson\\sprint_setup_guide.docx.txt:730:PublisherAgent runs at 12:00 PM every day. It picks up every job you've marked as 'approved', writes a platform-appropriate caption with hashtags, determines the next available posting slot for each platform, and schedules everything through Buffer.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\KnowledgeBase\\MattGanzak\\HeygenWorkflowLesson\\sprint_setup_guide.docx.txt:738:* Schedule: 0 12 * * *  (12:00 PM every day)\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\KnowledgeBase\\MattGanzak\\HeygenWorkflowLesson\\sprint_setup_guide.docx.txt:765:TikTok: 7:30 AM, 12:00 PM, 7:00 PM\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\KnowledgeBase\\MattGanzak\\HeygenWorkflowLesson\\sprint_setup_guide.docx.txt:766:Instagram Reels: 9:30 AM, 1:00 PM\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\KnowledgeBase\\MattGanzak\\HeygenWorkflowLesson\\sprint_setup_guide.docx.txt:767:YouTube Shorts: 1:00 PM\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\KnowledgeBase\\MattGanzak\\HeygenWorkflowLesson\\sprint_setup_guide.docx.txt:897:12:00 PM\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\KnowledgeBase\\MattGanzak\\HeygenWorkflowLesson\\transcription.txt:1:automation with Hey Jen, uh, step-by-step on how to create content. If you're creating content like I do on social media, if you just want like talking head type content, uh, this is exactly how to do it and automate it with open claw, uh, in the last video talking about UGC, that's more for, if you want like a model created or somebody like that, then you could create that with cling or VO three, et cetera. So I still want to do that video, but I want to do this one to talk about like talking head videos and how to program that. So let's go through step-by-step how this is going to work. So again, I'm not going to read through everything, but I'll give you access to this below. So you're going to need HeyGen, 11 Labs. And I'll talk about the breakdown of HeyGen and 11 Labs because HeyGen will generate voice for you based upon what you've already given it. But the downside is the quality might not be as good. So you can do it without 11 Labs or you can do it with 11 Labs. So definitely test it both ways. Costs will go up a little bit if you're generating the audio and then feeding the audio. into HeyGen and then it's syncing the mouth and blah, blah, blah, blah, blah. If you want to auto schedule, you can use buffer. So I'll give you a walkthrough on that, on how we can schedule buffer. And if you want to put this into Google Docs, you could do that. I'll walk through that a little bit. And then I have Slack. Slack is mine, but you don't necessarily need that. But I want an update on how things are going on. So it would just be whichever channel you're using to communicate with your bot. Cool? Cool. All right. So we're training assets. So you need at least 10 to 20, uh, 10 seconds to 20 minutes worth of continuous uncut recording. So this is where we start training the avatar. I know it says we need at least 20 seconds, but the more you feed it, the better. And also when you're creating that video, like don't make any like quick head movements and don't be blinking like crazy because it will mess things up. So when I record and I'm making these, I'm trying to stay perfectly like I'm doing it right now. I'm trying to stay perfectly still talking to you and trying to keep my eyes open as much as possible. I know I just blinked but try to keep your eyes open as much as possible as you're talking about it. Don make too many facial expressions because it won really render correctly Like be kind of robotic in a sense So I mean it kind of 