 visible through his open visor, flushed with adrenaline and stubborn pride under the warm glow of the late afternoon sun. Renaissance oil painting with dramatic Baroque lighting, 16:9 aspect ratio.\"\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\accounts\\001_dark_forensics\\data\\pt\\a_morte_de_henrique_ii_num_torneio_foi_muito_mais_\\video_spec.json:4385:\"image_prompt\": \"Using the provided portrait reference as the absolute identity lock, extreme close-up of Henry II's eyes through the narrow, horizontal slit of his golden tournament visor. Maintain the character's piercing gaze, now dilated with obsessive, pathological focus. His brow is furrowed in a refusal that borders on madness. The reflection of the distant, silhouetted Count of Montgomery is visible in the polished steel of the visor. The lighting is claustrophobic and intense, focusing entirely on the King's singular, destructive determination. Renaissance oil painting with dramatic Baroque lighting, 16:9 aspect ratio.\"\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\accounts\\001_dark_forensics\\data\\pt\\a_morte_de_henrique_ii_num_torneio_foi_muito_mais_\\video_spec.json:5239:\"image_prompt\": \"Using the provided portrait reference as the absolute identity lock, medium shot of Duarte I of Portugal in his 15th-century study. Maintain the character's intelligent dark eyes, neatly trimmed dark beard, and high forehead. His elegant fingers rest on the open pages of a leather-bound treatise, illuminated by the soft, scholarly light from a high window. His expression is one of melancholic wisdom, as if foreseeing the tragedy of a century later. The rich textures of his crimson velvet tunic and the heavy gold chain of office catch the gentle, diffused light. Renaissance oil painting with dramatic Baroque lighting, 16:9 aspect ratio.\"\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\accounts\\001_dark_forensics\\data\\pt\\a_morte_de_henrique_ii_num_torneio_foi_muito_mais_\\video_spec.json:5856:\"what_to_show\": \"The moment of impact at sunset; Montgomery's shattered lance exploding into splinters against Henry II's golden visor, the orange glow of the setting sun catching the dust and flying wood fragments, the two armored figures locked in a violent, frozen embrace of steel, the King's head snapped back by the force\",\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\accounts\\001_dark_forensics\\data\\pt\\a_morte_de_henrique_ii_num_torneio_foi_muito_mais_\\video_spec.json:5857:\"image_prompt\": \"Using the provided portrait references, wide action shot of the moment of impact at sunset. Subject A (Montgomery) is the primary focus, his shattered lance exploding into splinters against the golden visor of Subject B (Henry II). The orange glow of the setting sun catches the flying wood fragments and dust, creating sharp highlights against the dark, dramatic sky. The two armored figures are locked in a violent, frozen embrace of steel, the King's head snapped back by the sheer force of the blow. The textures of the polished steel and silk sash are rendered with intense chiaroscuro. Renaissance oil painting with dramatic Baroque lighting, 16:9 aspect ratio.\"\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\accounts\\001_dark_forensics\\data\\pt\\a_morte_de_henrique_ii_num_torneio_foi_muito_mais_\\video_spec.json:7534:\"what_to_show\": \"Ambroise Par� sitting at a desk, his face illuminated by a single candle, looking down at a manuscript with a quill in hand, his expression one of weary resignation as he crosses out lines in his original notes, shadows obscuring the hands of an unseen figure standing behind him.\",\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\accounts\\001_dark_forensics\\data\\pt\\a_morte_de_henrique_ii_num_torneio_foi_muito_mais_\\video_spec.json:7535:\"image_prompt\": \"Using the provided portrait reference, medium shot of Ambroise Par� sitting at a dark wooden desk, his face illuminated by a single candle. He looks down at a manuscript with a quill in hand, his expression one of weary resignation as he crosses out lines in his original notes. Shadows obscure the hands of an unseen figure standing behind him, representing the court's influence. Renaissance oil painting with dramatic Baroque lighting, 16:9 aspect ratio.\"\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\accounts\\001_dark_forensics\\data\\pt\\a_morte_de_henrique_ii_num_torneio_foi_muito_mais_\\video_spec.json:7795:\"what_to_show\": \"A dusty, dimly lit library archive with stacks of ancient, yellowed parchment, a single beam of light hitting a misplaced document folder, revealing the faded ink of original manuscript pages.\",\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\accounts\\001_dark_forensics\\data\\pt\\a_morte_de_henrique_ii_num_torneio_foi_muito_mais_\\video_spec.json:7796:\"image_prompt\": \"Wide shot of a dusty, dimly lit library archive with stacks of ancient, yellowed parchment. A single beam of light hits a misplaced document folder, revealing the faded ink of original manuscript pages. The atmosphere is mysterious and historical. Renaissance oil painting with dramatic Baroque lighting, 16:9 aspect ratio.\"\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\accounts\\001_dark_forensics\\data\\pt\\a_morte_de_henrique_ii_num_torneio_foi_muito_mais_\\video_spec.json:8227:\"what_to_show\": \"Henri Mondor in a 20th-century study, wearing scholarly attire, holding two different manuscripts side-by-side, his face lit with the intensity of discovery, the contrast between the old paper and his modern spectacles creating a bridge between eras.\",\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\accounts\\001_dark_forensics\\data\\pt\\a_morte_de_henrique_ii_num_torneio_foi_muito_mais_\\video_spec.json:8228:\"image_prompt\": \"Using the provided portrait reference, medium shot of Henri Mondor in a study, wearing scholarly attire. He holds two different manuscripts side-by-side, his face lit with the intensity of discovery. The contrast between the old paper and his modern spectacles creates a bridge between eras. Renaissance oil painting with dramatic Baroque lighting, 16:9 aspect ratio.\"\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\accounts\\001_dark_forensics\\data\\pt\\a_morte_de_henrique_ii_num_torneio_foi_muito_mais_\\video_spec.json:10772:\"what_to_show\": \"Close-up of a blood-stained silver tray holding several jagged wooden splinters and a sharp steel bistoury, the metal reflecting the warm candlelight, in the blurred background the silhouette of a surgeon's hands working over a pale brow, emphasizing the physical evidence of the trauma that cannot be undone.\",\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\accounts\\001_dark_forensics\\data\\pt\\a_morte_de_henrique_ii_num_torneio_foi_muito_mais_\\video_spec.json:10773:\"image_prompt\": \"Using the provided portrait reference as the identity lock, close-up of a blood-stained silver tray holding several jagged wooden splinters and a sharp steel bistoury. The metal reflects the warm candlelight, while in the blurred background, the pale silhouette of King Henry II lies in his bed, emphasizing the physical evidence of trauma. The King, in his downfall phase, remains a fading presence. The textures of blood-stained linen and cold steel are rendered with visceral detail. Renaissance oil painting with dramatic Baroque lighting, 16:9 aspect ratio.\"\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\accounts\\001_dark_forensics\\data\\pt\\a_morte_de_henrique_ii_num_torneio_foi_muito_mais_\\video_spec.json:12226:\"image_prompt\": \"Using the provided portrait reference as the identity lock, extreme close-up of King Henry II's right eye. The eye is glazed and unfocused, reflecting the flickering orange light of a single candle, the pupil dilated and fixed. The surrounding pale, sweaty skin of his brow captures the neurological dissolution. The King is in his downfall phase, his majesty lost to physical decay. Renaissance oil painting with dramatic Baroque lighting, 16:9 aspect ratio.\"\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\accounts\\001_dark_forensics\\data\\pt\\a_morte_de_henrique_ii_num_torneio_foi_muito_mais_\\video_spec.json:12938:\"image_prompt\": \"Using the provided portrait reference as the identity lock, medium shot of a barber-surgeon's hand holding a small lancet over the pale, vein-lined arm of King Henry II. Dark blood begins to flow into a shallow silver bowl held below. In the background, a thick, green herbal cataplasm is being prepared. The King, in his downfall phase, looks frail and drained under the cold, sallow light of a high window, emphasizing physical depletion and clinical cruelty. Renaissance oil painting with dramatic Baroque lighting, 16:9 aspect ratio.\"\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\accounts\\001_dark_forensics\\data\\pt\\a_morte_de_henrique_ii_num_torneio_foi_muito_mais_\\video_spec.json:13826:\"image_prompt\": \"Using the provided portrait reference as the absolute identity lock, close-up shot of Henry II during a brutal medical examination. The king's face is pale and gaunt, his expression motionless and vacant in the dim light. In the foreground, a silver spoon drips a dark, viscous liquid near the king's partially open mouth, while a second, unnamed physician's hand holds a heated metal rod near the king's foot, just out of focus. The king's pale skin contrasts sharply with the deep, suffocating shadows of the bedchamber. The scene captures the harrowing vulnerability of the monarch. Renaissance oil painting with dramatic Baroque lighting, 16:9 aspect ratio.\"\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factor