{"type":"message","id":"dd96df85","parentId":"61edb0dd","timestamp":"2026-03-30T17:21:39.730Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_J0joJXfuJSYxZZm9v88daulR|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169cab122f7a08195b6c2b79ad0364e9f","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\r\nGoogle Sheets API client.\r\n\r\nContent Factory Pro V2 - Shared Component\r\nMigrated from V1: content_factory/clients/google_sheets.py\r\n\r\nV2 Changes:\r\n- Removed dependency on V1 config singleton\r\n- credentials_path is now REQUIRED in __init__\r\n- sheet_id is now REQUIRED in all methods (no defaults)\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nfrom typing import Dict, List, Optional\r\n\r\nimport gspread\r\nfrom google.oauth2.service_account import Credentials\r\nfrom loguru import logger\r\n\r\nfrom ..models.script_data import ScriptData\r\nfrom ..utils.header_matcher import HeaderMatcher\r\n\r\n\r\nclass GoogleSheetsClient:\r\n    \"\"\"Client for interacting with Google Sheets API.\"\"\"\r\n\r\n    SCOPES = [\r\n        \"https://www.googleapis.com/auth/spreadsheets\",\r\n        \"https://www.googleapis.com/auth/drive\",\r\n    ]\r\n\r\n    def __init__(self, credentials_path: str):\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        Initialize Google Sheets client.\r\n\r\n        Args:\r\n            credentials_path: Path to service account credentials JSON (REQUIRED)\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        if not credentials_path:\r\n            raise ValueError(\"Google Sheets credentials path is required\")\r\n\r\n        self.credentials_path = credentials_path\r\n        self._client: Optional[gspread.Client] = None\r\n\r\n    @property\r\n    def client(self) -> gspread.Client:\r\n        \"\"\"Get or create gspread client.\"\"\"\r\n        if self._client is None:\r\n            creds = Credentials.from_service_account_file(\r\n                self.credentials_path, scopes=self.SCOPES\r\n            )\r\n            self._client = gspread.authorize(creds)\r\n        return self._client\r\n\r\n    def fetch_next_script(\r\n        self, sheet_id: str, sheet_name: str = \"Página1\"\r\n    ) -> Optional[ScriptData]:\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        Fetch next script with status 'to do' from Google Sheets.\r\n\r\n        DEPRECATED: Use fetch_and_lock_script() instead for production.\r\n        This method doesn't implement locking.\r\n\r\n        Args:\r\n            sheet_id: Google Sheets document ID (REQUIRED)\r\n            sheet_name: Sheet name (default: \"Página1\")\r\n\r\n        Returns:\r\n            ScriptData if found, None otherwise\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        if not sheet_id:\r\n            raise ValueError(\"sheet_id is required\")\r\n\r\n        try:\r\n            logger.info(f\"Fetching next script from sheet: {sheet_id}\")\r\n\r\n            # Open spreadsheet\r\n            spreadsheet = self.client.open_by_key(sheet_id)\r\n            worksheet = spreadsheet.worksheet(sheet_name)\r\n\r\n            # Get all records\r\n            records = worksheet.get_all_records()\r\n\r\n            # Find first record with status 'to do'\r\n            for idx, record in enumerate(records, start=2):  # Start at row 2 (after header)\r\n                if record.get(\"Status\", \"\").lower() == \"to do\":\r\n                    script_data = ScriptData(\r\n                        title=record.get(\"Title\", \"\"),\r\n                        description=record.get(\"Description\", \"\"),\r\n                        script=record.get(\"Script\", \"\"),\r\n                        row_number=idx,\r\n                        status=record.get(\"Status\", \"to do\"),\r\n                        id=record.get(\"ID\", \"\"),\r\n                    )\r\n\r\n                    logger.success(f\"Found script: {script_data.title} (row {idx})\")\r\n                    return script_data\r\n\r\n            logger.warning(\"No scripts with status 'to do' found\")\r\n            return None\r\n\r\n        except Exception as e:\r\n            logger.error(f\"Error fetching script: {e}\")\r\n            raise\r\n\r\n    def fetch_and_lock_script(\r\n        self, sheet_id: str, sheet_name: str = \"Página1\", account_id: str = \"\"\r\n    ) -> Optional[ScriptData]:\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        Fetch next script and atomically lock it by changing status to 'processing'.\r\n\r\n        This prevents race conditions when multiple instances are running.\r\n\r\n        Args:\r\n            sheet_id: Google Sheets document ID (REQUIRED)\r\n            sheet_name: Sheet name (default: \"Página1\")\r\n            account_id: Account ID for account-specific column handling (e.g., \"012\")\r\n\r\n        Returns:\r\n            ScriptData if found, None otherwise\r\n\r\n        Note:\r\n            The script status will be changed to 'processing'.\r\n            Use release_script() to mark as 'done' or 'error'.\r\n\r\n            Account 012 has different column structure:\r\n            - Column F is \"Personagem\" (character), NOT \"Processing_Started\"\r\n            - Uses HeaderMatcher for robust column lookup\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        if not sheet_id:\r\n            raise ValueError(\"sheet_id is required\")\r\n\r\n        try:\r\n            logger.info(f\"Fetching and locking script from sheet: {sheet_id} (account: {account_id or 'legacy'})\")\r\n\r\n            # Open spreadsheet\r\n            spreadsheet = self.client.open_by_key(sheet_id)\r\n            worksheet = spreadsheet.worksheet(sheet_name)\r\n\r\n            # Get headers for column lookup (account 012)\r\n            headers = worksheet.row_values(1) if account_id == \"012\" else []\r\n\r\n            # Get all records\r\n            records = worksheet.get_all_records()\r\n\r\n            # Find first record with status 'to do'\r\n            for idx, record in enumerate(records, start=2):  # Start at row 2 (after header)\r\n                # Check status - use HeaderMatcher for account 012\r\n                if account_id == \"012\":\r\n                    status_value = HeaderMatcher.get_value_by_field(record, headers, \"status\") or \"\"\r\n                else:\r\n                    status_value = record.get(\"Status\", \"\")\r\n\r\n                if status_value.lower() == \"to do\":\r\n                    # Extract character for account 012\r\n                    character = None\r\n                    if account_id == \"012\":\r\n                        character = HeaderMatcher.get_value_by_field(record, headers, \"personagem\")\r\n                        if character:\r\n                            character = character.strip().lower()\r\n                            logger.info(f\"  [CHARACTER] Found: {character}\")\r\n\r\n                    script_data = ScriptData(\r\n                        title=record.get(\"Title\", \"\") or HeaderMatcher.get_value_by_field(record, headers, \"title\") or \"\",\r\n                        description=record.get(\"Description\", \"\") or HeaderMatcher.get_value_by_field(record, headers, \"description\") or \"\",\r\n                        script=record.get(\"Script\", \"\") or HeaderMatcher.get_value_by_field(record, headers, \"script\") or \"\",\r\n                        row_number=idx,\r\n                        status=\"to do\",  # Original status\r\n                        id=record.get(\"ID\", \"\") or HeaderMatcher.get_value_by_field(record, headers, \"id\") or \"\",\r\n                        character=character,  # Account 012: from Personagem column\r\n                    )\r\n\r\n                    # ATOMIC LOCK: Immediately update status to 'processing'\r\n                    from datetime import datetime\r\n                    timestamp = datetime.now().isoformat()\r\n\r\n                    if account_id == \"012\":\r\n                        # Account 012: Use HeaderMatcher to find Status column\r\n                        # DO NOT write to Personagem column (F)!\r\n                        status_col = HeaderMatcher.find_column_index(headers, \"status\")\r\n                        if status_col:\r\n                            worksheet.update_cell(idx, status_col, \"processing\")\r\n                            logger.info(f\"  [LOCK] Status updated via HeaderMatcher (col {status_col})\")\r\n                        else:\r\n                            # Fallback to column E\r\n                            worksheet.update(f\"E{idx}\", [[\"processing\"]])\r\n                            logger.warning(\"  [LOCK] Status column not found, using fallback (E)\")\r\n                    else:\r\n                        # Legacy accounts (001-011): Fixed column positions\r\n                        # Update Status column (E)\r\n                        worksheet.update(f\"E{idx}\", [[\"processing\"]])\r\n\r\n                        # Update Processing_Started column (F) if exists\r\n                        try:\r\n                            worksheet.update(f\"F{idx}\", [[timestamp]])\r\n                        except Exception as e:\r\n                            logger.warning(f\"Could not update Processing_Started timestamp: {e}\")\r\n\r\n                    logger.success(\r\n                        f\"[OK] Script locked: {script_data.title} (row {idx})\"\r\n                    )\r\n                    if character:\r\n                        logger.info(f\"  [OK] Character: {character}\")\r\n\r\n                    return script_data\r\n\r\n            logger.warning(\"No scripts with status 'to do' found\")\r\n            return None\r\n\r\n        except Exception as e:\r\n            logger.error(f\"Error fetching and locking script: {e}\")\r\n            raise\r\n\r\n    def release_script(\r\n        self,\r\n        row_number: int,\r\n        success: bool,\r\n        sheet_id: str,\r\n        sheet_name: str = \"Página1\",\r\n        error_message: str = \"\",\r\n        account_id: str = \"\",\r\n    ) -> None:\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        Release script lock by updating status.\r\n\r\n        Args:\r\n            row_number: Row number in the sheet\r\n            success: True to mark as 'done', False to mark as 'error'\r\n            sheet_id: Google Sheets document ID (REQUIRED)\r\n            sheet_name: Sheet name (default: \"Página1\")\r\n            error_message: Error message to log (if failure)\r\n            account_id: Account ID that processed the script\r\n\r\n        Note:\r\n            - If success=True: Status -> 'done'\r\n            - If success=False: Status -> 'error'\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        if not sheet_id:\r\n            raise ValueError(\"sheet_id is required\")\r\n\r\n        try:\r\n            from datetime import datetime\r\n\r\n            timestamp = datetime.now().isoformat()\r\n\r\n            # Open spreadsheet\r\n            spreadsheet = self.client.open_by_key(sheet_id)\r\n            worksheet = spreadsheet.worksheet(sheet_name)\r\n\r\n            if success:\r\n                # Mark as done\r\n                worksheet.update(f\"E{row_number}\", [[\"done\"]])\r\n\r\n                # Update Processing_Completed column (G) if exists\r\n                try:\r\n                    worksheet.update(f\"G{row_number}\", [[timestamp]])\r\n                except Exception:\r\n                    pass\r\n\r\n                # Update Account_Used column (H) if exists\r\n                if account_id:\r\n                    try:\r\n                        worksheet.update(f\"H{row_number}\", [[account_id]])\r\n                    except Exception:\r\n                        pass\r\n\r\n                logger.success(f\"[OK] Script released as 'done' (row {row_number})\")\r\n            else:\r\n                # Mark as error\r\n                worksheet.update(f\"E{row_number}\", [[\"error\"]])\r\n\r\n                # Optionally log error message\r\n                # Note: This requires an error_message column in the sheet\r\n                # For now, we just log it\r\n\r\n                logger.warning(\r\n                    f\"[!]  Script released as 'error' (row {row_number}): {error_message}\"\r\n                )\r\n\r\n        except Exception as e:\r\n            logger.error(f\"Error releasing script lock: {e}\")\r\n            # Don't raise - this is cleanup, we don't want to fail the whole workflow\r\n            # if we can't update the sheet\r\n\r\n    def mark_script_used(\r\n        self,\r\n        row_number: int,\r\n        sheet_id: str,\r\n        sheet_name: str = \"Página1\",\r\n        used_date: Optional[str] = None,\r\n    ) -> None:\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        Mark script as used by updating status to 'done'.\r\n\r\n        Args:\r\n            row_number: Row number to update\r\n            sheet_id: Google Sheets document ID (REQUIRED)\r\n            sheet_name: Sheet name (default: \"Página1\")\r\n            used_date: Date used (default: current date/time)\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        if not sheet_id:\r\n            raise ValueError(\"sheet_id is required\")\r\n\r\n        try:\r\n            from datetime import datetime\r\n\r\n            if used_date is None:\r\n                used_date = datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S\")\r\n\r\n            logger.info(f\"Marking script as used (row {row_number})\")\r\n\r\n            spreadsheet = self.client.open_by_key(sheet_id)\r\n            worksheet = spreadsheet.worksheet(sheet_name)\r\n\r\n            # Get header to find column indices\r\n            headers = worksheet.row_values(1)\r\n            status_col = headers.index(\"Status\") + 1\r\n            used_date_col = headers.index(\"Used_Date\") + 1\r\n\r\n            # Update status\r\n            worksheet.update_cell(row_number, status_col, \"done\")\r\n            worksheet.update_cell(row_number, used_date_col, used_date)\r\n\r\n            logger.success(f\"Script marked as used (row {row_number})\")\r\n\r\n        except Exception as e:\r\n            logger.error(f\"Error marking script as used: {e}\")\r\n            raise\r\n\r\n    def append_video_data(\r\n        self,\r\n        video_data: Dict[str, str],\r\n        sheet_id: str,\r\n        sheet_name: str = \"Página1\",\r\n    ) -> None:\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        Append video data to output sheet.\r\n\r\n        Args:\r\n            video_data: Dictionary with video metadata\r\n            sheet_id: Google Sheets document ID (REQUIRED)\r\n            sheet_name: Sheet name (default: \"Página1\")\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        if not sheet_id:\r\n            raise ValueError(\"sheet_id is required\")\r\n\r\n        try:\r\n            logger.info(f\"Appending video data to sheet: {sheet_id}\")\r\n\r\n            spreadsheet = self.client.open_by_key(sheet_id)\r\n            worksheet = spreadsheet.worksheet(sheet_name)\r\n\r\n            # Get headers to determine order\r\n            headers = worksheet.row_values(1)\r\n\r\n            # Build row in same order as headers\r\n            row = []\r\n            for header in headers:\r\n                row.append(video_data.get(header, \"\"))\r\n\r\n            # Find next empty row explicitly (avoids issues with Google Sheets tables)\r\n            col_a_values = worksheet.col_values(1)\r\n            next_row = len(col_a_values) + 1\r\n\r\n            # Safety: ensure we're not overwriting existing data\r\n            while next_row > 1:\r\n                existing_row = worksheet.row_values(next_row)\r\n                if not any(existing_row):  # Row is empty\r\n                    break\r\n                next_row += 1\r\n\r\n            logger.info(f\"Inserting video data at row {next_row}\")\r\n\r\n            # Insert at specific row instead of using append_row\r\n            worksheet.insert_row(row, next_row)\r\n\r\n            logger.success(f\"Video data appended: {video_data.get('File Name', 'Unknown')}\")\r\n\r\n        except Exception as e:\r\n            logger.error(f\"Error appending video data: {e}\")\r\n            raise\r\n\r\n    def append_tracking_data(\r\n        self,\r\n        tracking_data: Dict[str, str],\r\n        sheet_id: str,\r\n        sheet_name: str = \"Página1\",\r\n    ) -> None:\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        Append video tracking data to tracking sheet.\r\n\r\n        Uses robust header matching to handle variations in column names\r\n        (spaces, case differences, typos).\r\n\r\n        Args:\r\n            tracking_data: Dictionary with tracking metadata (Name, Description, Keywords, etc.)\r\n            sheet_id: Google Sheets tracking sheet ID (REQUIRED)\r\n            sheet_name: Sheet name (default: \"Página1\")\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        if not sheet_id:\r\n            raise ValueError(\"sheet_id is required\")\r\n\r\n        try:\r\n            logger.info(f\"Appending tracking data to sheet: {sheet_id}\")\r\n\r\n            spreadsheet = self.client.open_by_key(sheet_id)\r\n            worksheet = spreadsheet.worksheet(sheet_name)\r\n\r\n            # Get headers to determine column order\r\n            headers = worksheet.row_values(1)\r\n            logger.debug(f\"Sheet headers ({len(headers)} columns): {headers}\")\r\n            logger.debug(f\"Data keys ({len(tracking_data)} fields): {list(tracking_data.keys())}\")\r\n\r\n            # Build row using robust header matching\r\n            # This tolerates: \"Name \" vs \"Name\", \"youtube url\" vs \"YouTube URL\", etc.\r\n            row = HeaderMatcher.build_row(\r\n                headers=headers,\r\n                data=tracking_data,\r\n                require_all=False  # Don't error on empty optional fields\r\n            )\r\n\r\n            logger.debug(f\"Built row with {len(row)} columns matching sheet headers\")\r\n\r\n            # Find next empty row explicitly (avoids issues with Google Sheets tables)\r\n            col_a_values = worksheet.col_values(1)\r\n            next_row = len(col_a_values) + 1\r\n\r\n            # Safety: ensure we're not overwriting existing data\r\n            while next_row > 1:\r\n                existing_row = worksheet.row_values(next_row)\r\n                if not any(existing_row):  # Row is empty\r\n                    break\r\n                next_row += 1\r\n\r\n            logger.info(f\"Inserting tracking data at row {next_row}\")\r\n\r\n            # Insert at specific row instead of using append_row\r\n            worksheet.insert_row(row, next_row)\r\n\r\n            # Log success (try both \"Name\" and \"Name \" for backward compatibility)\r\n            video_name = tracking_data.get('Name', tracking_data.get('Name ', 'Unknown'))\r\n            logger.success(f\"[OK] Tracking data appended: {video_name}\")\r\n\r\n        except Exception as e:\r\n            logger.error(f\"Error appending tracking data: {e}\")\r\n            raise\r\n\r\n    def update_cell(\r\n        self,\r\n        row: int,\r\n        col: int,\r\n        value: str,\r\n        sheet_id: str,\r\n        sheet_name: str = \"Página1\",\r\n    ) -> None:\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        Update a specific cell.\r\n\r\n        Args:\r\n            row: Row number (1-indexed)\r\n            col: Column number (1-indexed)\r\n            value: Value to set\r\n            sheet_id: Google Sheets document ID (REQUIRED)\r\n            sheet_name: Sheet name\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        if not sheet_id:\r\n            raise ValueError(\"sheet_id is required\")\r\n\r\n        try:\r\n            spreadsheet = self.client.open_by_key(sheet_id)\r\n            worksheet = spreadsheet.worksheet(sheet_name)\r\n            worksheet.update_cell(row, col, value)\r\n            logger.debug(f\"Updated cell ({row}, {col}) = {value}\")\r\n\r\n        except Exception as e:\r\n            logger.error(f\"Error updating cell: {e}\")\r\n            raise\r\n\r\n    def get_all_records(\r\n        self, sheet_id: str, sheet_name: str = \"Página1\"\r\n    ) -> List[Dict[str, str]]:\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        Get all records from sheet.\r\n\r\n        Args:\r\n            sheet_id: Google Sheets document ID (REQUIRED)\r\n            sheet_name: Sheet name\r\n\r\n        Returns:\r\n            List of records as dictionaries\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        if not sheet_id:\r\n            raise ValueError(\"sheet_id is required\")\r\n\r\n        try:\r\n            spreadsheet = self.client.open_by_key(sheet_id)\r\n            worksheet = spreadsheet.worksheet(sheet_name)\r\n            return worksheet.get_all_records()\r\n\r\n        except Exception as e:\r\n            logger.error(f\"Error getting all records: {e}\")\r\n            raise\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774891299600}}
{"type":"message","id":"8558e7d7","parentId":"dd96df85","timestamp":"2026-03-30T17:21:44.147Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_k7DogzOBP4ewn9jpUdGDLEpj|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169cab127f11081958705df2db9de54f3","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\shared\\models\\script_data.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\content_factory_v3\\\\shared\\\\models\\\\script_data.py\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":3809,"output":42,"cacheRead":116992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":120843,"cost":{"input":0.009522500000000001,"output":0.00063,"cacheRead":0.029248,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.039400500000000005}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774891300768,"responseId":"resp_0047bd771936d8e20169cab12676c8819599c3c94c46fb2d4c"}}
{"type":"message","id":"764f4130","parentId":"8558e7d7","timestamp":"2026-03-30T17:21:44.730Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_k7DogzOBP4ewn9jpUdGDLEpj|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169cab127f11081958705df2db9de54f3","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"Script and transcription data models.\"\"\"\n\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom typing import List, Optional\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass ScriptData:\n    \"\"\"Data from Google Sheets script fetch.\"\"\"\n\n    title: str\n    description: str\n    script: str\n    row_number: int\n    status: str = \"to do\"\n    id: Optional[str] = None\n    character: Optional[str] = None  # Account 012: Character from Personagem column\n\n    @property\n    def cleaned_script(self) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Clean script by removing special characters and extra whitespace.\"\"\"\n        import re\n\n        cleaned = self.script.replace(\"\\n\", \" \").replace(\"\\r\", \" \").replace(\"\\t\", \" \")\n        cleaned = re.sub(r'[\"\"'']', \" \", cleaned)\n        cleaned = re.sub(r\"\\s+\", \" \", cleaned)\n        return cleaned.strip()\n\n    @property\n    def word_count(self) -> int:\n        \"\"\"Count words in cleaned script.\"\"\"\n        return len([word for word in self.cleaned_script.split() if word])\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass WordTiming:\n    \"\"\"Timing information for a single word.\"\"\"\n\n    word: str\n    start: float\n    end: float\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass SegmentData:\n    \"\"\"A single segment from WhisperX transcription.\"\"\"\n\n    index: int\n    start: float\n    end: float\n    text: str\n    words: List[WordTiming] = field(default_factory=list)\n\n    @property\n    def duration(self) -> float:\n        \"\"\"Duration of the segment in seconds.\"\"\"\n        return self.end - self.start\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass GroupedSegment:\n    \"\"\"Multiple segments grouped together for a single image.\"\"\"\n\n    index: int\n    start: float\n    end: float\n    text: str\n    original_segments: List[SegmentData]\n    segments_count: int\n    time_window: str  # \"0-2min\", \"2-6min\", \"6-10min\", \"10+min\"\n\n    # Account 009: Video search system\n    media_type: Optional[str] = None  # \"video\" | \"image\" | None\n    media_path: Optional[str] = None  # Path to final media (video or animated image)\n\n    # Accounts 003, 005: Screenplay Agent narrative context\n    narrative_context: Optional[str] = None  # Rich narrative summary for enhanced prompts\n\n    @property\n    def duration(self) -> float:\n        \"\"\"Duration of the grouped segment in seconds.\"\"\"\n        return self.end - self.start\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass TranscriptionData:\n    \"\"\"Complete transcription data from WhisperX.\"\"\"\n\n    segments: List[SegmentData]\n    total_duration: float\n    word_count: int\n    full_transcript: str\n\n    @staticmethod\n    def from_whisperx_response(response: dict) -> \"TranscriptionData\":\n        \"\"\"Create TranscriptionData from WhisperX API response.\"\"\"\n        segments = []\n\n        for idx, seg in enumerate(response.get(\"segments\", [])):\n            words = []\n            if \"words\" in seg and seg[\"words\"]:\n                words = [\n                    WordTiming(\n                        word=w.get(\"word\", w.get(\"text\", \"\")),\n                        start=w.get(\"start\", 0),\n                        end=w.get(\"end\", 0),\n                    )\n                    for w in seg[\"words\"]\n                ]\n\n            segment = SegmentData(\n                index=idx,\n                start=seg.get(\"start\", 0),\n                end=seg.get(\"end\", 0),\n                text=seg.get(\"text\", \"\").strip(),\n                words=words,\n            )\n            segments.append(segment)\n\n        total_duration = segments[-1].end if segments else 0\n        word_count = sum(len(seg.words) for seg in segments)\n        full_transcript = \" \".join(seg.text for seg in segments)\n\n        return TranscriptionData(\n            segments=segments,\n            total_duration=total_duration,\n            word_count=word_count,\n            full_transcript=full_transcript,\n        )\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass ImageDuration:\n    \"\"\"Duration information for a single image in the video.\"\"\"\n\n    index: int\n    start: float\n    end: float\n    filename: str\n\n    @property\n    def duration(self) -> float:\n        \"\"\"Duration of the image display in seconds.\"\"\"\n        return self.end - self.start\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774891304609}}
{"type":"message","id":"2db9322e","parentId":"764f4130","timestamp":"2026-03-30T17:22:16.398Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Sim — fiz a investigação certa agora e já temos uma base muito melhor para pensar o próximo step.\n\n## Síntese clara do que o V3 faz hoje no fetch + lock de script\n\nEncontrei a lógica principal em:\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\shared\\clients\\google_sheets.py`\n\nE o comportamento actual do V3 é este:\n\n---\n\n# 1. Onde o Step 1 escolhe o script\nA lógica está na classe:\n### `GoogleSheetsClient`\n\nMétodo relevante:\n### `fetch_and_lock_script(sheet_id, sheet_name=\"Página1\", account_id=\"\")`\n\nEsse é o método de produção.\nO próprio código marca o `fetch_next_script()` como:\n> **deprecated**\ne diz explicitamente para usar `fetch_and_lock_script()` em produção.\n\n---\n\n# 2. Qual critério usa para pegar a row\nHoje o V3 faz isto:\n\n### percorre os records da sheet em ordem\ne\n### pega a **primeira row** com:\n```txt\nStatus = \"to do\"\n```\n\nOu seja:\n- não há ranking sofisticado dentro da sheet\n- não escolhe por score\n- não escolhe por data\n- não escolhe por outro campo\n- simplesmente pega o **primeiro `to do` disponível**, de cima para baixo\n\nIsso é importante porque responde já a tua pergunta:\n> “nem definimos ainda qual script ele vai puxar da sheet”\n\nNo V3, a resposta actual é:\n### **o primeiro script disponível com status `to do`**\n\n---\n\n# 3. Qual coluna usa\nPara as contas legacy, o V3 assume esta estrutura fixa:\n\n### Coluna E\n- `Status`\n\n### Coluna F\n- `Processing_Started`\n\n### Coluna G\n- `Processing_Completed`\n\n### Coluna H\n- `Account_Used`\n\nNo lock de produção, ele faz:\n\n- `E{row} = processing`\n- tenta escrever `F{row} = timestamp`\n\nNo release:\n- se sucesso → `E{row} = done`\n- tenta escrever `G{row} = timestamp`\n- tenta escrever `H{row} = account_id`\n\nSe falha:\n- `E{row} = error`\n\n---\n\n# 4. Como muda para `processing`\nA lógica do lock é bem directa:\n\n### ao encontrar a primeira row `Status = to do`\nele:\n1. monta o `ScriptData`\n2. **imediatamente** actualiza a row na sheet para:\n```txt\nStatus = processing\n```\n3. opcionalmente escreve timestamp de processing start\n\nOu seja:\n### o lock no V3 é o próprio update da coluna `Status`\n\nIsso é o mecanismo anti-colisão entre máquinas.\n\n---\n\n# 5. O que isso garante\nA ideia operacional do V3 é:\n\n- só uma máquina deveria apanhar primeiro aquele `to do`\n- depois de mudar para `processing`, as outras já não o veem como elegível\n- no fim, a row sai de `processing` para:\n  - `done`\n  - ou `error`\n\n### Em termos práticos:\né um lock simples, baseado em estado de row\n\nNão é lock distribuído super formal.\nMas é:\n- claro\n- auditável\n- e aparentemente suficiente para a operação real\n\n---\n\n# 6. O que ele devolve quando puxa o script\nO V3 devolve um objeto `ScriptData` com:\n- `title`\n- `description`\n- `script`\n- `row_number`\n- `status`\n- `id`\n- `character` (caso especial da account 012)\n\nEntão, além do texto do script, o sistema já preserva:\n- a row de origem\n- title\n- description\n- id\n\nIsto é óptimo porque sugere que o novo VO não devia guardar só `script_raw.txt`.\nDeveria também preservar metadata da row.\n\n---\n\n# 7. Ponto muito importante: a semântica actual é `to do`, não `done`\nTu mencionaste que achavas que ele puxava os com `status = done`.\nMas no código que vi, o fluxo actual é:\n\n### fetch elegível:\n```txt\nStatus = to do\n```\n\n### lock:\n```txt\nStatus = processing\n```\n\n### sucesso:\n```txt\nStatus = done\n```\n\n### falha:\n```txt\nStatus = error\n```\n\nOu seja, pelo menos no código actual do V3, o `done` parece ser:\n### **script já consumido / concluído**\nnão\n### “pronto para ser pego”\n\n---\n\n# 8. O que isto muda no nosso desenho\nMuda bastante — para melhor.\n\nPorque agora eu **não recomendo inventar uma lógica nova de lock** para o VO.\nEu recomendaria isto:\n\n## Recomendação\n### o novo `script_fetch_and_lock` do VO deve espelhar a semântica do V3\nou seja:\n\n### selecção:\n- pegar a **primeira row com `Status = to do`**\n\n### lock:\n- mudar imediatamente para `processing`\n\n### metadata:\n- guardar localmente:\n  - texto do script\n  - row number\n  - title\n  - description\n  - id\n  - timestamps\n  - estado do lock\n\n---\n\n# 9. O que ainda falta definir antes do briefing\nMesmo com isto esclarecido, ainda há 2 perguntas para fechar:\n\n## A. No sistema novo, queremos manter exactamente a mesma semântica?\nMinha recomendação: **sim**, pelo menos na v1.\n\nPorque:\n- reduz risco\n- mantém compatibilidade mental com o V3\n- aproveita padrão operacional já provado\n\n## B. O VO vai actualizar directamente a sheet de scripts como o V3?\nMinha recomendação: **sim**\nporque o lock real precisa continuar na fonte partilhada, não só localmente.\n\nO artefacto local (`script_lock.json`) continua útil,\nmas ele **não substitui** o lock na sheet.\n\n---\n\n# 10. Minha conclusão\n### Resposta curta:\nSim, olhar o V3 foi a decisão certa.\n\nE a síntese arquitectural é esta:\n\n- **qual script puxar?**\n  - a primeira row com `Status = to do`\n\n- **qual coluna usa?**\n  - principalmente `Status` em **E**\n  - timestamps auxiliares em **F/G**\n  - account usada em **H**\n\n- **como muda para processing?**\n  - update imediato da sheet quando a row é seleccionada\n\n- **como evita colisão?**\n  - o lock é o próprio `Status = processing`\n\n- **o que o VO novo deveria fazer?**\n  - muito provavelmente **adaptar esta mesma semântica do V3**, não inventar outra\n\n---\n\n## Próximo passo recomendado\nAgora sim faz sentido eu escrever o briefing do próximo slice como:\n\n### **VO script fetch + sheet lock**\nbaseado explicitamente no padrão do V3:\n- `to do` → `processing`\n- persistência local em `production/.../inputs/script/`\n- checkpoint `vo_script_ready.json`\n\nSe quiseres, eu já faço esse briefing completo agora, já ancorado no comportamento real do V3.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0047bd771936d8e20169cab12c41cc81958c1adf42b4a01ad9\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":1049,"output":1519,"cacheRead":120704,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":123272,"cost":{"input":0.0026225000000000003,"output":0.022785,"cacheRead":0.030175999999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.055583499999999994}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774891305317,"responseId":"resp_0047bd771936d8e20169cab12b45cc8195b68f4d71e3a7316a"}}
