ct planning | Artifact generation |\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.claude\\plans\\bloco2v1-kms-migration.md:82:\"\"\"Shared helpers for Bloco 2 v1 KMS migration.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.claude\\plans\\bloco2v1-kms-migration.md:554:**CRITICAL:** The `self._init_tts_services()` call MUST still happen before the dispatch - the parallel processor needs `self._text_normalizer`, `self._whisperx_service`, `self._quality_gate`, `self._transcription_validator`.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.claude\\plans\\bloco2v1-kms-migration.md:567:Phase 3: GPU validation - sequential (NISQA + WhisperX)\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.claude\\plans\\bloco2v1-kms-migration.md:581:whisperx_service=self._whisperx_service,\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.claude\\plans\\bloco2v1-kms-migration.md:583:transcription_validator=self._transcription_validator,\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.claude\\plans\\bloco2v1-kms-migration.md:677:All 11 text agents follow the EXACT same migration pattern. Shown in full for the first agent, then summarized.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.claude\\plans\\bloco2v1-kms-migration.md:822:- **Phase 2 (image):** Portrait generation via `GeminiClient` + `ApiKeyManager`  KMS adapter\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.claude\\plans\\bloco2v1-kms-migration.md:846:**NOTE:** `self.key_manager` stays as the IMAGE key manager (used throughout the file for image generation). The TEXT key manager is `self._text_key_manager`.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.claude\\plans\\bloco2v1-kms-migration.md:950:This is the SIMPLEST image migration - only needs `key_manager` param.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.claude\\plans\\bloco2v1-kms-migration.md:1155:git commit -m \"feat(bloco2v1): complete KMS migration - 12 agents + orchestrator 001\"\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.claude\\plans\\bloco2v1-kms-migration.md:1182:If KMS is unreachable or migration causes issues:\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\ARCHITECTURE.md:12:- **Bloco 2** - Character identification, reference portraits, scene direction, image generation\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\ARCHITECTURE.md:13:- **Bloco 3** - Remotion project generation, audio/SFX/lettering planning, TSX file generation, rendering\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\ARCHITECTURE.md:48:- Purpose: Validates GPT planner name-only outputs against catalogs, injects exact `path`, `volume`, `duration_seconds`, `loopable` fields\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\ARCHITECTURE.md:68:- `transcription_validator.py` - WhisperX-based audio validation (60% word match threshold)\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\ARCHITECTURE.md:83:- `whisperx_service.py` - HTTP client for local WhisperX transcription server\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\ARCHITECTURE.md:94:- `gemini_client.py` - Gemini image generation\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\ARCHITECTURE.md:102:**Configuration Layer:**\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\ARCHITECTURE.md:119:5. **Step 3**: Per-scene loop: TTS polish  Gemini/ElevenLabs TTS  silence trim  WhisperX validation  `clips/clip_NNN.mp3`\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\ARCHITECTURE.md:148:- Purpose: Central contract between Bloco 2 and Bloco 3. Contains all scene data: audio paths, durations, word timestamps, image paths, character descriptions, visual direction, timing frames.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\ARCHITECTURE.md:153:- Purpose: Ground truth for all audio assets. Each track/SFX has `name`, `recommended_volume`, `path`, `duration_seconds`, `description`, `mood`, `tags`. LLMs see only names+descriptions; Python resolver injects paths+volumes.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\ARCHITECTURE.md:221:**Validation:** Two-layer TSX validation: (1) Python static checks in `tsx_validator.py` (easing names, banned fonts, path references) with auto-fix; (2) Claude SDK `render_fix` agent if compile still fails. WhisperX validates TTS audio (60% word match threshold for EN).\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\CONCERNS.md:24:- Impact: Fragile - depends on undocumented `--input-format stream-json` protocol. If Claude CLI changes its stream-json protocol, all SDK agents break silently. The fallback (prepending system prompt to user message) degrades agent quality for prompts exceeding the 30K threshold.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\CONCERNS.md:44:- Symptoms: Lettering entries fail to sync because the planner outputs numeric trigger words (e.g., `\"47\"`) instead of spelled-out words (e.g., `\"forty\"`). WhisperX transcribes speech as words, never digits, so the frame-matching step finds no match and falls back to a scene-third position estimate (poor timing accuracy).\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\CONCERNS.md:47:- Workaround: Word Alignment algorithm (`_align_words_to_timestamps` in `shared/processors/lettering_tsx_generator.py` line 2928) partially mitigates via positional alignment but does not solve the root cause.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\CONCERNS.md:49:**WhisperX Misheard Numbers Causing Trigger Frame Drops:**\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\CONCERNS.md:50:- Symptoms: Lettering entries are dropped when WhisperX misreads numbers (e.g., \"911\" transcribed as \"1091\"). In Viking PT video: 3/110 entries dropped, all with `trigger_word: \"911\"`.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\CONCERNS.md:52:- Trigger: Any scene where the narrator speaks a number that WhisperX transcribes differently.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\CONCERNS.md:53:- Workaround: Word Alignment fallback partially handles this. Full algorithm proposed in `docs/python_tsx_engine/06_NEXT_STEPS.md` (Feature 3) is partially implemented.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\CONCERNS.md:70:- Risk: Accounts 003 (WWII Photography) and 005 (Dark History) generate images via Gemini Imagen of specific historical aircraft, weapons, and people. AI-generated images do not match actual historical assets (e.g., wrong plane model despite narration naming a specific type). Negative viewer comments documented in brainstorming session `docs/sessions/march-26-sessions/realfootage-chatgpt.txt`.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\CONCERNS.md:79:- Recommendations: Fetch a real photograph of the subject property from public domain sources and use as Imagen reference input before image generation runs.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\CONCERNS.md:81:**No Real Footage Integration:**\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\CONCERNS.md:82:- Risk: Pixabay/Pexels integration was attempted (formerly account 009, removed from repo). It failed due to poor tag-based search quality and imprecise local LLM (Qwen/LLaVA) scoring. No current mechanism exists to use real video or photographic footage in any account. Copyright risk also exists - even \"copyright-free\" music from such banks caused takedowns previously.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\CONCERNS.md:90:**Synchronous Image-Per-Scene Generation - No Batch API:**\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\CONCERNS.md:91:- Problem: Each scene image is generated one at a time via Gemini API (on-demand). With 50-130 scenes per video at ~$0.03-$0.07/image, videos cost $1.50-$9.10 in image generation alone. Google offers a batch API for Imagen with ~50% cost reduction, but the pipeline cannot use it because images are generated inline during Bloco 2.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\CONCERNS.md:114:- Why fragile: Bug with `list index out of range` on adjacent commented sequences was fixed in Feb 2026. The auto-fix modifies TSX files in-place using line-number-based operations and regex (not an AST parser). Complex TSX structures or nested sequences may produce incorrect auto-fixes that pass Python validation but fail at Remotion compile time.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\CONCERNS.md:118:**Lettering Duration Clamping Not Always Applied:**\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\CONCERNS.md:119:- Files: `shared/processors/lettering_tsx_generator.py` (`clamp_entry_durations` function, line 2517)\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\CONCERNS.md:120:- Why fragile: TsxValidator detected an unclamped case during Crusaders EN render: `LettBatch_13.tsx:651 [sequence_exceeds_total] Sequence from=39931 + duration=180 = 40111 exceeds total 39978`. The clamping function exists but is not guaranteed to be called before all TSX is written to disk.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\CONCERNS.md:121:- Safe modification: Ensure `clamp_entry_durations` is called in `_run_lettering_python()` immediately before writing TSX output. Add an assertion in `TsxValidator` that raises an error (not just a warning) for this case.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\CONCERNS.md:125:- Why fragile: Pool shrank from ~90 keys to 60 keys between Feb 23 and Mar 2 2026 (multiple `CONSUMER_SUSPENDED` accounts). Suspended keys cause image generation failures for all machines until the registry is manually updated and pushed. No automated health check removes failed keys.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\CONCERNS.md:126:- Safe modification: Add startup key validation in `shared/services/api_key_manager/key_monitor.py`. Mark keys inactive locally without requiring a git push. `key_monitor.py` exists but integration with image generation is unclear.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\CONCERNS.md:131:- Why fragile: Uses single `ELEVENLABS_API_KEY` environment variable with no rotation pool. If key hits rate limits or connection errors during a long batch, all PT/ES TTS generation fails. Account 011 video 2 experienced `ConnectionError` on scenes 46-66 during production.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\CONCERNS.md:136:## Security Considerations\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\CONCERNS.md:139:- Risk: `gemini_api_keys/api_keys_registry.yaml` contains 60 Gemini API keys and is committed to the git repository (shared across all machines). Any git access exposes all image generation keys.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\CONCERNS.md:157:- Scaling path: Diversify to billed Vertex AI (Imagen via a billing account) rather than free-tier personal Google accounts. Add OpenAI DALL-E 3 or Stability AI as secondary image generation fallback.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\CONCERNS.md:172:**Batch API for Image Generation:**\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\CONCERNS.md:176:**Word Alignment for Trigger Resolution (Feature 3):**\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\CONCERNS.md:177:- Problem: Full Word Alignment algorithm proposed in `docs/python_tsx_engine/06_NEXT_STEPS.md` uses `difflib.SequenceMatcher` to align original script words against WhisperX timestamps. Partial implementation exists in `shared/processors/lettering_tsx_generator.py` (`_align_words_to_timestamps`, line 2928) but it does not cover all cases and the clips_metadata.json integration (original_text per scene) is not wired into the main pipeline path.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\CONCERNS.md:207:- Risk: Account-specific step logic (screenplay analysis, TTS pipeline, image generation, checkpoint management) has no unit coverage.\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\CONVENTIONS.md:11:- Module grouping by functionality: `bloco3_orchestrator.py` (orchestration), `bloco3_preprocessor.py` (preprocessing)\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\.planning\\codebase\\CONVENTIONS.md:24:- Dataclass fields follow snake case: `start_frame`, `end_frame`, `duration_frames`, `scene_index`\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\con