{"type":"message","id":"a9800809","parentId":"fff3cf73","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:27:16.897Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Vou criar esse pacote mínimo do Supervisor do S1 agora: contrato central, a skill `s1_preflight_checker` e o ajuste resumido no mirror para apontar para a fonte canónica.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0047bd771936d8e20169caeab0b3048195bbc43f1a6a7df926\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_CzM2KFLCXoTflXR7WfKAzXMH|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caeab59a1c8195bc175c40ec59d1db","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\workspace_mirror\\branches\\01_pre_production\\TOOLS.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\workspace_mirror\\\\branches\\\\01_pre_production\\\\TOOLS.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_i05TBpPFu9bjgW9BAZGxkAFY|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caeab59a2c81959caeb9d6ef4f5681","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$base='C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1'; if (!(Test-Path -LiteralPath $base)) { New-Item -ItemType Directory -Path $base | Out-Null }; $skills=Join-Path $base 'supervisor_skills'; if (!(Test-Path -LiteralPath $skills)) { New-Item -ItemType Directory -Path $skills | Out-Null }; Get-ChildItem -LiteralPath $base | Select-Object Name,FullName,Mode | Format-Table -AutoSize","yieldMs":10000,"workdir":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"$base='C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1'; if (!(Test-Path -LiteralPath $base)) { New-Item -ItemType Directory -Path $base | Out-Null }; $skills=Join-Path $base 'supervisor_skills'; if (!(Test-Path -LiteralPath $skills)) { New-Item -ItemType Directory -Path $skills | Out-Null }; Get-ChildItem -LiteralPath $base | Select-Object Name,FullName,Mode | Format-Table -AutoSize\",\"yieldMs\":10000,\"workdir\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":171,"output":267,"cacheRead":172544,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":172982,"cost":{"input":0.00042750000000000004,"output":0.004005,"cacheRead":0.043136,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0475685}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774906029350,"responseId":"resp_0047bd771936d8e20169caeaafbfb081959e1a2ce556fa5f52"}}
{"type":"message","id":"596d87e3","parentId":"a9800809","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:27:17.824Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_CzM2KFLCXoTflXR7WfKAzXMH|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caeab59a1c8195bc175c40ec59d1db","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# TOOLS.md — SM-S1 (Supervisor do Setor de Pré-Produção)\n\n## Dispatch de Sub-Agentes\n\n### scene_director\n```\nopenclaw agents run scene_director\n```\nInput: job.json + script.json no directório do vídeo.\nOutput: screenplay.json\n\n### tts_polish\n```\nopenclaw agents run tts_polish\n```\nInput: screenplay validado no directório do vídeo.\nOutput: tts_polished.json\n\n### scene_bible_builder\n```\nopenclaw agents run scene_bible_builder\n```\nInput: screenplay + polish validados no directório do vídeo.\nOutput: scene_bible.json\n\n## Python Skills\n\n### screenplay_validator\nCompara narrações concatenadas vs script original.\nOutput: `screenplay_validation.json`\n\n### polish_validator\nCompara texto polido vs texto pre-polish.\nOutput: `polish_validation.json`\n\n## Paths de Input/Output\n\n| Ficheiro | Path |\n|----------|------|\n| Job input | `{video_dir}/input/job.json` |\n| Script input | `{video_dir}/input/script.json` |\n| Screenplay | `{video_dir}/s1_pre_production/screenplay.json` |\n| Screenplay validation | `{video_dir}/s1_pre_production/screenplay_validation.json` |\n| TTS polished | `{video_dir}/s1_pre_production/tts_polished.json` |\n| Polish validation | `{video_dir}/s1_pre_production/polish_validation.json` |\n| Scene bible | `{video_dir}/scene_bible.json` (raiz do video dir) |\n| Checkpoints | `{video_dir}/checkpoints/s1_step{N}_{name}.json` |\n| Agent logs | `{video_dir}/logs/agent_calls/{agent}_{call_number}.json` |\n\n## Reporting ao VO\n\n### Sucesso:\n```\nS1 complete: {N} scenes, screenplay validated ({retries} retries), polish validated ({retries} retries), scene_bible ready\n```\n\n### Escalação:\n```\nS1 BLOCKED: {agent} failed validation 3x. Error: {details}. Escalating to Lucca/Tobias/Claude Code.\n```\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774906037703}}
{"type":"message","id":"92146b69","parentId":"596d87e3","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:27:17.948Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_i05TBpPFu9bjgW9BAZGxkAFY|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caeab59a2c81959caeb9d6ef4f5681","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Name                            FullName                                                                               \r\n----                            --------                                                                               \r\nsupervisor_skills               C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor...\r\n__pycache__                     C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\__pycache__  \r\ncheckpoint_writer.py            C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\checkpoint...\r\npolish_validator.py             C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\polish_val...\r\ns1_start.py                     C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\s1_start.py  \r\nscene_bible_builder.py          C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\scene_bibl...\r\nscene_bible_schema_validator.py C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\scene_bibl...\r\nscene_director_runner.py        C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\scene_dire...\r\nscreenplay_validator.py         C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\screenplay...\r\ntts_polish_runner.py            C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\tts_polish...\r\n__init__.py                     C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\__init__.py"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":448,"aggregated":"Name                            FullName                                                                               \r\n----                            --------                                                                               \r\nsupervisor_skills               C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor...\r\n__pycache__                     C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\__pycache__  \r\ncheckpoint_writer.py            C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\checkpoint...\r\npolish_validator.py             C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\polish_val...\r\ns1_start.py                     C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\s1_start.py  \r\nscene_bible_builder.py          C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\scene_bibl...\r\nscene_bible_schema_validator.py C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\scene_bibl...\r\nscene_director_runner.py        C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\scene_dire...\r\nscreenplay_validator.py         C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\screenplay...\r\ntts_polish_runner.py            C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\tts_polish...\r\n__init__.py                     C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\__init__.py","cwd":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774906037824}}
{"type":"message","id":"a30991be","parentId":"92146b69","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:28:34.070Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_124jfBOD26WvribQHIqNS3tD|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caeb02c60c8195ad35358aa65e3dab","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1_supervisor_contract.md","content":"# S1 Supervisor Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the role, boundaries, and first deterministic skill of the S1 (Pre-Production) Supervisor._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-30_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe S1 Supervisor is the supervisory layer for Pre-Production.\n\nIts job is to take a run that is `ready_for_s1` and coordinate the sector until it produces:\n- `screenplay.json`\n- `screenplay_validation.json`\n- `tts_polished.json`\n- `polish_validation.json`\n- `scene_bible.json`\n- `b1_*` checkpoints\n\nThe supervisor is an **OpenClaw LLM supervisor**, not a purely conversational helper and not a monolithic Python script that absorbs all work itself.\n\nIt should supervise using:\n- deterministic Python skills\n- specialized operators/sub-agents\n- explicit file contracts\n\n---\n\n## Core principle\n\n### Supervisor = brain\n### Skills = hands\n### Operators = specialists\n\nThe S1 Supervisor should:\n- decide the order of operations\n- decide when to call an operator vs a deterministic skill\n- interpret validation results\n- decide retry / fail / continue\n- write or trigger checkpoints\n\nThe S1 Supervisor should **not** directly absorb:\n- semantic scene generation\n- TTS polish generation\n- low-level file/path mechanics\n- deterministic validation logic\n- JSON merge/reindex mechanics\n\nThose belong to:\n- S1 operators (`scene_director`, `tts_polish`)\n- deterministic supervisor skills\n\n---\n\n## Current operator model\n\nThe current intended operator structure for S1 is:\n- `scene_director` -> OpenClaw operator\n- `tts_polish` -> OpenClaw operator\n\nThese operators communicate with the supervisor via explicit file contracts:\n- supervisor prepares input payload/file\n- operator reads input\n- operator writes output file\n- supervisor validates and decides next step\n\n---\n\n## Current deterministic skills owned by the supervisor\n\n### Implemented now\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n\n### Expected next skills\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n- `retry_planner`\n- `checkpoint_writer`\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\n\nThis list may evolve, but the supervisor should remain supervisory rather than mechanically overloaded.\n\n---\n\n## File contract principle\n\nThe supervisor must operate on persisted run artifacts.\n\nMinimum expected inputs before S1 begins:\n- `job.json`\n- `run_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_raw.txt`\n- `inputs/script/script_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_lock.json`\n- `checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json`\n\nMinimum expected outputs after S1 completes:\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay_validation.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/polish_validation.json`\n- `scene_bible.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step1_screenplay.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step2_screenplay_validated.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step3_tts_polished.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step4_polish_validated.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step5_scene_bible.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_complete.json`\n\n---\n\n## First implemented supervisor skill: `s1_preflight_checker`\n\n### Purpose\nValidate that a run is structurally ready to enter S1 before any operator or semantic step is invoked.\n\n### Scope\nChecks:\n- run root exists\n- required input files exist\n- `job.json` is readable and contains `job_id`, `account`, `language`\n- channel config exists at `accounts/{account}/{language}.yaml`\n- `script_raw.txt` is readable and not empty\n- `vo_script_ready` checkpoint exists\n- run state is minimally compatible with entering S1\n\n### Out of scope\n`s1_preflight_checker` does **not**:\n- create sector outputs\n- call operators\n- validate screenplay semantics\n- decide batching\n- modify the run\n\n### Input shape\n```json\n{\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\"\n}\n```\n\n### Output shape\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"job\": {\n    \"job_id\": \"2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n    \"account\": \"004\",\n    \"language\": \"fr\"\n  },\n  \"paths\": {\n    \"job_json\": \".../job.json\",\n    \"run_metadata\": \".../run_metadata.json\",\n    \"script_raw\": \".../inputs/script/script_raw.txt\",\n    \"script_metadata\": \".../inputs/script/script_metadata.json\",\n    \"script_lock\": \".../inputs/script/script_lock.json\",\n    \"vo_script_ready_checkpoint\": \".../checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json\",\n    \"channel_config\": \".../accounts/004/fr.yaml\"\n  },\n  \"script_stats\": {\n    \"char_count\": 0,\n    \"word_count\": 0\n  },\n  \"errors\": [],\n  \"warnings\": []\n}\n```\n\n### Error policy\nThe skill should collect all relevant failures and return them together.\nIt should not stop at the first missing file.\n\n### Warning policy\nExamples of warning-worthy but non-fatal conditions:\n- script very short\n- script very long\n- `b1_pre_production/` already exists but `b1_complete.json` does not\n\n### Fatal examples\n- missing `job.json`\n- missing `script_raw.txt`\n- unreadable or invalid `job.json`\n- missing channel config\n- missing `vo_script_ready.json`\n- empty script\n\n---\n\n## Naming convention\nThe canonical checkpoint and sector naming for Pre-Production is:\n- `b1_pre_production/`\n- `b1_*` checkpoints\n\nThe older `s1_*` naming should not be treated as canonical.\n\n---\n\n## Current status summary\nAt this stage:\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\n- deterministic helper skills are being formalized\n- `s1_preflight_checker` is the first concrete supervisor skill to be implemented and used as the entry gate for the sector\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1_supervisor_contract.md\",\"content\":\"# S1 Supervisor Contract\\n\\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the role, boundaries, and first deterministic skill of the S1 (Pre-Production) Supervisor._\\n\\n_Last updated: 2026-03-30_\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\nThe S1 Supervisor is the supervisory layer for Pre-Production.\\n\\nIts job is to take a run that is `ready_for_s1` and coordinate the sector until it produces:\\n- `screenplay.json`\\n- `screenplay_validation.json`\\n- `tts_polished.json`\\n- `polish_validation.json`\\n- `scene_bible.json`\\n- `b1_*` checkpoints\\n\\nThe supervisor is an **OpenClaw LLM supervisor**, not a purely conversational helper and not a monolithic Python script that absorbs all work itself.\\n\\nIt should supervise using:\\n- deterministic Python skills\\n- specialized operators/sub-agents\\n- explicit file contracts\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Core principle\\n\\n### Supervisor = brain\\n### Skills = hands\\n### Operators = specialists\\n\\nThe S1 Supervisor should:\\n- decide the order of operations\\n- decide when to call an operator vs a deterministic skill\\n- interpret validation results\\n- decide retry / fail / continue\\n- write or trigger checkpoints\\n\\nThe S1 Supervisor should **not** directly absorb:\\n- semantic scene generation\\n- TTS polish generation\\n- low-level file/path mechanics\\n- deterministic validation logic\\n- JSON merge/reindex mechanics\\n\\nThose belong to:\\n- S1 operators (`scene_director`, `tts_polish`)\\n- deterministic supervisor skills\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Current operator model\\n\\nThe current intended operator structure for S1 is:\\n- `scene_director` -> OpenClaw operator\\n- `tts_polish` -> OpenClaw operator\\n\\nThese operators communicate with the supervisor via explicit file contracts:\\n- supervisor prepares input payload/file\\n- operator reads input\\n- operator writes output file\\n- supervisor validates and decides next step\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Current deterministic skills owned by the supervisor\\n\\n### Implemented now\\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\\n\\n### Expected next skills\\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\\n- `script_batch_planner`\\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\\n- `screenplay_merger`\\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\\n- `tts_polish_merger`\\n- `retry_planner`\\n- `checkpoint_writer`\\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\\n\\nThis list may evolve, but the supervisor should remain supervisory rather than mechanically overloaded.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## File contract principle\\n\\nThe supervisor must operate on persisted run artifacts.\\n\\nMinimum expected inputs before S1 begins:\\n- `job.json`\\n- `run_metadata.json`\\n- `inputs/script/script_raw.txt`\\n- `inputs/script/script_metadata.json`\\n- `inputs/script/script_lock.json`\\n- `checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json`\\n\\nMinimum expected outputs after S1 completes:\\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay.json`\\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay_validation.json`\\n- `b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json`\\n- `b1_pre_production/polish_validation.json`\\n- `scene_bible.json`\\n- `checkpoints/b1_step1_screenplay.json`\\n- `checkpoints/b1_step2_screenplay_validated.json`\\n- `checkpoints/b1_step3_tts_polished.json`\\n- `checkpoints/b1_step4_polish_validated.json`\\n- `checkpoints/b1_step5_scene_bible.json`\\n- `checkpoints/b1_complete.json`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## First implemented supervisor skill: `s1_preflight_checker`\\n\\n### Purpose\\nValidate that a run is structurally ready to enter S1 before any operator or semantic step is invoked.\\n\\n### Scope\\nChecks:\\n- run root exists\\n- required input files exist\\n- `job.json` is readable and contains `job_id`, `account`, `language`\\n- channel config exists at `accounts/{account}/{language}.yaml`\\n- `script_raw.txt` is readable and not empty\\n- `vo_script_ready` checkpoint exists\\n- run state is minimally compatible with entering S1\\n\\n### Out of scope\\n`s1_preflight_checker` does **not**:\\n- create sector outputs\\n- call operators\\n- validate screenplay semantics\\n- decide batching\\n- modify the run\\n\\n### Input shape\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"run_root\\\": \\\"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### Output shape\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"ok\\\": true,\\n  \\\"run_root\\\": \\\"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\\\",\\n  \\\"job\\\": {\\n    \\\"job_id\\\": \\\"2026-03-30_004_fr_001\\\",\\n    \\\"account\\\": \\\"004\\\",\\n    \\\"language\\\": \\\"fr\\\"\\n  },\\n  \\\"paths\\\": {\\n    \\\"job_json\\\": \\\".../job.json\\\",\\n    \\\"run_metadata\\\": \\\".../run_metadata.json\\\",\\n    \\\"script_raw\\\": \\\".../inputs/script/script_raw.txt\\\",\\n    \\\"script_metadata\\\": \\\".../inputs/script/script_metadata.json\\\",\\n    \\\"script_lock\\\": \\\".../inputs/script/script_lock.json\\\",\\n    \\\"vo_script_ready_checkpoint\\\": \\\".../checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json\\\",\\n    \\\"channel_config\\\": \\\".../accounts/004/fr.yaml\\\"\\n  },\\n  \\\"script_stats\\\": {\\n    \\\"char_count\\\": 0,\\n    \\\"word_count\\\": 0\\n  },\\n  \\\"errors\\\": [],\\n  \\\"warnings\\\": []\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### Error policy\\nThe skill should collect all relevant failures and return them together.\\nIt should not stop at the first missing file.\\n\\n### Warning policy\\nExamples of warning-worthy but non-fatal conditions:\\n- script very short\\n- script very long\\n- `b1_pre_production/` already exists but `b1_complete.json` does not\\n\\n### Fatal examples\\n- missing `job.json`\\n- missing `script_raw.txt`\\n- unreadable or invalid `job.json`\\n- missing channel config\\n- missing `vo_script_ready.json`\\n- empty script\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Naming convention\\nThe canonical checkpoint and sector naming for Pre-Production is:\\n- `b1_pre_production/`\\n- `b1_*` checkpoints\\n\\nThe older `s1_*` naming should not be treated as canonical.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Current status summary\\nAt this stage:\\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\\n- deterministic helper skills are being formalized\\n- `s1_preflight_checker` is the first concrete supervisor skill to be implemented and used as the entry gate for the sector\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_R9cRQIlsV46AgaBlZOkD56i8|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caeb02c61c8195a6d1594208b61d84","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\s1_preflight_checker.py","content":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\ndef run_preflight(run_root: str | Path) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    run_root = Path(run_root)\n    errors: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n    warnings: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n\n    result: dict[str, Any] = {\n        \"ok\": False,\n        \"run_root\": str(run_root),\n        \"job\": {},\n        \"paths\": {},\n        \"script_stats\": {},\n        \"errors\": errors,\n        \"warnings\": warnings,\n    }\n\n    if not run_root.exists() or not run_root.is_dir():\n        errors.append({\n            \"code\": \"missing_run_root\",\n            \"message\": f\"Run root not found or not a directory: {run_root}\",\n        })\n        return result\n\n    job_json = run_root / \"job.json\"\n    run_metadata = run_root / \"run_metadata.json\"\n    script_raw = run_root / \"inputs\" / \"script\" / \"script_raw.txt\"\n    script_metadata = run_root / \"inputs\" / \"script\" / \"script_metadata.json\"\n    script_lock = run_root / \"inputs\" / \"script\" / \"script_lock.json\"\n    vo_script_ready = run_root / \"checkpoints\" / \"vo_script_ready.json\"\n    b1_root = run_root / \"b1_pre_production\"\n    b1_complete = run_root / \"checkpoints\" / \"b1_complete.json\"\n\n    result[\"paths\"].update(\n        {\n            \"job_json\": str(job_json),\n            \"run_metadata\": str(run_metadata),\n            \"script_raw\": str(script_raw),\n            \"script_metadata\": str(script_metadata),\n            \"script_lock\": str(script_lock),\n            \"vo_script_ready_checkpoint\": str(vo_script_ready),\n        }\n    )\n\n    required_files = [\n        (job_json, \"missing_job_json\", \"job.json not found\"),\n        (run_metadata, \"missing_run_metadata\", \"run_metadata.json not found\"),\n        (script_raw, \"missing_script_raw\", \"inputs/script/script_raw.txt not found\"),\n        (script_metadata, \"missing_script_metadata\", \"inputs/script/script_metadata.json not found\"),\n        (script_lock, \"missing_script_lock\", \"inputs/script/script_lock.json not found\"),\n        (vo_script_ready, \"missing_vo_script_ready_checkpoint\", \"checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json not found\"),\n    ]\n\n    for path_obj, code, message in required_files:\n        if not path_obj.exists():\n            errors.append({\"code\": code, \"message\": message})\n\n    job_data: dict[str, Any] = {}\n    if job_json.exists():\n        try:\n            job_data = json.loads(job_json.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\n        except Exception as exc:  # noqa: BLE001\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"invalid_job_json\",\n                \"message\": f\"Failed to read/parse job.json: {exc}\",\n            })\n\n    job_id = job_data.get(\"job_id\") if isinstance(job_data, dict) else None\n    account = job_data.get(\"account\") if isinstance(job_data, dict) else None\n    language = job_data.get(\"language\") if isinstance(job_data, dict) else None\n\n    if not job_id:\n        errors.append({\"code\": \"missing_job_id\", \"message\": \"job.json missing required field 'job_id'\"})\n    if not account:\n        errors.append({\"code\": \"missing_account\", \"message\": \"job.json missing required field 'account'\"})\n    if not language:\n        errors.append({\"code\": \"missing_language\", \"message\": \"job.json missing required field 'language'\"})\n\n    result[\"job\"] = {\n        \"job_id\": job_id,\n        \"account\": account,\n        \"language\": language,\n    }\n\n    channel_config: Path | None = None\n    if account and language:\n        repo_root = run_root.parent.parent.parent\n        channel_config = repo_root / \"accounts\" / str(account) / f\"{language}.yaml\"\n        result[\"paths\"][\"channel_config\"] = str(channel_config)\n        if not channel_config.exists():\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"missing_channel_config\",\n                \"message\": f\"Channel config not found: {channel_config}\",\n            })\n\n    if script_raw.exists():\n        try:\n            script_text = script_raw.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\").strip()\n            if not script_text:\n                errors.append({\"code\": \"empty_script\", \"message\": \"script_raw.txt is empty\"})\n            else:\n                word_count = len(script_text.split())\n                char_count = len(script_text)\n                result[\"script_stats\"] = {\n                    \"char_count\": char_count,\n                    \"word_count\": word_count,\n                }\n                if word_count < 50:\n                    warnings.append({\n                        \"code\": \"script_very_short\",\n                        \"message\": f\"Script appears unusually short ({word_count} words)\",\n                    })\n                if word_count > 5000:\n                    warnings.append({\n                        \"code\": \"script_very_long\",\n                        \"message\": f\"Script appears unusually long ({word_count} words)\",\n                    })\n        except Exception as exc:  # noqa: BLE001\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"script_unreadable\",\n                \"message\": f\"Failed to read script_raw.txt: {exc}\",\n            })\n\n    if b1_root.exists() and not b1_complete.exists():\n        warnings.append({\n            \"code\": \"b1_outputs_already_present\",\n            \"message\": \"b1_pre_production directory already exists but b1_complete.json does not\",\n        })\n\n    if b1_complete.exists():\n        errors.append({\n            \"code\": \"b1_already_complete\",\n            \"message\": \"b1_complete.json already exists; S1 appears to be already completed for this run\",\n        })\n\n    result[\"ok\"] = len(errors) == 0\n    return result\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\supervisor_skills\\\\s1_preflight_checker.py\",\"content\":\"from __future__ import annotations\\n\\nimport json\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\nfrom typing import Any\\n\\n\\ndef run_preflight(run_root: str | Path) -> dict[str, Any]:\\n    run_root = Path(run_root)\\n    errors: list[dict[str, str]] = []\\n    warnings: list[dict[str, str]] = []\\n\\n    result: dict[str, Any] = {\\n        \\\"ok\\\": False,\\n        \\\"run_root\\\": str(run_root),\\n        \\\"job\\\": {},\\n        \\\"paths\\\": {},\\n        \\\"script_stats\\\": {},\\n        \\\"errors\\\": errors,\\n        \\\"warnings\\\": warnings,\\n    }\\n\\n    if not run_root.exists() or not run_root.is_dir():\\n        errors.append({\\n            \\\"code\\\": \\\"missing_run_root\\\",\\n            \\\"message\\\": f\\\"Run root not found or not a directory: {run_root}\\\",\\n        })\\n        return result\\n\\n    job_json = run_root / \\\"job.json\\\"\\n    run_metadata = run_root / \\\"run_metadata.json\\\"\\n    script_raw = run_root / \\\"inputs\\\" / \\\"script\\\" / \\\"script_raw.txt\\\"\\n    script_metadata = run_root / \\\"inputs\\\" / \\\"script\\\" / \\\"script_metadata.json\\\"\\n    script_lock = run_root / \\\"inputs\\\" / \\\"script\\\" / \\\"script_lock.json\\\"\\n    vo_script_ready = run_root / \\\"checkpoints\\\" / \\\"vo_script_ready.json\\\"\\n    b1_root = run_root / \\\"b1_pre_production\\\"\\n    b1_complete = run_root / \\\"checkpoints\\\" / \\\"b1_complete.json\\\"\\n\\n    result[\\\"paths\\\"].update(\\n        {\\n            \\\"job_json\\\": str(job_json),\\n            \\\"run_metadata\\\": str(run_metadata),\\n            \\\"script_raw\\\": str(script_raw),\\n            \\\"script_metadata\\\": str(script_metadata),\\n            \\\"script_lock\\\": str(script_lock),\\n            \\\"vo_script_ready_checkpoint\\\": str(vo_script_ready),\\n        }\\n    )\\n\\n    required_files = [\\n        (job_json, \\\"missing_job_json\\\", \\\"job.json not found\\\"),\\n        (run_metadata, \\\"missing_run_metadata\\\", \\\"run_metadata.json not found\\\"),\\n        (script_raw, \\\"missing_script_raw\\\", \\\"inputs/script/script_raw.txt not found\\\"),\\n        (script_metadata, \\\"missing_script_metadata\\\", \\\"inputs/script/script_metadata.json not found\\\"),\\n        (script_lock, \\\"missing_script_lock\\\", \\\"inputs/script/script_lock.json not found\\\"),\\n        (vo_script_ready, \\\"missing_vo_script_ready_checkpoint\\\", \\\"checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json not found\\\"),\\n    ]\\n\\n    for path_obj, code, message in required_files:\\n        if not path_obj.exists():\\n            errors.append({\\\"code\\\": code, \\\"message\\\": message})\\n\\n    job_data: dict[str, Any] = {}\\n    if job_json.exists():\\n        try:\\n            job_data = json.loads(job_json.read_text(encoding=\\\"utf-8\\\"))\\n        except Exception as exc:  # noqa: BLE001\\n            errors.append({\\n                \\\"code\\\": \\\"invalid_job_json\\\",\\n                \\\"message\\\": f\\\"Failed to read/parse job.json: {exc}\\\",\\n            })\\n\\n    job_id = job_data.get(\\\"job_id\\\") if isinstance(job_data, dict) else None\\n    account = job_data.get(\\\"account\\\") if isinstance(job_data, dict) else None\\n    language = job_data.get(\\\"language\\\") if isinstance(job_data, dict) else None\\n\\n    if not job_id:\\n        errors.append({\\\"code\\\": \\\"missing_job_id\\\", \\\"message\\\": \\\"job.json missing required field 'job_id'\\\"})\\n    if not account:\\n        errors.append({\\\"code\\\": \\\"missing_account\\\", \\\"message\\\": \\\"job.json missing required field 'account'\\\"})\\n    if not language:\\n        errors.append({\\\"code\\\": \\\"missing_language\\\", \\\"message\\\": \\\"job.json missing required field 'language'\\\"})\\n\\n    result[\\\"job\\\"] = {\\n        \\\"job_id\\\": job_id,\\n        \\\"account\\\": account,\\n        \\\"language\\\": language,\\n    }\\n\\n    channel_config: Path | None = None\\n    if account and language:\\n        repo_root = run_root.parent.parent.parent\\n        channel_config = repo_root / \\\"accounts\\\" / str(account) / f\\\"{language}.yaml\\\"\\n        result[\\\"paths\\\"][\\\"channel_config\\\"] = str(channel_config)\\n        if not channel_config.exists():\\n            errors.append({\\n                \\\"code\\\": \\\"missing_channel_config\\\",\\n                \\\"message\\\": f\\\"Channel config not found: {channel_config}\\\",\\n            })\\n\\n    if script_raw.exists():\\n        try:\\n            script_text = script_raw.read_text(encoding=\\\"utf-8\\\").strip()\\n            if not script_text:\\n                errors.append({\\\"code\\\": \\\"empty_script\\\", \\\"message\\\": \\\"script_raw.txt is empty\\\"})\\n            else:\\n                word_count = len(script_text.split())\\n                char_count = len(script_text)\\n                result[\\\"script_stats\\\"] = {\\n                    \\\"char_count\\\": char_count,\\n                    \\\"word_count\\\": word_count,\\n                }\\n                if word_count < 50:\\n                    warnings.append({\\n                        \\\"code\\\": \\\"script_very_short\\\",\\n                        \\\"message\\\": f\\\"Script appears unusually short ({word_count} words)\\\",\\n                    })\\n                if word_count > 5000:\\n                    warnings.append({\\n                        \\\"code\\\": \\\"script_very_long\\\",\\n                        \\\"message\\\": f\\\"Script appears unusually long ({word_count} words)\\\",\\n                    })\\n        except Exception as exc:  # noqa: BLE001\\n            errors.append({\\n                \\\"code\\\": \\\"script_unreadable\\\",\\n                \\\"message\\\": f\\\"Failed to read script_raw.txt: {exc}\\\",\\n            })\\n\\n    if b1_root.exists() and not b1_complete.exists():\\n        warnings.append({\\n            \\\"code\\\": \\\"b1_outputs_already_present\\\",\\n            \\\"message\\\": \\\"b1_pre_production directory already exists but b1_complete.json does not\\\",\\n        })\\n\\n    if b1_complete.exists():\\n        errors.append({\\n            \\\"code\\\": \\\"b1_already_complete\\\",\\n            \\\"message\\\": \\\"b1_complete.json already exists; S1 appears to be already completed for this run\\\",\\n        })\\n\\n    result[\\\"ok\\\"] = len(errors) == 0\\n    return result\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_j9pHKa4VuopnK7qcl8Fx1TRC|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caeb02c6288195b47eb58001846975","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\workspace_mirror\\branches\\01_pre_production\\TOOLS.md","oldText":"# TOOLS.md — SM-S1 (Supervisor do Setor de Pré-Produção)\n\n## Dispatch de Sub-Agentes\n\n### scene_director\n```\nopenclaw agents run scene_director\n```\nInput: job.json + script.json no directório do vídeo.\nOutput: screenplay.json\n\n### tts_polish\n```\nopenclaw agents run tts_polish\n```\nInput: screenplay validado no directório do vídeo.\nOutput: tts_polished.json\n\n### scene_bible_builder\n```\nopenclaw agents run scene_bible_builder\n```\nInput: screenplay + polish validados no directório do vídeo.\nOutput: scene_bible.json\n\n## Python Skills\n\n### screenplay_validator\nCompara narrações concatenadas vs script original.\nOutput: `screenplay_validation.json`\n\n### polish_validator\nCompara texto polido vs texto pre-polish.\nOutput: `polish_validation.json`\n\n## Paths de Input/Output\n\n| Ficheiro | Path |\n|----------|------|\n| Job input | `{video_dir}/input/job.json` |\n| Script input | `{video_dir}/input/script.json` |\n| Screenplay | `{video_dir}/s1_pre_production/screenplay.json` |\n| Screenplay validation | `{video_dir}/s1_pre_production/screenplay_validation.json` |\n| TTS polished | `{video_dir}/s1_pre_production/tts_polished.json` |\n| Polish validation | `{video_dir}/s1_pre_production/polish_validation.json` |\n| Scene bible | `{video_dir}/scene_bible.json` (raiz do video dir) |\n| Checkpoints | `{video_dir}/checkpoints/s1_step{N}_{name}.json` |\n| Agent logs | `{video_dir}/logs/agent_calls/{agent}_{call_number}.json` |\n\n## Reporting ao VO\n\n### Sucesso:\n```\nS1 complete: {N} scenes, screenplay validated ({retries} retries), polish validated ({retries} retries), scene_bible ready\n```\n\n### Escalação:\n```\nS1 BLOCKED: {agent} failed validation 3x. Error: {details}. Escalating to Lucca/Tobias/Claude Code.\n```\n","newText":"# TOOLS.md — SM-S1 (Supervisor do Setor de Pré-Produção)\n\n## Canonical source\n\nThis workspace mirror is not the canonical source of truth for S1 Supervisor behavior.\nThe canonical supervisor contract now lives at:\n\n- `docs/contracts/s1_supervisor_contract.md`\n\nUse that file for role, boundaries, owned skills, and naming conventions.\n\n## Current supervisor model\n\nSM-S1 is treated as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor that coordinates:\n- deterministic Python skills\n- specialized operators/sub-agents\n- explicit file contracts\n\nThe supervisor should supervise the sector, not absorb all mechanical work itself.\n\n## Current implemented supervisor skill\n\n### `s1_preflight_checker`\nDeterministic Python skill that validates whether a run is structurally ready to enter S1.\n\nChecks include:\n- `job.json`\n- `run_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_raw.txt`\n- `inputs/script/script_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_lock.json`\n- `checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json`\n- channel config existence\n- script non-empty sanity check\n\nImplementation path:\n- `runtime/s1/supervisor_skills/s1_preflight_checker.py`\n\n## Current operators\n\n### `scene_director`\nExpected role: generate `screenplay.json` from script batches prepared by the supervisor stack.\n\n### `tts_polish`\nExpected role: generate TTS-polished scene text batches without overwriting the original screenplay narration.\n\n## Current deterministic sector skills\n\n- `screenplay_validator`\n- `polish_validator`\n- `scene_bible_builder`\n- `scene_bible_schema_validator`\n- `checkpoint_writer`\n\n## Canonical naming\n\nUse:\n- `b1_pre_production/`\n- `b1_*` checkpoints\n\nDo not treat older `s1_*` naming as canonical.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\workspace_mirror\\\\branches\\\\01_pre_production\\\\TOOLS.md\",\"oldText\":\"# TOOLS.md — SM-S1 (Supervisor do Setor de Pré-Produção)\\n\\n## Dispatch de Sub-Agentes\\n\\n### scene_director\\n```\\nopenclaw agents run scene_director\\n```\\nInput: job.json + script.json no directório do vídeo.\\nOutput: screenplay.json\\n\\n### tts_polish\\n```\\nopenclaw agents run tts_polish\\n```\\nInput: screenplay validado no directório do vídeo.\\nOutput: tts_polished.json\\n\\n### scene_bible_builder\\n```\\nopenclaw agents run scene_bible_builder\\n```\\nInput: screenplay + polish validados no directório do vídeo.\\nOutput: scene_bible.json\\n\\n## Python Skills\\n\\n### screenplay_validator\\nCompara narrações concatenadas vs script original.\\nOutput: `screenplay_validation.json`\\n\\n### polish_validator\\nCompara texto polido vs texto pre-polish.\\nOutput: `polish_validation.json`\\n\\n## Paths de Input/Output\\n\\n| Ficheiro | Path |\\n|----------|------|\\n| Job input | `{video_dir}/input/job.json` |\\n| Script input | `{video_dir}/input/script.json` |\\n| Screenplay | `{video_dir}/s1_pre_production/screenplay.json` |\\n| Screenplay validation | `{video_dir}/s1_pre_production/screenplay_validation.json` |\\n| TTS polished | `{video_dir}/s1_pre_production/tts_polished.json` |\\n| Polish validation | `{video_dir}/s1_pre_production/polish_validation.json` |\\n| Scene bible | `{video_dir}/scene_bible.json` (raiz do video dir) |\\n| Checkpoints | `{video_dir}/checkpoints/s1_step{N}_{name}.json` |\\n| Agent logs | `{video_dir}/logs/agent_calls/{agent}_{call_number}.json` |\\n\\n## Reporting ao VO\\n\\n### Sucesso:\\n```\\nS1 complete: {N} scenes, screenplay validated ({retries} retries), polish validated ({retries} retries), scene_bible ready\\n```\\n\\n### Escalação:\\n```\\nS1 BLOCKED: {agent} failed validation 3x. Error: {details}. Escalating to Lucca/Tobias/Claude Code.\\n```\\n\",\"newText\":\"# TOOLS.md — SM-S1 (Supervisor do Setor de Pré-Produção)\\n\\n## Canonical source\\n\\nThis workspace mirror is not the canonical source of truth for S1 Supervisor behavior.\\nThe canonical supervisor contract now lives at:\\n\\n- `docs/contracts/s1_supervisor_contract.md`\\n\\nUse that file for role, boundaries, owned skills, and naming conventions.\\n\\n## Current supervisor model\\n\\nSM-S1 is treated as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor that coordinates:\\n- deterministic Python skills\\n- specialized operators/sub-agents\\n- explicit file contracts\\n\\nThe supervisor should supervise the sector, not absorb all mechanical work itself.\\n\\n## Current implemented supervisor skill\\n\\n### `s1_preflight_checker`\\nDeterministic Python skill that validates whether a run is structurally ready to enter S1.\\n\\nChecks include:\\n- `job.json`\\n- `run_metadata.json`\\n- `inputs/script/script_raw.txt`\\n- `inputs/script/script_metadata.json`\\n- `inputs/script/script_lock.json`\\n- `checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json`\\n- channel config existence\\n- script non-empty sanity check\\n\\nImplementation path:\\n- `runtime/s1/supervisor_skills/s1_preflight_checker.py`\\n\\n## Current operators\\n\\n### `scene_director`\\nExpected role: generate `screenplay.json` from script batches prepared by the supervisor stack.\\n\\n### `tts_polish`\\nExpected role: generate TTS-polished scene text batches without overwriting the original screenplay narration.\\n\\n## Current deterministic sector skills\\n\\n- `screenplay_validator`\\n- `polish_validator`\\n- `scene_bible_builder`\\n- `scene_bible_schema_validator`\\n- `checkpoint_writer`\\n\\n## Canonical naming\\n\\nUse:\\n- `b1_pre_production/`\\n- `b1_*` checkpoints\\n\\nDo not treat older `s1_*` naming as canonical.\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":1005,"output":4048,"cacheRead":172800,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":177853,"cost":{"input":0.0025125000000000004,"output":0.06072,"cacheRead":0.043199999999999995,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.10643249999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774906038710,"responseId":"resp_0047bd771936d8e20169caeab898d08195aabe469e7587f66d"}}
