{"type":"message","id":"7270cfcf","parentId":"b3e0024a","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:34:41.996Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Vou seguir no mesmo padrão com a `s1_paths_resolver`: definir claramente, criar a skill e atualizar o contrato/mirror só no mínimo necessário.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0047bd771936d8e20169caec70271c81959f55991b3265755c\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_oNC1DrMGsAbM4KsvSTorcmmU|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caec72e800819598ad510d0ccb98b9","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1_supervisor_contract.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1_supervisor_contract.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_2AAa4x0iC2f0rpNNK5r6IWkC|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caec72e80c81958081cd6258f937b6","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\s1_preflight_checker.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\supervisor_skills\\\\s1_preflight_checker.py\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":256,"output":144,"cacheRead":177792,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":178192,"cost":{"input":0.00064,"output":0.00216,"cacheRead":0.044448,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.047248}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774906477470,"responseId":"resp_0047bd771936d8e20169caec6f4128819583034ae0520dae9a"}}
{"type":"message","id":"ff51e48b","parentId":"7270cfcf","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:34:42.716Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_oNC1DrMGsAbM4KsvSTorcmmU|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caec72e800819598ad510d0ccb98b9","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# S1 Supervisor Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the role, boundaries, and first deterministic skill of the S1 (Pre-Production) Supervisor._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-30_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe S1 Supervisor is the supervisory layer for Pre-Production.\n\nIts job is to take a run that is `ready_for_s1` and coordinate the sector until it produces:\n- `screenplay.json`\n- `screenplay_validation.json`\n- `tts_polished.json`\n- `polish_validation.json`\n- `scene_bible.json`\n- `b1_*` checkpoints\n\nThe supervisor is an **OpenClaw LLM supervisor**, not a purely conversational helper and not a monolithic Python script that absorbs all work itself.\n\nIt should supervise using:\n- deterministic Python skills\n- specialized operators/sub-agents\n- explicit file contracts\n\n---\n\n## Core principle\n\n### Supervisor = brain\n### Skills = hands\n### Operators = specialists\n\nThe S1 Supervisor should:\n- decide the order of operations\n- decide when to call an operator vs a deterministic skill\n- interpret validation results\n- decide retry / fail / continue\n- write or trigger checkpoints\n\nThe S1 Supervisor should **not** directly absorb:\n- semantic scene generation\n- TTS polish generation\n- low-level file/path mechanics\n- deterministic validation logic\n- JSON merge/reindex mechanics\n\nThose belong to:\n- S1 operators (`scene_director`, `tts_polish`)\n- deterministic supervisor skills\n\n---\n\n## Current operator model\n\nThe current intended operator structure for S1 is:\n- `scene_director` -> OpenClaw operator\n- `tts_polish` -> OpenClaw operator\n\nThese operators communicate with the supervisor via explicit file contracts:\n- supervisor prepares input payload/file\n- operator reads input\n- operator writes output file\n- supervisor validates and decides next step\n\n---\n\n## Current deterministic skills owned by the supervisor\n\n### Implemented now\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n\n### Expected next skills\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n- `retry_planner`\n- `checkpoint_writer`\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\n\nThis list may evolve, but the supervisor should remain supervisory rather than mechanically overloaded.\n\n---\n\n## File contract principle\n\nThe supervisor must operate on persisted run artifacts.\n\nMinimum expected inputs before S1 begins:\n- `job.json`\n- `run_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_raw.txt`\n- `inputs/script/script_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_lock.json`\n- `checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json`\n\nMinimum expected outputs after S1 completes:\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay_validation.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/polish_validation.json`\n- `scene_bible.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step1_screenplay.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step2_screenplay_validated.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step3_tts_polished.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step4_polish_validated.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step5_scene_bible.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_complete.json`\n\n---\n\n## First implemented supervisor skill: `s1_preflight_checker`\n\n### Purpose\nValidate that a run is structurally ready to enter S1 before any operator or semantic step is invoked.\n\n### Scope\nChecks:\n- run root exists\n- required input files exist\n- `job.json` is readable and contains `job_id`, `account`, `language`\n- channel config exists at `accounts/{account}/{language}.yaml`\n- `script_raw.txt` is readable and not empty\n- `vo_script_ready` checkpoint exists\n- run state is minimally compatible with entering S1\n\n### Out of scope\n`s1_preflight_checker` does **not**:\n- create sector outputs\n- call operators\n- validate screenplay semantics\n- decide batching\n- modify the run\n\n### Input shape\n```json\n{\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\"\n}\n```\n\n### Output shape\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"job\": {\n    \"job_id\": \"2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n    \"account\": \"004\",\n    \"language\": \"fr\"\n  },\n  \"paths\": {\n    \"job_json\": \".../job.json\",\n    \"run_metadata\": \".../run_metadata.json\",\n    \"script_raw\": \".../inputs/script/script_raw.txt\",\n    \"script_metadata\": \".../inputs/script/script_metadata.json\",\n    \"script_lock\": \".../inputs/script/script_lock.json\",\n    \"vo_script_ready_checkpoint\": \".../checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json\",\n    \"channel_config\": \".../accounts/004/fr.yaml\"\n  },\n  \"script_stats\": {\n    \"char_count\": 0,\n    \"word_count\": 0\n  },\n  \"errors\": [],\n  \"warnings\": []\n}\n```\n\n### Error policy\nThe skill should collect all relevant failures and return them together.\nIt should not stop at the first missing file.\n\n### Warning policy\nExamples of warning-worthy but non-fatal conditions:\n- script very short\n- script very long\n- `b1_pre_production/` already exists but `b1_complete.json` does not\n\n### Fatal examples\n- missing `job.json`\n- missing `script_raw.txt`\n- unreadable or invalid `job.json`\n- missing channel config\n- missing `vo_script_ready.json`\n- empty script\n\n---\n\n## Naming convention\nThe canonical checkpoint and sector naming for Pre-Production is:\n- `b1_pre_production/`\n- `b1_*` checkpoints\n\nThe older `s1_*` naming should not be treated as canonical.\n\n---\n\n## Current status summary\nAt this stage:\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\n- deterministic helper skills are being formalized\n- `s1_preflight_checker` is the first concrete supervisor skill to be implemented and used as the entry gate for the sector\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774906482588}}
{"type":"message","id":"0f351357","parentId":"ff51e48b","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:34:42.839Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_2AAa4x0iC2f0rpNNK5r6IWkC|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caec72e80c81958081cd6258f937b6","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\ndef run_preflight(run_root: str | Path) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    run_root = Path(run_root)\n    errors: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n    warnings: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n\n    result: dict[str, Any] = {\n        \"ok\": False,\n        \"run_root\": str(run_root),\n        \"job\": {},\n        \"paths\": {},\n        \"script_stats\": {},\n        \"errors\": errors,\n        \"warnings\": warnings,\n    }\n\n    if not run_root.exists() or not run_root.is_dir():\n        errors.append({\n            \"code\": \"missing_run_root\",\n            \"message\": f\"Run root not found or not a directory: {run_root}\",\n        })\n        return result\n\n    job_json = run_root / \"job.json\"\n    run_metadata = run_root / \"run_metadata.json\"\n    script_raw = run_root / \"inputs\" / \"script\" / \"script_raw.txt\"\n    script_metadata = run_root / \"inputs\" / \"script\" / \"script_metadata.json\"\n    script_lock = run_root / \"inputs\" / \"script\" / \"script_lock.json\"\n    vo_script_ready = run_root / \"checkpoints\" / \"vo_script_ready.json\"\n    b1_root = run_root / \"b1_pre_production\"\n    b1_complete = run_root / \"checkpoints\" / \"b1_complete.json\"\n\n    result[\"paths\"].update(\n        {\n            \"job_json\": str(job_json),\n            \"run_metadata\": str(run_metadata),\n            \"script_raw\": str(script_raw),\n            \"script_metadata\": str(script_metadata),\n            \"script_lock\": str(script_lock),\n            \"vo_script_ready_checkpoint\": str(vo_script_ready),\n        }\n    )\n\n    required_files = [\n        (job_json, \"missing_job_json\", \"job.json not found\"),\n        (run_metadata, \"missing_run_metadata\", \"run_metadata.json not found\"),\n        (script_raw, \"missing_script_raw\", \"inputs/script/script_raw.txt not found\"),\n        (script_metadata, \"missing_script_metadata\", \"inputs/script/script_metadata.json not found\"),\n        (script_lock, \"missing_script_lock\", \"inputs/script/script_lock.json not found\"),\n        (vo_script_ready, \"missing_vo_script_ready_checkpoint\", \"checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json not found\"),\n    ]\n\n    for path_obj, code, message in required_files:\n        if not path_obj.exists():\n            errors.append({\"code\": code, \"message\": message})\n\n    job_data: dict[str, Any] = {}\n    if job_json.exists():\n        try:\n            job_data = json.loads(job_json.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\n        except Exception as exc:  # noqa: BLE001\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"invalid_job_json\",\n                \"message\": f\"Failed to read/parse job.json: {exc}\",\n            })\n\n    job_id = job_data.get(\"job_id\") if isinstance(job_data, dict) else None\n    account = job_data.get(\"account\") if isinstance(job_data, dict) else None\n    language = job_data.get(\"language\") if isinstance(job_data, dict) else None\n\n    if not job_id:\n        errors.append({\"code\": \"missing_job_id\", \"message\": \"job.json missing required field 'job_id'\"})\n    if not account:\n        errors.append({\"code\": \"missing_account\", \"message\": \"job.json missing required field 'account'\"})\n    if not language:\n        errors.append({\"code\": \"missing_language\", \"message\": \"job.json missing required field 'language'\"})\n\n    result[\"job\"] = {\n        \"job_id\": job_id,\n        \"account\": account,\n        \"language\": language,\n    }\n\n    channel_config: Path | None = None\n    if account and language:\n        repo_root = run_root.parent.parent.parent\n        channel_config = repo_root / \"accounts\" / str(account) / f\"{language}.yaml\"\n        result[\"paths\"][\"channel_config\"] = str(channel_config)\n        if not channel_config.exists():\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"missing_channel_config\",\n                \"message\": f\"Channel config not found: {channel_config}\",\n            })\n\n    if script_raw.exists():\n        try:\n            script_text = script_raw.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\").strip()\n            if not script_text:\n                errors.append({\"code\": \"empty_script\", \"message\": \"script_raw.txt is empty\"})\n            else:\n                word_count = len(script_text.split())\n                char_count = len(script_text)\n                result[\"script_stats\"] = {\n                    \"char_count\": char_count,\n                    \"word_count\": word_count,\n                }\n                if word_count < 50:\n                    warnings.append({\n                        \"code\": \"script_very_short\",\n                        \"message\": f\"Script appears unusually short ({word_count} words)\",\n                    })\n                if word_count > 5000:\n                    warnings.append({\n                        \"code\": \"script_very_long\",\n                        \"message\": f\"Script appears unusually long ({word_count} words)\",\n                    })\n        except Exception as exc:  # noqa: BLE001\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"script_unreadable\",\n                \"message\": f\"Failed to read script_raw.txt: {exc}\",\n            })\n\n    if b1_root.exists() and not b1_complete.exists():\n        warnings.append({\n            \"code\": \"b1_outputs_already_present\",\n            \"message\": \"b1_pre_production directory already exists but b1_complete.json does not\",\n        })\n\n    if b1_complete.exists():\n        errors.append({\n            \"code\": \"b1_already_complete\",\n            \"message\": \"b1_complete.json already exists; S1 appears to be already completed for this run\",\n        })\n\n    result[\"ok\"] = len(errors) == 0\n    return result\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774906482716}}
{"type":"message","id":"6761782d","parentId":"0f351357","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:35:17.573Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_T61S5VNvB2Xza0lidZDhVhx7|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caec964b54819599b638c569fea2d8","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\s1_paths_resolver.py","content":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\ndef resolve_paths(run_root: str | Path, create_dirs: bool = True) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    run_root = Path(run_root)\n\n    b1_root = run_root / \"b1_pre_production\"\n    inputs_root = b1_root / \"inputs\"\n    intermediate_root = b1_root / \"intermediate\"\n    scene_director_inputs = inputs_root / \"scene_director\"\n    tts_polish_inputs = inputs_root / \"tts_polish\"\n    scene_director_intermediate = intermediate_root / \"scene_director\"\n    tts_polish_intermediate = intermediate_root / \"tts_polish\"\n    checkpoints_root = run_root / \"checkpoints\"\n\n    if create_dirs:\n        for path_obj in [\n            b1_root,\n            inputs_root,\n            intermediate_root,\n            scene_director_inputs,\n            tts_polish_inputs,\n            scene_director_intermediate,\n            tts_polish_intermediate,\n            checkpoints_root,\n        ]:\n            path_obj.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n    paths = {\n        \"run_root\": str(run_root),\n        \"b1_root\": str(b1_root),\n        \"inputs_root\": str(inputs_root),\n        \"intermediate_root\": str(intermediate_root),\n        \"scene_director_inputs_root\": str(scene_director_inputs),\n        \"tts_polish_inputs_root\": str(tts_polish_inputs),\n        \"scene_director_intermediate_root\": str(scene_director_intermediate),\n        \"tts_polish_intermediate_root\": str(tts_polish_intermediate),\n        \"screenplay_path\": str(b1_root / \"screenplay.json\"),\n        \"screenplay_validation_path\": str(b1_root / \"screenplay_validation.json\"),\n        \"tts_polished_path\": str(b1_root / \"tts_polished.json\"),\n        \"polish_validation_path\": str(b1_root / \"polish_validation.json\"),\n        \"scene_bible_path\": str(run_root / \"scene_bible.json\"),\n        \"checkpoints_root\": str(checkpoints_root),\n        \"b1_step1_checkpoint\": str(checkpoints_root / \"b1_step1_screenplay.json\"),\n        \"b1_step2_checkpoint\": str(checkpoints_root / \"b1_step2_screenplay_validated.json\"),\n        \"b1_step3_checkpoint\": str(checkpoints_root / \"b1_step3_tts_polished.json\"),\n        \"b1_step4_checkpoint\": str(checkpoints_root / \"b1_step4_polish_validated.json\"),\n        \"b1_step5_checkpoint\": str(checkpoints_root / \"b1_step5_scene_bible.json\"),\n        \"b1_complete_checkpoint\": str(checkpoints_root / \"b1_complete.json\"),\n    }\n\n    return {\n        \"ok\": True,\n        \"run_root\": str(run_root),\n        \"created_dirs\": create_dirs,\n        \"paths\": paths,\n        \"errors\": [],\n        \"warnings\": [],\n    }\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\supervisor_skills\\\\s1_paths_resolver.py\",\"content\":\"from __future__ import annotations\\n\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\nfrom typing import Any\\n\\n\\ndef resolve_paths(run_root: str | Path, create_dirs: bool = True) -> dict[str, Any]:\\n    run_root = Path(run_root)\\n\\n    b1_root = run_root / \\\"b1_pre_production\\\"\\n    inputs_root = b1_root / \\\"inputs\\\"\\n    intermediate_root = b1_root / \\\"intermediate\\\"\\n    scene_director_inputs = inputs_root / \\\"scene_director\\\"\\n    tts_polish_inputs = inputs_root / \\\"tts_polish\\\"\\n    scene_director_intermediate = intermediate_root / \\\"scene_director\\\"\\n    tts_polish_intermediate = intermediate_root / \\\"tts_polish\\\"\\n    checkpoints_root = run_root / \\\"checkpoints\\\"\\n\\n    if create_dirs:\\n        for path_obj in [\\n            b1_root,\\n            inputs_root,\\n            intermediate_root,\\n            scene_director_inputs,\\n            tts_polish_inputs,\\n            scene_director_intermediate,\\n            tts_polish_intermediate,\\n            checkpoints_root,\\n        ]:\\n            path_obj.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\\n\\n    paths = {\\n        \\\"run_root\\\": str(run_root),\\n        \\\"b1_root\\\": str(b1_root),\\n        \\\"inputs_root\\\": str(inputs_root),\\n        \\\"intermediate_root\\\": str(intermediate_root),\\n        \\\"scene_director_inputs_root\\\": str(scene_director_inputs),\\n        \\\"tts_polish_inputs_root\\\": str(tts_polish_inputs),\\n        \\\"scene_director_intermediate_root\\\": str(scene_director_intermediate),\\n        \\\"tts_polish_intermediate_root\\\": str(tts_polish_intermediate),\\n        \\\"screenplay_path\\\": str(b1_root / \\\"screenplay.json\\\"),\\n        \\\"screenplay_validation_path\\\": str(b1_root / \\\"screenplay_validation.json\\\"),\\n        \\\"tts_polished_path\\\": str(b1_root / \\\"tts_polished.json\\\"),\\n        \\\"polish_validation_path\\\": str(b1_root / \\\"polish_validation.json\\\"),\\n        \\\"scene_bible_path\\\": str(run_root / \\\"scene_bible.json\\\"),\\n        \\\"checkpoints_root\\\": str(checkpoints_root),\\n        \\\"b1_step1_checkpoint\\\": str(checkpoints_root / \\\"b1_step1_screenplay.json\\\"),\\n        \\\"b1_step2_checkpoint\\\": str(checkpoints_root / \\\"b1_step2_screenplay_validated.json\\\"),\\n        \\\"b1_step3_checkpoint\\\": str(checkpoints_root / \\\"b1_step3_tts_polished.json\\\"),\\n        \\\"b1_step4_checkpoint\\\": str(checkpoints_root / \\\"b1_step4_polish_validated.json\\\"),\\n        \\\"b1_step5_checkpoint\\\": str(checkpoints_root / \\\"b1_step5_scene_bible.json\\\"),\\n        \\\"b1_complete_checkpoint\\\": str(checkpoints_root / \\\"b1_complete.json\\\"),\\n    }\\n\\n    return {\\n        \\\"ok\\\": True,\\n        \\\"run_root\\\": str(run_root),\\n        \\\"created_dirs\\\": create_dirs,\\n        \\\"paths\\\": paths,\\n        \\\"errors\\\": [],\\n        \\\"warnings\\\": [],\\n    }\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_VoqvZloy5ljdroihYFLMoI6n|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caec964b988195bbb1a89384d529ad","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1_supervisor_contract.md","oldText":"### Implemented now\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n","newText":"### Implemented now\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1_supervisor_contract.md\",\"oldText\":\"### Implemented now\\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\\n\",\"newText\":\"### Implemented now\\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_gsoBmpCFXeR9uKKl7FAHPQBG|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caec964ba08195b09f6d4c348adf66","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1_supervisor_contract.md","oldText":"## First implemented supervisor skill: `s1_preflight_checker`\n\n### Purpose\nValidate that a run is structurally ready to enter S1 before any operator or semantic step is invoked.\n","newText":"## First implemented supervisor skill: `s1_preflight_checker`\n\n### Purpose\nValidate that a run is structurally ready to enter S1 before any operator or semantic step is invoked.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1_supervisor_contract.md\",\"oldText\":\"## First implemented supervisor skill: `s1_preflight_checker`\\n\\n### Purpose\\nValidate that a run is structurally ready to enter S1 before any operator or semantic step is invoked.\\n\",\"newText\":\"## First implemented supervisor skill: `s1_preflight_checker`\\n\\n### Purpose\\nValidate that a run is structurally ready to enter S1 before any operator or semantic step is invoked.\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_xSeFmE0mgIsM6qa2hiPa4yEA|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caec964ba88195bcfdf1ca53b8288a","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1_supervisor_contract.md","oldText":"## Current status summary\nAt this stage:\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\n- deterministic helper skills are being formalized\n- `s1_preflight_checker` is the first concrete supervisor skill to be implemented and used as the entry gate for the sector\n","newText":"## Second implemented supervisor skill: `s1_paths_resolver`\n\n### Purpose\nResolve and centralize the canonical S1 paths for the run.\n\n### Scope\nResolves and optionally creates the directory structure for:\n- `b1_pre_production/`\n- `b1_pre_production/inputs/`\n- `b1_pre_production/intermediate/`\n- `inputs/scene_director/`\n- `inputs/tts_polish/`\n- `intermediate/scene_director/`\n- `intermediate/tts_polish/`\n- canonical output file paths\n- canonical `b1_*` checkpoint file paths\n\n### Out of scope\n`s1_paths_resolver` does **not**:\n- validate semantic readiness\n- call operators\n- inspect screenplay or polish content\n- perform batching\n\n### Input shape\n```json\n{\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"create_dirs\": true\n}\n```\n\n### Output shape\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"created_dirs\": true,\n  \"paths\": {\n    \"b1_root\": \".../b1_pre_production\",\n    \"inputs_root\": \".../b1_pre_production/inputs\",\n    \"intermediate_root\": \".../b1_pre_production/intermediate\",\n    \"screenplay_path\": \".../b1_pre_production/screenplay.json\",\n    \"tts_polished_path\": \".../b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json\",\n    \"scene_bible_path\": \".../scene_bible.json\",\n    \"b1_complete_checkpoint\": \".../checkpoints/b1_complete.json\"\n  },\n  \"errors\": [],\n  \"warnings\": []\n}\n```\n\n## Current status summary\nAt this stage:\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\n- deterministic helper skills are being formalized\n- `s1_preflight_checker` is implemented as the entry gate for the sector\n- `s1_paths_resolver` is implemented as the canonical path/structure resolver for the sector\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1_supervisor_contract.md\",\"oldText\":\"## Current status summary\\nAt this stage:\\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\\n- deterministic helper skills are being formalized\\n- `s1_preflight_checker` is the first concrete supervisor skill to be implemented and used as the entry gate for the sector\\n\",\"newText\":\"## Second implemented supervisor skill: `s1_paths_resolver`\\n\\n### Purpose\\nResolve and centralize the canonical S1 paths for the run.\\n\\n### Scope\\nResolves and optionally creates the directory structure for:\\n- `b1_pre_production/`\\n- `b1_pre_production/inputs/`\\n- `b1_pre_production/intermediate/`\\n- `inputs/scene_director/`\\n- `inputs/tts_polish/`\\n- `intermediate/scene_director/`\\n- `intermediate/tts_polish/`\\n- canonical output file paths\\n- canonical `b1_*` checkpoint file paths\\n\\n### Out of scope\\n`s1_paths_resolver` does **not**:\\n- validate semantic readiness\\n- call operators\\n- inspect screenplay or polish content\\n- perform batching\\n\\n### Input shape\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"run_root\\\": \\\"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\\\",\\n  \\\"create_dirs\\\": true\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### Output shape\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"ok\\\": true,\\n  \\\"run_root\\\": \\\"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\\\",\\n  \\\"created_dirs\\\": true,\\n  \\\"paths\\\": {\\n    \\\"b1_root\\\": \\\".../b1_pre_production\\\",\\n    \\\"inputs_root\\\": \\\".../b1_pre_production/inputs\\\",\\n    \\\"intermediate_root\\\": \\\".../b1_pre_production/intermediate\\\",\\n    \\\"screenplay_path\\\": \\\".../b1_pre_production/screenplay.json\\\",\\n    \\\"tts_polished_path\\\": \\\".../b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json\\\",\\n    \\\"scene_bible_path\\\": \\\".../scene_bible.json\\\",\\n    \\\"b1_complete_checkpoint\\\": \\\".../checkpoints/b1_complete.json\\\"\\n  },\\n  \\\"errors\\\": [],\\n  \\\"warnings\\\": []\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## Current status summary\\nAt this stage:\\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\\n- deterministic helper skills are being formalized\\n- `s1_preflight_checker` is implemented as the entry gate for the sector\\n- `s1_paths_resolver` is implemented as the canonical path/structure resolver for the sector\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":98248,"output":1612,"cacheRead":79360,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":179220,"cost":{"input":0.24562000000000003,"output":0.02418,"cacheRead":0.01984,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.28964000000000006}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774906483561,"responseId":"resp_0047bd771936d8e20169caec759118819593fd7236de2dfd9a"}}
