{"type":"message","id":"1c088477","parentId":"a35f4ee7","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:37:38.267Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Vou seguir com a próxima skill do supervisor, `script_batch_planner`, no mesmo padrão: definir via implementação concreta e alinhar o contrato mínimo do S1 Supervisor.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0047bd771936d8e20169caed205a10819592039124f44a5600\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_JG1d8IhMGolPi3VMqJ0PNeNV|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caed230a408195a2aec9b4d5353863","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1_supervisor_contract.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1_supervisor_contract.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_CNI78oJzgCfnK6uVd1X3rLv3|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caed230ba88195bfa30b6d3caaeb2b","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\s1_paths_resolver.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\supervisor_skills\\\\s1_paths_resolver.py\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":246,"output":147,"cacheRead":179712,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":180105,"cost":{"input":0.0006150000000000001,"output":0.002205,"cacheRead":0.044927999999999996,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.047748}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774906652515,"responseId":"resp_0047bd771936d8e20169caed1f66648195b9e50664c51d254d"}}
{"type":"message","id":"7af54c5b","parentId":"1c088477","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:37:38.941Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_JG1d8IhMGolPi3VMqJ0PNeNV|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caed230a408195a2aec9b4d5353863","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# S1 Supervisor Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the role, boundaries, and first deterministic skill of the S1 (Pre-Production) Supervisor._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-30_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe S1 Supervisor is the supervisory layer for Pre-Production.\n\nIts job is to take a run that is `ready_for_s1` and coordinate the sector until it produces:\n- `screenplay.json`\n- `screenplay_validation.json`\n- `tts_polished.json`\n- `polish_validation.json`\n- `scene_bible.json`\n- `b1_*` checkpoints\n\nThe supervisor is an **OpenClaw LLM supervisor**, not a purely conversational helper and not a monolithic Python script that absorbs all work itself.\n\nIt should supervise using:\n- deterministic Python skills\n- specialized operators/sub-agents\n- explicit file contracts\n\n---\n\n## Core principle\n\n### Supervisor = brain\n### Skills = hands\n### Operators = specialists\n\nThe S1 Supervisor should:\n- decide the order of operations\n- decide when to call an operator vs a deterministic skill\n- interpret validation results\n- decide retry / fail / continue\n- write or trigger checkpoints\n\nThe S1 Supervisor should **not** directly absorb:\n- semantic scene generation\n- TTS polish generation\n- low-level file/path mechanics\n- deterministic validation logic\n- JSON merge/reindex mechanics\n\nThose belong to:\n- S1 operators (`scene_director`, `tts_polish`)\n- deterministic supervisor skills\n\n---\n\n## Current operator model\n\nThe current intended operator structure for S1 is:\n- `scene_director` -> OpenClaw operator\n- `tts_polish` -> OpenClaw operator\n\nThese operators communicate with the supervisor via explicit file contracts:\n- supervisor prepares input payload/file\n- operator reads input\n- operator writes output file\n- supervisor validates and decides next step\n\n---\n\n## Current deterministic skills owned by the supervisor\n\n### Implemented now\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n\n### Expected next skills\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n- `retry_planner`\n- `checkpoint_writer`\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\n\nThis list may evolve, but the supervisor should remain supervisory rather than mechanically overloaded.\n\n---\n\n## File contract principle\n\nThe supervisor must operate on persisted run artifacts.\n\nMinimum expected inputs before S1 begins:\n- `job.json`\n- `run_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_raw.txt`\n- `inputs/script/script_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_lock.json`\n- `checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json`\n\nMinimum expected outputs after S1 completes:\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay_validation.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/polish_validation.json`\n- `scene_bible.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step1_screenplay.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step2_screenplay_validated.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step3_tts_polished.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step4_polish_validated.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step5_scene_bible.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_complete.json`\n\n---\n\n## First implemented supervisor skill: `s1_preflight_checker`\n\n### Purpose\nValidate that a run is structurally ready to enter S1 before any operator or semantic step is invoked.\n\n### Scope\nChecks:\n- run root exists\n- required input files exist\n- `job.json` is readable and contains `job_id`, `account`, `language`\n- channel config exists at `accounts/{account}/{language}.yaml`\n- `script_raw.txt` is readable and not empty\n- `vo_script_ready` checkpoint exists\n- run state is minimally compatible with entering S1\n\n### Out of scope\n`s1_preflight_checker` does **not**:\n- create sector outputs\n- call operators\n- validate screenplay semantics\n- decide batching\n- modify the run\n\n### Input shape\n```json\n{\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\"\n}\n```\n\n### Output shape\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"job\": {\n    \"job_id\": \"2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n    \"account\": \"004\",\n    \"language\": \"fr\"\n  },\n  \"paths\": {\n    \"job_json\": \".../job.json\",\n    \"run_metadata\": \".../run_metadata.json\",\n    \"script_raw\": \".../inputs/script/script_raw.txt\",\n    \"script_metadata\": \".../inputs/script/script_metadata.json\",\n    \"script_lock\": \".../inputs/script/script_lock.json\",\n    \"vo_script_ready_checkpoint\": \".../checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json\",\n    \"channel_config\": \".../accounts/004/fr.yaml\"\n  },\n  \"script_stats\": {\n    \"char_count\": 0,\n    \"word_count\": 0\n  },\n  \"errors\": [],\n  \"warnings\": []\n}\n```\n\n### Error policy\nThe skill should collect all relevant failures and return them together.\nIt should not stop at the first missing file.\n\n### Warning policy\nExamples of warning-worthy but non-fatal conditions:\n- script very short\n- script very long\n- `b1_pre_production/` already exists but `b1_complete.json` does not\n\n### Fatal examples\n- missing `job.json`\n- missing `script_raw.txt`\n- unreadable or invalid `job.json`\n- missing channel config\n- missing `vo_script_ready.json`\n- empty script\n\n---\n\n## Naming convention\nThe canonical checkpoint and sector naming for Pre-Production is:\n- `b1_pre_production/`\n- `b1_*` checkpoints\n\nThe older `s1_*` naming should not be treated as canonical.\n\n---\n\n## Second implemented supervisor skill: `s1_paths_resolver`\n\n### Purpose\nResolve and centralize the canonical S1 paths for the run.\n\n### Scope\nResolves and optionally creates the directory structure for:\n- `b1_pre_production/`\n- `b1_pre_production/inputs/`\n- `b1_pre_production/intermediate/`\n- `inputs/scene_director/`\n- `inputs/tts_polish/`\n- `intermediate/scene_director/`\n- `intermediate/tts_polish/`\n- canonical output file paths\n- canonical `b1_*` checkpoint file paths\n\n### Out of scope\n`s1_paths_resolver` does **not**:\n- validate semantic readiness\n- call operators\n- inspect screenplay or polish content\n- perform batching\n\n### Input shape\n```json\n{\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"create_dirs\": true\n}\n```\n\n### Output shape\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"created_dirs\": true,\n  \"paths\": {\n    \"b1_root\": \".../b1_pre_production\",\n    \"inputs_root\": \".../b1_pre_production/inputs\",\n    \"intermediate_root\": \".../b1_pre_production/intermediate\",\n    \"screenplay_path\": \".../b1_pre_production/screenplay.json\",\n    \"tts_polished_path\": \".../b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json\",\n    \"scene_bible_path\": \".../scene_bible.json\",\n    \"b1_complete_checkpoint\": \".../checkpoints/b1_complete.json\"\n  },\n  \"errors\": [],\n  \"warnings\": []\n}\n```\n\n## Current status summary\nAt this stage:\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\n- deterministic helper skills are being formalized\n- `s1_preflight_checker` is implemented as the entry gate for the sector\n- `s1_paths_resolver` is implemented as the canonical path/structure resolver for the sector\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774906658822}}
{"type":"message","id":"acdc2153","parentId":"7af54c5b","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:37:39.066Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_CNI78oJzgCfnK6uVd1X3rLv3|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caed230ba88195bfa30b6d3caaeb2b","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\ndef resolve_paths(run_root: str | Path, create_dirs: bool = True) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    run_root = Path(run_root)\n\n    b1_root = run_root / \"b1_pre_production\"\n    inputs_root = b1_root / \"inputs\"\n    intermediate_root = b1_root / \"intermediate\"\n    scene_director_inputs = inputs_root / \"scene_director\"\n    tts_polish_inputs = inputs_root / \"tts_polish\"\n    scene_director_intermediate = intermediate_root / \"scene_director\"\n    tts_polish_intermediate = intermediate_root / \"tts_polish\"\n    checkpoints_root = run_root / \"checkpoints\"\n\n    if create_dirs:\n        for path_obj in [\n            b1_root,\n            inputs_root,\n            intermediate_root,\n            scene_director_inputs,\n            tts_polish_inputs,\n            scene_director_intermediate,\n            tts_polish_intermediate,\n            checkpoints_root,\n        ]:\n            path_obj.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n    paths = {\n        \"run_root\": str(run_root),\n        \"b1_root\": str(b1_root),\n        \"inputs_root\": str(inputs_root),\n        \"intermediate_root\": str(intermediate_root),\n        \"scene_director_inputs_root\": str(scene_director_inputs),\n        \"tts_polish_inputs_root\": str(tts_polish_inputs),\n        \"scene_director_intermediate_root\": str(scene_director_intermediate),\n        \"tts_polish_intermediate_root\": str(tts_polish_intermediate),\n        \"screenplay_path\": str(b1_root / \"screenplay.json\"),\n        \"screenplay_validation_path\": str(b1_root / \"screenplay_validation.json\"),\n        \"tts_polished_path\": str(b1_root / \"tts_polished.json\"),\n        \"polish_validation_path\": str(b1_root / \"polish_validation.json\"),\n        \"scene_bible_path\": str(run_root / \"scene_bible.json\"),\n        \"checkpoints_root\": str(checkpoints_root),\n        \"b1_step1_checkpoint\": str(checkpoints_root / \"b1_step1_screenplay.json\"),\n        \"b1_step2_checkpoint\": str(checkpoints_root / \"b1_step2_screenplay_validated.json\"),\n        \"b1_step3_checkpoint\": str(checkpoints_root / \"b1_step3_tts_polished.json\"),\n        \"b1_step4_checkpoint\": str(checkpoints_root / \"b1_step4_polish_validated.json\"),\n        \"b1_step5_checkpoint\": str(checkpoints_root / \"b1_step5_scene_bible.json\"),\n        \"b1_complete_checkpoint\": str(checkpoints_root / \"b1_complete.json\"),\n    }\n\n    return {\n        \"ok\": True,\n        \"run_root\": str(run_root),\n        \"created_dirs\": create_dirs,\n        \"paths\": paths,\n        \"errors\": [],\n        \"warnings\": [],\n    }\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774906658942}}
{"type":"message","id":"1ae7c222","parentId":"acdc2153","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:38:24.701Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_HsX1NG4DVihP2TR9t9nbFoOp|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caed51605c819580b7bb408217ad73","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\script_batch_planner.py","content":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nimport re\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\ndef plan_script_batches(\n    script_text: str,\n    *,\n    target_words_per_batch: int = 750,\n    min_words_per_batch: int = 450,\n    max_words_per_batch: int = 950,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    errors: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n    warnings: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n\n    if not script_text or not script_text.strip():\n        return {\n            \"ok\": False,\n            \"batch_count\": 0,\n            \"batches\": [],\n            \"errors\": [{\"code\": \"empty_script\", \"message\": \"Cannot plan batches for empty script text\"}],\n            \"warnings\": [],\n        }\n\n    normalized_text = script_text.strip()\n    total_words = len(normalized_text.split())\n\n    paragraphs = [p.strip() for p in re.split(r\"\\n\\s*\\n+\", normalized_text) if p.strip()]\n    if not paragraphs:\n        paragraphs = [normalized_text]\n\n    batches: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n    current_parts: list[str] = []\n    current_word_count = 0\n    running_word_index = 1\n    batch_number = 1\n\n    def flush_batch() -> None:\n        nonlocal current_parts, current_word_count, running_word_index, batch_number\n        if not current_parts:\n            return\n        batch_text = \"\\n\\n\".join(current_parts).strip()\n        batch_words = len(batch_text.split())\n        start_word = running_word_index\n        end_word = running_word_index + batch_words - 1\n        batches.append(\n            {\n                \"batch_id\": f\"sd_{batch_number:03d}\",\n                \"start_word\": start_word,\n                \"end_word\": end_word,\n                \"word_count\": batch_words,\n                \"text\": batch_text,\n            }\n        )\n        running_word_index = end_word + 1\n        batch_number += 1\n        current_parts = []\n        current_word_count = 0\n\n    for paragraph in paragraphs:\n        paragraph_words = len(paragraph.split())\n\n        # Oversized single paragraph: split by sentences as fallback\n        if paragraph_words > max_words_per_batch:\n            if current_parts:\n                flush_batch()\n            sentence_chunks = _split_paragraph_to_sentence_chunks(\n                paragraph,\n                target_words_per_batch=target_words_per_batch,\n                max_words_per_batch=max_words_per_batch,\n            )\n            for chunk in sentence_chunks:\n                current_parts = [chunk]\n                current_word_count = len(chunk.split())\n                flush_batch()\n            continue\n\n        if current_word_count == 0:\n            current_parts.append(paragraph)\n            current_word_count = paragraph_words\n            continue\n\n        if current_word_count + paragraph_words <= target_words_per_batch:\n            current_parts.append(paragraph)\n            current_word_count += paragraph_words\n            continue\n\n        if current_word_count < min_words_per_batch and current_word_count + paragraph_words <= max_words_per_batch:\n            current_parts.append(paragraph)\n            current_word_count += paragraph_words\n            continue\n\n        flush_batch()\n        current_parts.append(paragraph)\n        current_word_count = paragraph_words\n\n    if current_parts:\n        flush_batch()\n\n    if not batches:\n        errors.append({\"code\": \"no_batches_generated\", \"message\": \"Batch planner failed to produce any batches\"})\n\n    if batches and len(batches[-1][\"text\"].split()) < min_words_per_batch and len(batches) > 1:\n        warnings.append(\n            {\n                \"code\": \"small_final_batch\",\n                \"message\": f\"Final batch is smaller than recommended ({batches[-1]['word_count']} words)\",\n            }\n        )\n\n    return {\n        \"ok\": len(errors) == 0,\n        \"total_words\": total_words,\n        \"batch_count\": len(batches),\n        \"target_words_per_batch\": target_words_per_batch,\n        \"min_words_per_batch\": min_words_per_batch,\n        \"max_words_per_batch\": max_words_per_batch,\n        \"batches\": batches,\n        \"errors\": errors,\n        \"warnings\": warnings,\n    }\n\n\ndef plan_script_batches_from_file(\n    script_path: str | Path,\n    *,\n    target_words_per_batch: int = 750,\n    min_words_per_batch: int = 450,\n    max_words_per_batch: int = 950,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    script_path = Path(script_path)\n    if not script_path.exists():\n        return {\n            \"ok\": False,\n            \"batch_count\": 0,\n            \"batches\": [],\n            \"errors\": [{\"code\": \"missing_script_file\", \"message\": f\"Script file not found: {script_path}\"}],\n            \"warnings\": [],\n        }\n\n    text = script_path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\")\n    result = plan_script_batches(\n        text,\n        target_words_per_batch=target_words_per_batch,\n        min_words_per_batch=min_words_per_batch,\n        max_words_per_batch=max_words_per_batch,\n    )\n    result[\"script_path\"] = str(script_path)\n    return result\n\n\ndef _split_paragraph_to_sentence_chunks(\n    paragraph: str,\n    *,\n    target_words_per_batch: int,\n    max_words_per_batch: int,\n) -> list[str]:\n    sentences = [s.strip() for s in re.split(r\"(?<=[.!?])\\s+\", paragraph) if s.strip()]\n    if not sentences:\n        return [paragraph]\n\n    chunks: list[str] = []\n    current: list[str] = []\n    current_words = 0\n\n    for sentence in sentences:\n        sentence_words = len(sentence.split())\n\n        if current_words == 0:\n            current.append(sentence)\n            current_words = sentence_words\n            continue\n\n        if current_words + sentence_words <= target_words_per_batch:\n            current.append(sentence)\n            current_words += sentence_words\n            continue\n\n        if current_words + sentence_words <= max_words_per_batch:\n            current.append(sentence)\n            current_words += sentence_words\n            continue\n\n        chunks.append(\" \".join(current).strip())\n        current = [sentence]\n        current_words = sentence_words\n\n    if current:\n        chunks.append(\" \".join(current).strip())\n\n    return chunks\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\supervisor_skills\\\\script_batch_planner.py\",\"content\":\"from __future__ import annotations\\n\\nimport re\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\nfrom typing import Any\\n\\n\\ndef plan_script_batches(\\n    script_text: str,\\n    *,\\n    target_words_per_batch: int = 750,\\n    min_words_per_batch: int = 450,\\n    max_words_per_batch: int = 950,\\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\\n    errors: list[dict[str, str]] = []\\n    warnings: list[dict[str, str]] = []\\n\\n    if not script_text or not script_text.strip():\\n        return {\\n            \\\"ok\\\": False,\\n            \\\"batch_count\\\": 0,\\n            \\\"batches\\\": [],\\n            \\\"errors\\\": [{\\\"code\\\": \\\"empty_script\\\", \\\"message\\\": \\\"Cannot plan batches for empty script text\\\"}],\\n            \\\"warnings\\\": [],\\n        }\\n\\n    normalized_text = script_text.strip()\\n    total_words = len(normalized_text.split())\\n\\n    paragraphs = [p.strip() for p in re.split(r\\\"\\\\n\\\\s*\\\\n+\\\", normalized_text) if p.strip()]\\n    if not paragraphs:\\n        paragraphs = [normalized_text]\\n\\n    batches: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\\n    current_parts: l