{"type":"message","id":"f07b947f","parentId":"f99c066e","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:40:07.976Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Vou seguir para o próximo componente natural do Supervisor do S1: `scene_director_io_adapter`, para ligar os batches já planeados ao primeiro operator com contrato explícito.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0047bd771936d8e20169caedb609808195bdf3b887b9b8ddfe\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_51G8Qkky34omwAqyYRNjsIoj|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caedb8ba748195b3a8e017891eaed4","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1_supervisor_contract.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1_supervisor_contract.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_yDyqHH2JD7DrNWU3OsIA9NF1|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caedb8bbdc8195975ce8210c53d515","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\script_batch_planner.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\supervisor_skills\\\\script_batch_planner.py\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":139,"output":147,"cacheRead":181632,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":181918,"cost":{"input":0.00034750000000000004,"output":0.002205,"cacheRead":0.045408,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.047960499999999996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774906802749,"responseId":"resp_0047bd771936d8e20169caedb4e99c819584c86aea54f90843"}}
{"type":"message","id":"6f230755","parentId":"f07b947f","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:40:08.688Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_51G8Qkky34omwAqyYRNjsIoj|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caedb8ba748195b3a8e017891eaed4","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# S1 Supervisor Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the role, boundaries, and first deterministic skill of the S1 (Pre-Production) Supervisor._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-30_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe S1 Supervisor is the supervisory layer for Pre-Production.\n\nIts job is to take a run that is `ready_for_s1` and coordinate the sector until it produces:\n- `screenplay.json`\n- `screenplay_validation.json`\n- `tts_polished.json`\n- `polish_validation.json`\n- `scene_bible.json`\n- `b1_*` checkpoints\n\nThe supervisor is an **OpenClaw LLM supervisor**, not a purely conversational helper and not a monolithic Python script that absorbs all work itself.\n\nIt should supervise using:\n- deterministic Python skills\n- specialized operators/sub-agents\n- explicit file contracts\n\n---\n\n## Core principle\n\n### Supervisor = brain\n### Skills = hands\n### Operators = specialists\n\nThe S1 Supervisor should:\n- decide the order of operations\n- decide when to call an operator vs a deterministic skill\n- interpret validation results\n- decide retry / fail / continue\n- write or trigger checkpoints\n\nThe S1 Supervisor should **not** directly absorb:\n- semantic scene generation\n- TTS polish generation\n- low-level file/path mechanics\n- deterministic validation logic\n- JSON merge/reindex mechanics\n\nThose belong to:\n- S1 operators (`scene_director`, `tts_polish`)\n- deterministic supervisor skills\n\n---\n\n## Current operator model\n\nThe current intended operator structure for S1 is:\n- `scene_director` -> OpenClaw operator\n- `tts_polish` -> OpenClaw operator\n\nThese operators communicate with the supervisor via explicit file contracts:\n- supervisor prepares input payload/file\n- operator reads input\n- operator writes output file\n- supervisor validates and decides next step\n\n---\n\n## Current deterministic skills owned by the supervisor\n\n### Implemented now\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n\n### Expected next skills\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n- `retry_planner`\n- `checkpoint_writer`\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\n\nThis list may evolve, but the supervisor should remain supervisory rather than mechanically overloaded.\n\n---\n\n## File contract principle\n\nThe supervisor must operate on persisted run artifacts.\n\nMinimum expected inputs before S1 begins:\n- `job.json`\n- `run_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_raw.txt`\n- `inputs/script/script_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_lock.json`\n- `checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json`\n\nMinimum expected outputs after S1 completes:\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay_validation.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/polish_validation.json`\n- `scene_bible.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step1_screenplay.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step2_screenplay_validated.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step3_tts_polished.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step4_polish_validated.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step5_scene_bible.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_complete.json`\n\n---\n\n## First implemented supervisor skill: `s1_preflight_checker`\n\n### Purpose\nValidate that a run is structurally ready to enter S1 before any operator or semantic step is invoked.\n\n### Scope\nChecks:\n- run root exists\n- required input files exist\n- `job.json` is readable and contains `job_id`, `account`, `language`\n- channel config exists at `accounts/{account}/{language}.yaml`\n- `script_raw.txt` is readable and not empty\n- `vo_script_ready` checkpoint exists\n- run state is minimally compatible with entering S1\n\n### Out of scope\n`s1_preflight_checker` does **not**:\n- create sector outputs\n- call operators\n- validate screenplay semantics\n- decide batching\n- modify the run\n\n### Input shape\n```json\n{\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\"\n}\n```\n\n### Output shape\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"job\": {\n    \"job_id\": \"2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n    \"account\": \"004\",\n    \"language\": \"fr\"\n  },\n  \"paths\": {\n    \"job_json\": \".../job.json\",\n    \"run_metadata\": \".../run_metadata.json\",\n    \"script_raw\": \".../inputs/script/script_raw.txt\",\n    \"script_metadata\": \".../inputs/script/script_metadata.json\",\n    \"script_lock\": \".../inputs/script/script_lock.json\",\n    \"vo_script_ready_checkpoint\": \".../checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json\",\n    \"channel_config\": \".../accounts/004/fr.yaml\"\n  },\n  \"script_stats\": {\n    \"char_count\": 0,\n    \"word_count\": 0\n  },\n  \"errors\": [],\n  \"warnings\": []\n}\n```\n\n### Error policy\nThe skill should collect all relevant failures and return them together.\nIt should not stop at the first missing file.\n\n### Warning policy\nExamples of warning-worthy but non-fatal conditions:\n- script very short\n- script very long\n- `b1_pre_production/` already exists but `b1_complete.json` does not\n\n### Fatal examples\n- missing `job.json`\n- missing `script_raw.txt`\n- unreadable or invalid `job.json`\n- missing channel config\n- missing `vo_script_ready.json`\n- empty script\n\n---\n\n## Naming convention\nThe canonical checkpoint and sector naming for Pre-Production is:\n- `b1_pre_production/`\n- `b1_*` checkpoints\n\nThe older `s1_*` naming should not be treated as canonical.\n\n---\n\n## Second implemented supervisor skill: `s1_paths_resolver`\n\n### Purpose\nResolve and centralize the canonical S1 paths for the run.\n\n### Scope\nResolves and optionally creates the directory structure for:\n- `b1_pre_production/`\n- `b1_pre_production/inputs/`\n- `b1_pre_production/intermediate/`\n- `inputs/scene_director/`\n- `inputs/tts_polish/`\n- `intermediate/scene_director/`\n- `intermediate/tts_polish/`\n- canonical output file paths\n- canonical `b1_*` checkpoint file paths\n\n### Out of scope\n`s1_paths_resolver` does **not**:\n- validate semantic readiness\n- call operators\n- inspect screenplay or polish content\n- perform batching\n\n### Input shape\n```json\n{\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"create_dirs\": true\n}\n```\n\n### Output shape\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"created_dirs\": true,\n  \"paths\": {\n    \"b1_root\": \".../b1_pre_production\",\n    \"inputs_root\": \".../b1_pre_production/inputs\",\n    \"intermediate_root\": \".../b1_pre_production/intermediate\",\n    \"screenplay_path\": \".../b1_pre_production/screenplay.json\",\n    \"tts_polished_path\": \".../b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json\",\n    \"scene_bible_path\": \".../scene_bible.json\",\n    \"b1_complete_checkpoint\": \".../checkpoints/b1_complete.json\"\n  },\n  \"errors\": [],\n  \"warnings\": []\n}\n```\n\n## Third implemented supervisor skill: `script_batch_planner`\n\n### Purpose\nSplit the raw script into manageable work batches for `scene_director` without turning the supervisor into a monolithic batching script.\n\n### Scope\n- receives raw script text or script file path\n- plans batches using target/min/max word budgets\n- prefers paragraph boundaries\n- falls back to sentence-based splitting for oversized paragraphs\n- preserves order and emits a stable `sd_###` batch sequence\n\n### Out of scope\n`script_batch_planner` does **not**:\n- divide the script into final scenes\n- call `scene_director`\n- perform semantic validation\n- merge operator outputs\n\n### Recommended v1 defaults\n- target words per batch: `750`\n- minimum words per batch: `450`\n- maximum words per batch: `950`\n\n### Output shape\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"total_words\": 3520,\n  \"batch_count\": 5,\n  \"target_words_per_batch\": 750,\n  \"min_words_per_batch\": 450,\n  \"max_words_per_batch\": 950,\n  \"batches\": [\n    {\n      \"batch_id\": \"sd_001\",\n      \"start_word\": 1,\n      \"end_word\": 742,\n      \"word_count\": 742,\n      \"text\": \"...\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"errors\": [],\n  \"warnings\": []\n}\n```\n\n## Current status summary\nAt this stage:\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\n- deterministic helper skills are being formalized\n- `s1_preflight_checker` is implemented as the entry gate for the sector\n- `s1_paths_resolver` is implemented as the canonical path/structure resolver for the sector\n- `script_batch_planner` is implemented as the first batching/planning skill for the sector\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774906808562}}
{"type":"message","id":"a15d35d2","parentId":"6f230755","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:40:08.812Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_yDyqHH2JD7DrNWU3OsIA9NF1|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caedb8bbdc8195975ce8210c53d515","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nimport re\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\ndef plan_script_batches(\n    script_text: str,\n    *,\n    target_words_per_batch: int = 750,\n    min_words_per_batch: int = 450,\n    max_words_per_batch: int = 950,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    errors: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n    warnings: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n\n    if not script_text or not script_text.strip():\n        return {\n            \"ok\": False,\n            \"batch_count\": 0,\n            \"batches\": [],\n            \"errors\": [{\"code\": \"empty_script\", \"message\": \"Cannot plan batches for empty script text\"}],\n            \"warnings\": [],\n        }\n\n    normalized_text = script_text.strip()\n    total_words = len(normalized_text.split())\n\n    paragraphs = [p.strip() for p in re.split(r\"\\n\\s*\\n+\", normalized_text) if p.strip()]\n    if not paragraphs:\n        paragraphs = [normalized_text]\n\n    batches: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n    current_parts: list[str] = []\n    current_word_count = 0\n    running_word_index = 1\n    batch_number = 1\n\n    def flush_batch() -> None:\n        nonlocal current_parts, current_word_count, running_word_index, batch_number\n        if not current_parts:\n            return\n        batch_text = \"\\n\\n\".join(current_parts).strip()\n        batch_words = len(batch_text.split())\n        start_word = running_word_index\n        end_word = running_word_index + batch_words - 1\n        batches.append(\n            {\n                \"batch_id\": f\"sd_{batch_number:03d}\",\n                \"start_word\": start_word,\n                \"end_word\": end_word,\n                \"word_count\": batch_words,\n                \"text\": batch_text,\n            }\n        )\n        running_word_index = end_word + 1\n        batch_number += 1\n        current_parts = []\n        current_word_count = 0\n\n    for paragraph in paragraphs:\n        paragraph_words = len(paragraph.split())\n\n        # Oversized single paragraph: split by sentences as fallback\n        if paragraph_words > max_words_per_batch:\n            if current_parts:\n                flush_batch()\n            sentence_chunks = _split_paragraph_to_sentence_chunks(\n                paragraph,\n                target_words_per_batch=target_words_per_batch,\n                max_words_per_batch=max_words_per_batch,\n            )\n            for chunk in sentence_chunks:\n                current_parts = [chunk]\n                current_word_count = len(chunk.split())\n                flush_batch()\n            continue\n\n        if current_word_count == 0:\n            current_parts.append(paragraph)\n            current_word_count = paragraph_words\n            continue\n\n        if current_word_count + paragraph_words <= target_words_per_batch:\n            current_parts.append(paragraph)\n            current_word_count += paragraph_words\n            continue\n\n        if current_word_count < min_words_per_batch and current_word_count + paragraph_words <= max_words_per_batch:\n            current_parts.append(paragraph)\n            current_word_count += paragraph_words\n            continue\n\n        flush_batch()\n        current_parts.append(paragraph)\n        current_word_count = paragraph_words\n\n    if current_parts:\n        flush_batch()\n\n    if not batches:\n        errors.append({\"code\": \"no_batches_generated\", \"message\": \"Batch planner failed to produce any batches\"})\n\n    if batches and len(batches[-1][\"text\"].split()) < min_words_per_batch and len(batches) > 1:\n        warnings.append(\n            {\n                \"code\": \"small_final_batch\",\n                \"message\": f\"Final batch is smaller than recommended ({batches[-1]['word_count']} words)\",\n            }\n        )\n\n    return {\n        \"ok\": len(errors) == 0,\n        \"total_words\": total_words,\n        \"batch_count\": len(batches),\n        \"target_words_per_batch\": target_words_per_batch,\n        \"min_words_per_batch\": min_words_per_batch,\n        \"max_words_per_batch\": max_words_per_batch,\n        \"batches\": batches,\n        \"errors\": errors,\n        \"warnings\": warnings,\n    }\n\n\ndef plan_script_batches_from_file(\n    script_path: str | Path,\n    *,\n    target_words_per_batch: int = 750,\n    min_words_per_batch: int = 450,\n    max_words_per_batch: int = 950,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    script_path = Path(script_path)\n    if not script_path.exists():\n        return {\n            \"ok\": False,\n            \"batch_count\": 0,\n            \"batches\": [],\n            \"errors\": [{\"code\": \"missing_script_file\", \"message\": f\"Script file not found: {script_path}\"}],\n            \"warnings\": [],\n        }\n\n    text = script_path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\")\n    result = plan_script_batches(\n        text,\n        target_words_per_batch=target_words_per_batch,\n        min_words_per_batch=min_words_per_batch,\n        max_words_per_batch=max_words_per_batch,\n    )\n    result[\"script_path\"] = str(script_path)\n    return result\n\n\ndef _split_paragraph_to_sentence_chunks(\n    paragraph: str,\n    *,\n    target_words_per_batch: int,\n    max_words_per_batch: int,\n) -> list[str]:\n    sentences = [s.strip() for s in re.split(r\"(?<=[.!?])\\s+\", paragraph) if s.strip()]\n    if not sentences:\n        return [paragraph]\n\n    chunks: list[str] = []\n    current: list[str] = []\n    current_words = 0\n\n    for sentence in sentences:\n        sentence_words = len(sentence.split())\n\n        if current_words == 0:\n            current.append(sentence)\n            current_words = sentence_words\n            continue\n\n        if current_words + sentence_words <= target_words_per_batch:\n            current.append(sentence)\n            current_words += sentence_words\n            continue\n\n        if current_words + sentence_words <= max_words_per_batch:\n            current.append(sentence)\n            current_words += sentence_words\n            continue\n\n        chunks.append(\" \".join(current).strip())\n        current = [sentence]\n        current_words = sentence_words\n\n    if current:\n        chunks.append(\" \".join(current).strip())\n\n    return chunks\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774906808688}}
{"type":"message","id":"32840ab8","parentId":"a15d35d2","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:40:39.553Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_GrnVOUJt5PeheaKKR9Or370z|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caedd7ffa88195a177ba583a940cb1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\scene_director_io_adapter.py","content":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\ndef build_scene_director_payload(\n    *,\n    run_root: str | Path,\n    job: dict[str, Any],\n    batch: dict[str, Any],\n    channel_config: dict[str, Any],\n    output_path: str | Path,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    run_root = Path(run_root)\n    output_path = Path(output_path)\n\n    account = job.get(\"account\")\n    language = job.get(\"language\")\n    job_id = job.get(\"job_id\")\n\n    payload = {\n        \"job_id\": job_id,\n        \"account\": account,\n        \"language\": language,\n        \"run_root\": str(run_root),\n        \"batch\": {\n            \"batch_id\": batch.get(\"batch_id\"),\n            \"start_word\": batch.get(\"start_word\"),\n            \"end_word\": batch.get(\"end_word\"),\n            \"word_count\": batch.get(\"word_count\"),\n            \"text\": batch.get(\"text\"),\n        },\n        \"scene_words_range\": channel_config.get(\"scene_words_range\"),\n        \"style_context\": {\n            \"channel_name\": job.get(\"channel_name\"),\n            \"reason\": job.get(\"reason\"),\n        },\n        \"instructions\": {\n            \"task\": \"Divide this script batch into ordered scenes for screenplay generation.\",\n            \"requirements\": [\n                \"Preserve narrative meaning and order.\",\n                \"Return scene objects only for this batch.\",\n                \"Each scene must include scene_id, narration_original, visual_direction, mood, duration_estimate.\",\n                \"Do not rewrite the story beyond what is needed for clean scene segmentation.\",\n                \"Do not polish for TTS in this step.\",\n            ],\n        },\n        \"output_path\": str(output_path),\n    }\n\n    return payload\n\n\ndef write_scene_director_payload(\n    *,\n    run_root: str | Path,\n    job: dict[str, Any],\n    batch: dict[str, Any],\n    channel_config: dict[str, Any],\n    input_path: str | Path,\n    output_path: str | Path,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    input_path = Path(input_path)\n    output_path = Path(output_path)\n    input_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    output_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n    payload = build_scene_director_payload(\n        run_root=run_root,\n        job=job,\n        batch=batch,\n        channel_config=channel_config,\n        output_path=output_path,\n    )\n\n    input_path.write_text(json.dumps(payload, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n    return {\n        \"ok\": True,\n        \"input_path\": str(input_path),\n        \"output_path\": str(output_path),\n        \"batch_id\": batch.get(\"batch_id\"),\n        \"payload\": payload,\n        \"errors\": [],\n        \"warnings\": [],\n    }\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\supervisor_skills\\\\scene_director_io_adapter.py\",\"content\":\"from __future__ import annotations\\n\\nimport json\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\nfrom typing import Any\\n\\n\\ndef build_scene_director_payload(\\n    *,\\n    run_root: str | Path,\\n    job: dict[str, Any],\\n    batch: dict[str, Any],\\n    channel_config: dict[str, Any],\\n    output_path: str | Path,\\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\\n    run_root = Path(run_root)\\n    output_path = Path(output_path)\\n\\n    account = job.get(\\\"account\\\")\\n    language = job.get(\\\"language\\\")\\n    job_id = job.get(\\\"job_id\\\")\\n\\n    payload = {\\n        \\\"job_id\\\": job_id,\\n        \\\"account\\\": account,\\n        \\\"language\\\": language,\\n        \\\"run_root\\\": str(run_root),\\n        \\\"batch\\\": {\\n            \\\"batch_id\\\": batch.get(\\\"batch_id\\\"),\\n            \\\"start_word\\\": batch.get(\\\"start_word\\\"),\\n            \\\"end_word\\\": batch.get(\\\"end_word\\\"),\\n            \\\"word_count\\\": batch.get(\\\"word_count\\\"),\\n            \\\"text\\\": batch.get(\\\"text\\\"),\\n        },\\n        \\\"scene_words_range\\\": channel_config.get(\\\"scene_words_range\\\"),\\n        \\\"style_context\\\": {\\n            \\\"channel_name\\\": job.get(\\\"channel_name\\\"),\\n            \\\"reason\\\": job.get(\\\"reason\\\"),\\n        },\\n        \\\"instructions\\\": {\\n            \\\"task\\\": \\\"Divide this script batch into ordered scenes for screenplay generation.\\\",\\n            \\\"requirements\\\": [\\n                \\\"Preserve narrative meaning and order.\\\",\\n                \\\"Return scene objects only for this batch.\\\",\\n                \\\"Each scene must include scene_id, narration_original, visual_direction, mood, duration_estimate.\\\",\\n                \\\"Do not rewrite the story beyond what is needed for clean scene segmentation.\\\",\\n                \\\"Do not polish for TTS in this step.\\\",\\n            ],\\n        },\\n        \\\"output_path\\\": str(output_path),\\n    }\\n\\n    return payload\\n\\n\\ndef write_scene_director_payload(\\n    *,\\n    run_root: str | Path,\\n    job: dict[str, Any],\\n    batch: dict[str, Any],\\n    channel_config: dict[str, Any],\\n    input_path: str | Path,\\n    output_path: str | Path,\\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\\n    input_path = Path(input_path)\\n    output_path = Path(output_path)\\n    input_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\\n    output_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\\n\\n    payload = build_scene_director_payload(\\n        run_root=run_root,\\n        job=job,\\n        batch=batch,\\n        channel_config=channel_config,\\n        output_path=output_path,\\n    )\\n\\n    input_path.write_text(json.dumps(payload, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False), encoding=\\\"utf-8\\\")\\n\\n    return {\\n        \\\"ok\\\": True,\\n        \\\"input_path\\\": str(input_path),\\n        \\\"output_path\\\": str(output_path),\\n        \\\"batch_id\\\": batch.get(\\\"batch_id\\\"),\\n        \\\"payload\\\": payload,\\n        \\\"errors\\\": [],\\n        \\\"warnings\\\": [],\\n    }\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_5TYOCXfmhpREb3At6OtXf5CZ|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caedd7ffb88195b107aa34a24cca94","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1_supervisor_contract.md","oldText":"### Implemented now\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n","newText":"### Implemented now\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1_supervisor_contract.md\",\"oldText\":\"### Implemented now\\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\\n- `script_batch_planner`\\n\",\"newText\":\"### Implemented now\\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\\n- `script_batch_planner`\\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ilPmkRXhRLnvUyK0lzfbdMG1|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caedd7ffc08195ac222e65662102f3","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1_supervisor_contract.md","oldText":"### Expected next skills\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n","newText":"### Expected next skills\n- `screenplay_merger`\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1_supervisor_contract.md\",\"oldText\":\"### Expected next skills\\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\\n- `screenplay_merger`\\n\",\"newText\":\"### Expected next skills\\n- `screenplay_merger`\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_skVuArWD9JcFllQvfCyQcTL6|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caedd7ffd48195805cd1c443dc81d1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1_supervisor_contract.md","oldText":"## Current status summary\nAt this stage:\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\n- deterministic helper skills are being formalized\n- `s1_preflight_checker` is implemented as the entry gate for the sector\n- `s1_paths_resolver` is implemented as the canonical path/structure resolver for the sector\n- `script_batch_planner` is implemented as the first batching/planning skill for the sector\n","newText":"## Fourth implemented supervisor skill: `scene_director_io_adapter`\n\n### Purpose\nPrepare the explicit input/output contract between the S1 Supervisor and the `scene_director` operator for each planned script batch.\n\n### Scope\n- receives run/job context\n- receives one script batch from `script_batch_planner`\n- injects `scene_words_range` from channel config\n- writes a deterministic payload file for the operator\n- declares the expected output path for the batch result\n\n### Out of scope\n`scene_director_io_adapter` does **not**:\n- run the operator\n- validate semantic quality\n- merge batch outputs\n- choose retry policy\n\n### Output contract principle\nEach batch payload should explicitly tell `scene_director`:\n- who the run/job is\n- what the batch text is\n- what scene structure is expected\n- where to write the result\n\n## Current status summary\nAt this stage:\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\n- deterministic helper skills are being formalized\n- `s1_preflight_checker` is implemented as the entry gate for the sector\n- `s1_paths_resolver` is implemented as the canonical path/structure resolver for the sector\n- `script_batch_planner` is implemented as the first batching/planning skill for the sector\n- `scene_director_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `scene_director` operator\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1_supervisor_contract.md\",\"oldText\":\"## Current status summary\\nAt this stage:\\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\\n- deterministic helper skills are being formalized\\n- `s1_preflight_checker` is implemented as the entry gate for the sector\\n- `s1_paths_resolver` is implemented as the canonical path/structure resolver for the sector\\n- `script_batch_planner` is implemented as the first batching/planning skill for the sector\\n\",\"newText\":\"## Fourth implemented supervisor skill: `scene_director_io_adapter`\\n\\n### Purpose\\nPrepare the explicit input/output contract between the S1 Supervisor and the `scene_director` operator for each planned script batch.\\n\\n### Scope\\n- receives run/job context\\n- receives one script batch from `script_batch_planner`\\n- injects `scene_words_range` from channel config\\n- writes a deterministic payload file for the operator\\n- declares the expected output path for the batch result\\n\\n### Out of scope\\n`scene_director_io_adapter` does **not**:\\n- run the operator\\n- validate semantic quality\\n- merge batch outputs\\n- choose retry policy\\n\\n### Output contract principle\\nEach batch payload should explicitly tell `scene_director`:\\n- who the run/job is\\n- what the batch text is\\n- what scene structure is expected\\n- where to write the result\\n\\n## Current status summary\\nAt this stage:\\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\\n- deterministic helper skills are being formalized\\n- `s1_preflight_checker` is implemented as the entry gate for the sector\\n- `s1_paths_resolver` is implemented as the canonical path/structure resolver for the sector\\n- `script_batch_planner` is implemented as the first batching/planning skill for the sector\\n- `scene_director_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `scene_director` operator\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":102654,"output":1452,"cacheRead":79360,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":183466,"cost":{"input":0.256635,"output":0.02178,"cacheRead":0.01984,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.29825500000000005}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774906809385,"responseId":"resp_0047bd771936d8e20169caedbb13d48195b912c0de0bfb5cf4"}}
