{"type":"message","id":"fa6f8a0d","parentId":"22834efa","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:44:42.392Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Vou continuar agora com o próximo bloco do Supervisor do S1: `tts_polish_batch_planner`, para preparar o fluxo batchado do segundo operator no mesmo padrão do `scene_director`.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0047bd771936d8e20169caeec874108195b0d077b17f78923c\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3phkA27Jicav7OKTdIW6mutU|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caeecb3c74819592370d504c3dbc2c","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1_supervisor_contract.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1_supervisor_contract.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_w5EPl8kDGL7Qw07Ta9ngqM6q|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caeecb3c8881959e642cb50955f7a5","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\screenplay_merger.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\supervisor_skills\\\\screenplay_merger.py\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":200,"output":151,"cacheRead":168704,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":169055,"cost":{"input":0.0005,"output":0.002265,"cacheRead":0.042176,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.044940999999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774907074996,"responseId":"resp_0047bd771936d8e20169caeec4865c81959a649ff88c69922d"}}
{"type":"message","id":"d60246e4","parentId":"fa6f8a0d","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:44:43.069Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_3phkA27Jicav7OKTdIW6mutU|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caeecb3c74819592370d504c3dbc2c","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# S1 Supervisor Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the role, boundaries, and first deterministic skill of the S1 (Pre-Production) Supervisor._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-30_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe S1 Supervisor is the supervisory layer for Pre-Production.\n\nIts job is to take a run that is `ready_for_s1` and coordinate the sector until it produces:\n- `screenplay.json`\n- `screenplay_validation.json`\n- `tts_polished.json`\n- `polish_validation.json`\n- `scene_bible.json`\n- `b1_*` checkpoints\n\nThe supervisor is an **OpenClaw LLM supervisor**, not a purely conversational helper and not a monolithic Python script that absorbs all work itself.\n\nIt should supervise using:\n- deterministic Python skills\n- specialized operators/sub-agents\n- explicit file contracts\n\n---\n\n## Core principle\n\n### Supervisor = brain\n### Skills = hands\n### Operators = specialists\n\nThe S1 Supervisor should:\n- decide the order of operations\n- decide when to call an operator vs a deterministic skill\n- interpret validation results\n- decide retry / fail / continue\n- write or trigger checkpoints\n\nThe S1 Supervisor should **not** directly absorb:\n- semantic scene generation\n- TTS polish generation\n- low-level file/path mechanics\n- deterministic validation logic\n- JSON merge/reindex mechanics\n\nThose belong to:\n- S1 operators (`scene_director`, `tts_polish`)\n- deterministic supervisor skills\n\n---\n\n## Current operator model\n\nThe current intended operator structure for S1 is:\n- `scene_director` -> OpenClaw operator\n- `tts_polish` -> OpenClaw operator\n\nThese operators communicate with the supervisor via explicit file contracts:\n- supervisor prepares input payload/file\n- operator reads input\n- operator writes output file\n- supervisor validates and decides next step\n\n---\n\n## Current deterministic skills owned by the supervisor\n\n### Implemented now\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n\n### Expected next skills\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n- `retry_planner`\n- `checkpoint_writer`\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\n\nThis list may evolve, but the supervisor should remain supervisory rather than mechanically overloaded.\n\n---\n\n## File contract principle\n\nThe supervisor must operate on persisted run artifacts.\n\nMinimum expected inputs before S1 begins:\n- `job.json`\n- `run_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_raw.txt`\n- `inputs/script/script_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_lock.json`\n- `checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json`\n\nMinimum expected outputs after S1 completes:\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay_validation.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/polish_validation.json`\n- `scene_bible.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step1_screenplay.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step2_screenplay_validated.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step3_tts_polished.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step4_polish_validated.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step5_scene_bible.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_complete.json`\n\n---\n\n## First implemented supervisor skill: `s1_preflight_checker`\n\n### Purpose\nValidate that a run is structurally ready to enter S1 before any operator or semantic step is invoked.\n\n### Scope\nChecks:\n- run root exists\n- required input files exist\n- `job.json` is readable and contains `job_id`, `account`, `language`\n- channel config exists at `accounts/{account}/{language}.yaml`\n- `script_raw.txt` is readable and not empty\n- `vo_script_ready` checkpoint exists\n- run state is minimally compatible with entering S1\n\n### Out of scope\n`s1_preflight_checker` does **not**:\n- create sector outputs\n- call operators\n- validate screenplay semantics\n- decide batching\n- modify the run\n\n### Input shape\n```json\n{\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\"\n}\n```\n\n### Output shape\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"job\": {\n    \"job_id\": \"2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n    \"account\": \"004\",\n    \"language\": \"fr\"\n  },\n  \"paths\": {\n    \"job_json\": \".../job.json\",\n    \"run_metadata\": \".../run_metadata.json\",\n    \"script_raw\": \".../inputs/script/script_raw.txt\",\n    \"script_metadata\": \".../inputs/script/script_metadata.json\",\n    \"script_lock\": \".../inputs/script/script_lock.json\",\n    \"vo_script_ready_checkpoint\": \".../checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json\",\n    \"channel_config\": \".../accounts/004/fr.yaml\"\n  },\n  \"script_stats\": {\n    \"char_count\": 0,\n    \"word_count\": 0\n  },\n  \"errors\": [],\n  \"warnings\": []\n}\n```\n\n### Error policy\nThe skill should collect all relevant failures and return them together.\nIt should not stop at the first missing file.\n\n### Warning policy\nExamples of warning-worthy but non-fatal conditions:\n- script very short\n- script very long\n- `b1_pre_production/` already exists but `b1_complete.json` does not\n\n### Fatal examples\n- missing `job.json`\n- missing `script_raw.txt`\n- unreadable or invalid `job.json`\n- missing channel config\n- missing `vo_script_ready.json`\n- empty script\n\n---\n\n## Naming convention\nThe canonical checkpoint and sector naming for Pre-Production is:\n- `b1_pre_production/`\n- `b1_*` checkpoints\n\nThe older `s1_*` naming should not be treated as canonical.\n\n---\n\n## Second implemented supervisor skill: `s1_paths_resolver`\n\n### Purpose\nResolve and centralize the canonical S1 paths for the run.\n\n### Scope\nResolves and optionally creates the directory structure for:\n- `b1_pre_production/`\n- `b1_pre_production/inputs/`\n- `b1_pre_production/intermediate/`\n- `inputs/scene_director/`\n- `inputs/tts_polish/`\n- `intermediate/scene_director/`\n- `intermediate/tts_polish/`\n- canonical output file paths\n- canonical `b1_*` checkpoint file paths\n\n### Out of scope\n`s1_paths_resolver` does **not**:\n- validate semantic readiness\n- call operators\n- inspect screenplay or polish content\n- perform batching\n\n### Input shape\n```json\n{\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"create_dirs\": true\n}\n```\n\n### Output shape\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"created_dirs\": true,\n  \"paths\": {\n    \"b1_root\": \".../b1_pre_production\",\n    \"inputs_root\": \".../b1_pre_production/inputs\",\n    \"intermediate_root\": \".../b1_pre_production/intermediate\",\n    \"screenplay_path\": \".../b1_pre_production/screenplay.json\",\n    \"tts_polished_path\": \".../b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json\",\n    \"scene_bible_path\": \".../scene_bible.json\",\n    \"b1_complete_checkpoint\": \".../checkpoints/b1_complete.json\"\n  },\n  \"errors\": [],\n  \"warnings\": []\n}\n```\n\n## Third implemented supervisor skill: `script_batch_planner`\n\n### Purpose\nSplit the raw script into manageable work batches for `scene_director` without turning the supervisor into a monolithic batching script.\n\n### Scope\n- receives raw script text or script file path\n- plans batches using target/min/max word budgets\n- prefers paragraph boundaries\n- falls back to sentence-based splitting for oversized paragraphs\n- preserves order and emits a stable `sd_###` batch sequence\n\n### Out of scope\n`script_batch_planner` does **not**:\n- divide the script into final scenes\n- call `scene_director`\n- perform semantic validation\n- merge operator outputs\n\n### Recommended v1 defaults\n- target words per batch: `750`\n- minimum words per batch: `450`\n- maximum words per batch: `950`\n\n### Output shape\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"total_words\": 3520,\n  \"batch_count\": 5,\n  \"target_words_per_batch\": 750,\n  \"min_words_per_batch\": 450,\n  \"max_words_per_batch\": 950,\n  \"batches\": [\n    {\n      \"batch_id\": \"sd_001\",\n      \"start_word\": 1,\n      \"end_word\": 742,\n      \"word_count\": 742,\n      \"text\": \"...\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"errors\": [],\n  \"warnings\": []\n}\n```\n\n## Fourth implemented supervisor skill: `scene_director_io_adapter`\n\n### Purpose\nPrepare the explicit input/output contract between the S1 Supervisor and the `scene_director` operator for each planned script batch.\n\n### Scope\n- receives run/job context\n- receives one script batch from `script_batch_planner`\n- injects `scene_words_range` from channel config\n- writes a deterministic payload file for the operator\n- declares the expected output path for the batch result\n\n### Out of scope\n`scene_director_io_adapter` does **not**:\n- run the operator\n- validate semantic quality\n- merge batch outputs\n- choose retry policy\n\n### Output contract principle\nEach batch payload should explicitly tell `scene_director`:\n- who the run/job is\n- what the batch text is\n- what scene structure is expected\n- where to write the result\n\n## Fifth implemented supervisor skill: `screenplay_merger`\n\n### Purpose\nMerge the batch outputs of `scene_director` into one canonical `screenplay.json` without forcing the supervisor itself to concatenate, validate, and reindex scene objects manually.\n\n### Scope\n- loads ordered batch output files\n- validates minimum required scene fields\n- concatenates scenes in batch order\n- reassigns canonical `scene_###` IDs globally\n- writes `screenplay.json`\n\n### Out of scope\n`screenplay_merger` does **not**:\n- perform semantic validation\n- decide retry policy\n- invoke operators\n- polish TTS text\n\n### Output contract principle\nThe merged screenplay should preserve order while normalizing scene IDs into one canonical sequence for the rest of S1.\n\n## Current status summary\nAt this stage:\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\n- deterministic helper skills are being formalized\n- `s1_preflight_checker` is implemented as the entry gate for the sector\n- `s1_paths_resolver` is implemented as the canonical path/structure resolver for the sector\n- `script_batch_planner` is implemented as the first batching/planning skill for the sector\n- `scene_director_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `scene_director` operator\n- `screenplay_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch screenplay outputs\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774907082947}}
{"type":"message","id":"a71d47ab","parentId":"d60246e4","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:44:43.205Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_w5EPl8kDGL7Qw07Ta9ngqM6q|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caeecb3c8881959e642cb50955f7a5","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\nREQUIRED_SCENE_FIELDS = {\n    \"scene_id\",\n    \"narration_original\",\n    \"visual_direction\",\n    \"mood\",\n    \"duration_estimate\",\n}\n\n\ndef merge_screenplay_batches(\n    batch_files: list[str | Path],\n    *,\n    output_path: str | Path | None = None,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    errors: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n    warnings: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n    merged_scenes: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n    loaded_batches: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n\n    ordered_files = sorted([Path(p) for p in batch_files], key=lambda p: p.name)\n    if not ordered_files:\n        return {\n            \"ok\": False,\n            \"scene_count\": 0,\n            \"screenplay\": {\"scenes\": []},\n            \"errors\": [{\"code\": \"no_batch_files\", \"message\": \"No scene_director batch files provided\"}],\n            \"warnings\": [],\n        }\n\n    for file_path in ordered_files:\n        if not file_path.exists():\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"missing_batch_file\",\n                \"message\": f\"Batch output file not found: {file_path}\",\n            })\n            continue\n\n        try:\n            payload = json.loads(file_path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\n        except Exception as exc:  # noqa: BLE001\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"invalid_batch_json\",\n                \"message\": f\"Failed to parse batch file {file_path}: {exc}\",\n            })\n            continue\n\n        batch_id = payload.get(\"batch_id\")\n        scenes = payload.get(\"scenes\", [])\n        if not isinstance(scenes, list):\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"invalid_batch_scenes\",\n                \"message\": f\"Batch file {file_path} has invalid 'scenes' payload\",\n            })\n            continue\n\n        if not scenes:\n            warnings.append({\n                \"code\": \"empty_batch_scenes\",\n                \"message\": f\"Batch file {file_path} produced zero scenes\",\n            })\n\n        loaded_batches.append({\n            \"batch_id\": batch_id,\n            \"file_path\": str(file_path),\n            \"scene_count\": len(scenes),\n        })\n\n        for index_in_batch, scene in enumerate(scenes, start=1):\n            if not isinstance(scene, dict):\n                errors.append({\n                    \"code\": \"invalid_scene_payload\",\n                    \"message\": f\"Batch {batch_id or file_path.name} contains a non-object scene entry\",\n                })\n                continue\n\n            missing_fields = sorted(REQUIRED_SCENE_FIELDS - set(scene.keys()))\n            if missing_fields:\n                errors.append({\n                    \"code\": \"missing_scene_fields\",\n                    \"message\": (\n                        f\"Batch {batch_id or file_path.name} scene {index_in_batch} \"\n                        f\"is missing required fields: {', '.join(missing_fields)}\"\n                    ),\n                })\n                continue\n\n            merged_scenes.append(\n                {\n                    \"source_batch_id\": batch_id,\n                    \"source_batch_scene_index\": index_in_batch,\n                    **scene,\n                }\n            )\n\n    for global_index, scene in enumerate(merged_scenes, start=1):\n        scene[\"scene_id\"] = f\"scene_{global_index:03d}\"\n\n    screenplay = {\n        \"scene_count\": len(merged_scenes),\n        \"scenes\": merged_scenes,\n    }\n\n    if output_path is not None:\n        output_path = Path(output_path)\n        output_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n        output_path.write_text(json.dumps(screenplay, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n    return {\n        \"ok\": len(errors) == 0,\n        \"scene_count\": len(merged_scenes),\n        \"batch_count\": len(loaded_batches),\n        \"screenplay\": screenplay,\n        \"loaded_batches\": loaded_batches,\n        \"output_path\": str(output_path) if output_path is not None else None,\n        \"errors\": errors,\n        \"warnings\": warnings,\n    }\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774907083070}}
{"type":"message","id":"4a9e84d2","parentId":"a71d47ab","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:45:22.862Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_2fK1QpLESncYCAT4YBC4Y6uW|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caeef3909c81958fb8bc799328e208","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\tts_polish_batch_planner.py","content":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\ndef plan_tts_polish_batches(\n    screenplay: dict[str, Any],\n    *,\n    target_scenes_per_batch: int = 5,\n    min_scenes_per_batch: int = 3,\n    max_scenes_per_batch: int = 6,\n    max_words_per_batch: int = 350,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    errors: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n    warnings: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n\n    scenes = screenplay.get(\"scenes\", []) if isinstance(screenplay, dict) else []\n    if not isinstance(scenes, list) or not scenes:\n        return {\n            \"ok\": False,\n            \"batch_count\": 0,\n            \"batches\": [],\n            \"errors\": [{\"code\": \"empty_screenplay\", \"message\": \"Cannot plan polish batches without screenplay scenes\"}],\n            \"warnings\": [],\n        }\n\n    batches: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n    current_scene_ids: list[str] = []\n    current_word_count = 0\n    batch_number = 1\n\n    def scene_word_count(scene: dict[str, Any]) -> int:\n        return len(str(scene.get(\"narration_original\", \"\")).split())\n\n    def flush_batch() -> None:\n        nonlocal current_scene_ids, current_word_count, batch_number\n        if not current_scene_ids:\n            return\n        batches.append(\n            {\n                \"batch_id\": f\"tp_{batch_number:03d}\",\n                \"scene_ids\": current_scene_ids[:],\n                \"scene_count\": len(current_scene_ids),\n                \"word_count\": current_word_count,\n            }\n        )\n        batch_number += 1\n        current_scene_ids = []\n        current_word_count = 0\n\n    for scene in scenes:\n        scene_id = scene.get(\"scene_id\")\n        if not scene_id:\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"missing_scene_id\",\n                \"message\": \"Screenplay scene is missing 'scene_id' required for polish batching\",\n            })\n            continue\n\n        words = scene_word_count(scene)\n\n        if not current_scene_ids:\n            current_scene_ids.append(scene_id)\n            current_word_count = words\n            continue\n\n        next_scene_count = len(current_scene_ids) + 1\n        next_word_count = current_word_count + words\n\n        if next_scene_count <= target_scenes_per_batch and next_word_count <= max_words_per_batch:\n            current_scene_ids.append(scene_id)\n            current_word_count = next_word_count\n            continue\n\n        if len(current_scene_ids) < min_scenes_per_batch and next_scene_count <= max_scenes_per_batch:\n            current_scene_ids.append(scene_id)\n            current_word_count = next_word_count\n            continue\n\n        flush_batch()\n        current_scene_ids.append(scene_id)\n        current_word_count = words\n\n    if current_scene_ids:\n        flush_batch()\n\n    if batches and batches[-1][\"scene_count\"] < min_scenes_per_batch and len(batches) > 1:\n        warnings.append(\n            {\n                \"code\": \"small_final_polish_batch\",\n                \"message\": (\n                    f\"Final TTS polish batch is smaller than recommended \"\n                    f\"({batches[-1]['scene_count']} scenes)\"\n                ),\n            }\n        )\n\n    return {\n        \"ok\": len(errors) == 0,\n        \"scene_count\": len(scenes),\n        \"batch_count\": len(batches),\n        \"target_scenes_per_batch\": target_scenes_per_batch,\n        \"min_scenes_per_batch\": min_scenes_per_batch,\n        \"max_scenes_per_batch\": max_scenes_per_batch,\n        \"max_words_per_batch\": max_words_per_batch,\n        \"batches\": batches,\n        \"errors\": errors,\n        \"warnings\": warnings,\n    }\n\n\ndef plan_tts_polish_batches_from_file(\n    screenplay_path: str | Path,\n    *,\n    target_scenes_per_batch: int = 5,\n    min_scenes_per_batch: int = 3,\n    max_scenes_per_batch: int = 6,\n    max_words_per_batch: int = 350,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    screenplay_path = Path(screenplay_path)\n    if not screenplay_path.exists():\n        return {\n            \"ok\": False,\n            \"batch_count\": 0,\n            \"batches\": [],\n            \"errors\": [{\"code\": \"missing_screenplay_file\", \"message\": f\"Screenplay file not found: {screenplay_path}\"}],\n            \"warnings\": [],\n        }\n\n    screenplay = json.loads(screenplay_path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\n    result = plan_tts_polish_batches(\n        screenplay,\n        target_scenes_per_batch=target_scenes_per_batch,\n        min_scenes_per_batch=min_scenes_per_batch,\n        max_scenes_per_batch=max_scenes_per_batch,\n        max_words_per_batch=max_words_per_batch,\n    )\n    result[\"screenplay_path\"] = str(screenplay_path)\n    return result\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\supervisor_skills\\\\tts_polish_batch_planner.py\",\"content\":\"from __future__ import annotations\\n\\nimport json\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\nfrom typing import Any\\n\\n\\ndef plan_tts_polish_batches(\\n    screenplay: dict[str, Any],\\n    *,\\n    target_scenes_per_batch: int = 5,\\n    min_scenes_per_batch: int = 3,\\n    max_scenes_per_batch: int = 6,\\n    max_words_per_batch: int = 350,\\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\\n    errors: list[dict[str, str]] = []\\n    warnings: list[dict[str, str]] = []\\n\\n    scenes = screenplay.get(\\\"scenes\\\", []) if isinstance(screenplay, dict) else []\\n    if not isinstance(scenes, list) or not scenes:\\n        return {\\n            \\\"ok\\\": False,\\n            \\\"batch_count\\\": 0,\\n            \\\"batches\\\": [],\\n            \\\"errors\\\": [{\\\"code\\\": \\\"empty_screenplay\\\", \\\"message\\\": \\\"Cannot plan polish batches without screenplay scenes\\\"}],\\n            \\\"warnings\\\": [],\\n        }\\n\\n    batches: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\\n    current_scene_ids: list[str] = []\\n    current_word_count = 0\\n    batch_number = 1\\n\\n    def scene_word_count(scene: dict[str, Any]) -> int:\\n        return len(str(scene.get(\\\"narration_original\\\", \\\"\\\")).split())\\n\\n    def flush_batch() -> None:\\n        nonlocal current_scene_ids, current_word_count, batch_number\\n        if not current_scene_ids:\\n            return\\n        batches.append(\\n            {\\n                \\\"batch_id\\\": f\\\"tp_{batch_number:03d}\\\",\\n                \\\"scene_ids\\\": current_scene_ids[:],\\n                \\\"scene_count\\\": len(current_scene_ids),\\n                \\\"word_count\\\": current_word_count,\\n            }\\n        )\\n        batch_number += 1\\n        current_scene_ids = []\\n        current_word_count = 0\\n\\n    for scene in scenes:\\n        scene_id = scene.get(\\\"scene_id\\\")\\n        if not scene_id:\\n            errors.append({\\n                \\\"code\\\": \\\"missing_scene_id\\\",\\n                \\\"message\\\": \\\"Screenplay scene is missing 'scene_id' required for polish batching\\\",\\n            })\\n            continue\\n\\n        words = scene_word_count(scene)\\n\\n        if not current_scene_ids:\\n            current_scene_ids.append(scene_id)\\n            current_word_count = words\\n            continue\\n\\n        next_scene_count = len(current_scene_ids) + 1\\n        next_word_count = current_word_count + words\\n\\n        if next_scene_count <= target_scenes_per_batch and next_word_count <= max_words_per_batch:\\n            current_scene_ids.append(scene_id)\\n            current_word_count = next_word_count\\n            continue\\n\\n        if len(current_scene_ids) < min_scenes_per_batch and next_scene_count <= max_scenes_per_batch:\\n            current_scene_ids.append(scene_id)\\n            current_word_count = next_word_count\\n            continue\\n\\n        flush_batch()\\n        current_scene_ids.append(scene_id)\\n        current_word_count = words\\n\\n    if current_scene_ids:\\n        flush_batch()\\n\\n    if batches and batches[-1][\\\"scene_count\\\"] < min_scenes_per_batch and len(batches) > 1:\\n        warnings.append(\\n            {\\n                \\\"code\\\": \\\"small_final_polish_batch\\\",\\n                \\\"message\\\": (\\n                    f\\\"Final TTS polish batch is smaller than recommended \\\"\\n                    f\\\"({batches[-1]['scene_count']} scenes)\\\"\\n                ),\\n            }\\n        )\\n\\n    return {\\n        \\\"ok\\\": len(errors) == 0,\\n        \\\"scene_count\\\": len(scenes),\\n        \\\"batch_count\\\": len(batches),\\n        \\\"target_scenes_per_batch\\\": target_scenes_per_batch,\\n        \\\"min_scenes_per_batch\\\": min_scenes_per_batch,\\n        \\\"max_scenes_per_batch\\\": max_scenes_per_batch,\\n        \\\"max_words_per_batch\\\": max_words_per_batch,\\n        \\\"batches\\\": batches,\\n        \\\"errors\\\": errors,\\n        \\\"warnings\\\": warnings,\\n    }\\n\\n\\ndef plan_tts_polish_batches_from_file(\\n    screenplay_path: str | Path,\\n    *,\\n    target_scenes_per_batch: int = 5,\\n    min_scenes_per_batch: int = 3,\\n    max_scenes_per_batch: int = 6,\\n    max_words_per_batch: int = 350,\\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\\n    screenplay_path = Path(screenplay_path)\\n    if not screenplay_path.exists():\\n        return {\\n            \\\"ok\\\": False,\\n            \\\"batch_count\\\": 0,\\n            \\\"batches\\\": [],\\n            \\\"errors\\\": [{\\\"code\\\": \\\"missing_screenplay_file\\\", \\\"message\\\": f\\\"Screenplay file not found: {screenplay_path}\\\"}],\\n            \\\"warnings\\\": [],\\n        }\\n\\n    screenplay = json.loads(screenplay_path.read_text(encoding=\\\"utf-8\\\"))\\n    result = plan_tts_polish_batches(\\n        screenplay,\\n        target_scenes_per_batch=target_scenes_per_batch,\\n        min_scenes_per_batch=min_scenes_per_batch,\\n        max_scenes_per_batch=max_scenes_per_batch,\\n        max_words_per_batch=max_words_per_batch,\\n    )\\n    result[\\\"screenplay_path\\\"] = str(screenplay_path)\\n    return result\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_Oef8qB0LgNrrwBMo5GJLremf|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caeef390a881958162db15e1f2deb9","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1_supervisor_contract.md","oldText":"### Implemented now\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n","newText":"### Implemented now\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1_supervisor_contract.md\",\"oldText\":\"### Implemented now\\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\\n- `script_batch_planner`\\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\\n- `screenplay_merger`\\n\",\"newText\":\"### Implemented now\\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\\n- `script_batch_planner`\\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\\n- `screenplay_merger`\\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_I79BJKAgxchKr4fSQZpU6zUy|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caeef390ac8195a9950302cc2354aa","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1_supervisor_contract.md","oldText":"### Expected next skills\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n","newText":"### Expected next skills\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1_supervisor_contract.md\",\"oldText\":\"### Expected next skills\\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\\n\",\"newText\":\"### Expected next skills\\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_SAMYavRJlmTLGKAygcd7NO9a|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caeef390b481959303871e58707720","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1_supervisor_contract.md","oldText":"## Current status summary\nAt this stage:\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\n- deterministic helper skills are being formalized\n- `s1_preflight_checker` is implemented as the entry gate for the sector\n- `s1_paths_resolver` is implemented as the canonical path/structure resolver for the sector\n- `script_batch_planner` is implemented as the first batching/planning skill for the sector\n- `scene_director_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `scene_director` operator\n- `screenplay_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch screenplay outputs\n","newText":"## Sixth implemented supervisor skill: `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n\n### Purpose\nPlan small, stable polish batches from the merged screenplay so that `tts_polish` receives manageable groups of scenes instead of the full screenplay at once.\n\n### Scope\n- receives `screenplay.json`\n- groups scenes by count and approximate word budget\n- preserves scene order\n- emits a stable `tp_###` batch sequence\n\n### Recommended v1 defaults\n- target scenes per batch: `5`\n- minimum scenes per batch: `3`\n- maximum scenes per batch: `6`\n- maximum words per batch: `350`\n\n### Out of scope\n`tts_polish_batch_planner` does **not**:\n- perform TTS polish\n- validate semantic quality\n- merge polish outputs\n- decide retry policy\n\n## Current status summary\nAt this stage:\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\n- deterministic helper skills are being formalized\n- `s1_preflight_checker` is implemented as the entry gate for the sector\n- `s1_paths_resolver` is implemented as the canonical path/structure resolver for the sector\n- `script_batch_planner` is implemented as the first batching/planning skill for the sector\n- `scene_director_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `scene_director` operator\n- `screenplay_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch screenplay outputs\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner` is implemented as the batching/planning layer for `tts_polish`\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1_supervisor_contract.md\",\"oldText\":\"## Current status summary\\nAt this stage:\\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\\n- deterministic helper skills are being formalized\\n- `s1_preflight_checker` is implemented as the entry gate for the sector\\n- `s1_paths_resolver` is implemented as the canonical path/structure resolver for the sector\\n- `script_batch_planner` is implemented as the first batching/planning skill for the sector\\n- `scene_director_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `scene_director` operator\\n- `screenplay_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch screenplay outputs\\n\",\"newText\":\"## Sixth implemented supervisor skill: `tts_polish_batch_planner`\\n\\n### Purpose\\nPlan small, stable polish batches from the merged screenplay so that `tts_polish` receives manageable groups of scenes instead of the full screenplay at once.\\n\\n### Scope\\n- receives `screenplay.json`\\n- groups scenes by count and approximate word budget\\n- preserves scene order\\n- emits a stable `tp_###` batch sequence\\n\\n### Recommended v1 defaults\\n- target scenes per batch: `5`\\n- minimum scenes per batch: `3`\\n- maximum scenes per batch: `6`\\n- maximum words per batch: `350`\\n\\n### Out of scope\\n`tts_polish_batch_planner` does **not**:\\n- perform TTS polish\\n- validate semantic quality\\n- merge polish outputs\\n- decide retry policy\\n\\n## Current status summary\\nAt this stage:\\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\\n- deterministic helper skills are being formalized\\n- `s1_preflight_checker` is implemented as the entry gate for the sector\\n- `s1_paths_resolver` is implemented as the canonical path/structure resolver for the sector\\n- `script_batch_planner` is implemented as the first batching/planning skill for the sector\\n- `scene_director_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `scene_director` operator\\n- `screenplay_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch screenplay outputs\\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner` is implemented as the batching/planning layer for `tts_polish`\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":3417,"output":2042,"cacheRead":168960,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":174419,"cost":{"input":0.008542500000000001,"output":0.03063,"cacheRead":0.04224,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0814125}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774907083881,"responseId":"resp_0047bd771936d8e20169caeecd76fc8195bceb8c455dfbc301"}}
