{"type":"message","id":"45274302","parentId":"674aed4f","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:46:52.829Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_cBoGkz0N6QykKtnJwMvbyef9|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caef4c349881959e0bdba8074eec0e","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1_supervisor_contract.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 373 - validate semantic quality\n 374 - merge polish outputs\n 375 - decide retry policy\n 376 \n+377 ## Seventh implemented supervisor skill: `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n+378 \n+379 ### Purpose\n+380 Prepare the explicit input/output contract between the S1 Supervisor and the `tts_polish` operator for each planned polish batch.\n+381 \n+382 ### Scope\n+383 - receives run/job context\n+384 - receives merged screenplay\n+385 - receives one polish batch from `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n+386 - injects `tts_polish_rules` from channel config\n+387 - writes a deterministic payload file for the operator\n+388 - declares the expected output path for the batch result\n+389 \n+390 ### Out of scope\n+391 `tts_polish_io_adapter` does **not**:\n+392 - run the operator\n+393 - validate semantic quality\n+394 - merge polish outputs\n+395 - choose retry policy\n+396 \n+397 ### Output contract principle\n+398 Each polish batch payload should explicitly tell `tts_polish`:\n+399 - which scenes belong to the batch\n+400 - what the original narration is\n+401 - what rules govern polish behavior\n+402 - where to write the result\n+403 \n 377 ## Current status summary\n 378 At this stage:\n 379 - the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\n 380 - deterministic helper skills are being formalized\n     ...\n 383 - `script_batch_planner` is implemented as the first batching/planning skill for the sector\n 384 - `scene_director_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `scene_director` operator\n 385 - `screenplay_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch screenplay outputs\n 386 - `tts_polish_batch_planner` is implemented as the batching/planning layer for `tts_polish`\n+414 - `tts_polish_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `tts_polish` operator","firstChangedLine":377},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774907212705}}
{"type":"message","id":"b9983bbc","parentId":"45274302","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:47:06.244Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Feito.\n\n## O que criei agora\n\n### Skill nova\nCriei:\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\tts_polish_io_adapter.py`\n\n---\n\n## O que ela faz\nEla cria o **contrato explícito** entre o Supervisor do S1 e o `tts_polish` para cada batch de cenas.\n\n### Funções implementadas\n- `build_tts_polish_payload(...)`\n- `write_tts_polish_payload(...)`\n\n### O payload que ela monta inclui:\n- `job_id`\n- `account`\n- `language`\n- `run_root`\n- dados do batch:\n  - `batch_id`\n  - `scene_ids`\n  - `scene_count`\n  - `word_count`\n- `tts_polish_rules` vindas da config\n- `style_context` mínimo:\n  - `channel_name`\n  - `reason`\n- instruções explícitas:\n  - polir texto para TTS sem mudar sentido\n  - preservar ordem e `scene_id`\n  - **não apagar a camada original**\n  - devolver `narration_tts`\n  - devolver metadata de mudanças quando possível\n- `scenes` concretas daquele batch\n- `output_path` esperado\n\n### E ela também já:\n- escreve o input file\n- cria diretórios necessários\n\n---\n\n## Ponto importante\nAqui já embuti explicitamente a decisão que alinhámos:\n### o `tts_polish` **não substitui** o texto original\nEle adiciona uma camada nova de texto para TTS.\n\n---\n\n## Doc central actualizado\nTambém actualizei:\n- `docs/contracts/s1_supervisor_contract.md`\n\nAgora ele já reflecte como implementadas:\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n\n---\n\n# Onde estamos agora\nO Supervisor do S1 já tem boa parte da espinha dorsal dos dois lados:\n\n## Lado `scene_director`\n- preflight\n- paths\n- script batching\n- IO adapter\n- merge\n\n## Lado `tts_polish`\n- batch planning\n- IO adapter\n\nOu seja:\njá temos planeamento + contrato explícito para os dois operators.\n\n---\n\n# Próximo passo mais lógico\nAgora o próximo componente natural é:\n\n## `tts_polish_merger`\n\nPorque:\n- já temos os batches do polish\n- já temos como preparar os inputs do operator\n- falta a recomposição final em `tts_polished.json`\n\nSe quiseres, eu sigo já nele.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0047bd771936d8e20169caef5086408195868a860fa9117b65\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":300,"output":574,"cacheRead":180608,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":181482,"cost":{"input":0.00075,"output":0.00861,"cacheRead":0.045152,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.054512}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774907213485,"responseId":"resp_0047bd771936d8e20169caef4f4c2881959f611d4372499307"}}
