{"type":"message","id":"bf3bae92","parentId":"f12a32c5","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:47:33.022Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Vou seguir para o `tts_polish_merger`, que fecha a recomposição determinística do segundo operator e completa a espinha dorsal batchada do S1.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0047bd771936d8e20169caef73200481958a699e1273423bc7\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_n7IAQnHoBymKioadnqCKz7qM|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caef75db3c8195ac1b6903695a099d","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1_supervisor_contract.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1_supervisor_contract.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_yxLvJoNt2lQ8OSc9T6pptteJ|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caef75dd308195bad6a042929dad22","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\tts_polish_io_adapter.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\supervisor_skills\\\\tts_polish_io_adapter.py\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":167,"output":146,"cacheRead":181376,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":181689,"cost":{"input":0.0004175,"output":0.00219,"cacheRead":0.045343999999999995,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.047951499999999994}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774907246878,"responseId":"resp_0047bd771936d8e20169caef717134819581f92a1735f614a1"}}
{"type":"message","id":"d2d63610","parentId":"bf3bae92","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:47:33.729Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_n7IAQnHoBymKioadnqCKz7qM|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caef75db3c8195ac1b6903695a099d","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# S1 Supervisor Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the role, boundaries, and first deterministic skill of the S1 (Pre-Production) Supervisor._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-30_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe S1 Supervisor is the supervisory layer for Pre-Production.\n\nIts job is to take a run that is `ready_for_s1` and coordinate the sector until it produces:\n- `screenplay.json`\n- `screenplay_validation.json`\n- `tts_polished.json`\n- `polish_validation.json`\n- `scene_bible.json`\n- `b1_*` checkpoints\n\nThe supervisor is an **OpenClaw LLM supervisor**, not a purely conversational helper and not a monolithic Python script that absorbs all work itself.\n\nIt should supervise using:\n- deterministic Python skills\n- specialized operators/sub-agents\n- explicit file contracts\n\n---\n\n## Core principle\n\n### Supervisor = brain\n### Skills = hands\n### Operators = specialists\n\nThe S1 Supervisor should:\n- decide the order of operations\n- decide when to call an operator vs a deterministic skill\n- interpret validation results\n- decide retry / fail / continue\n- write or trigger checkpoints\n\nThe S1 Supervisor should **not** directly absorb:\n- semantic scene generation\n- TTS polish generation\n- low-level file/path mechanics\n- deterministic validation logic\n- JSON merge/reindex mechanics\n\nThose belong to:\n- S1 operators (`scene_director`, `tts_polish`)\n- deterministic supervisor skills\n\n---\n\n## Current operator model\n\nThe current intended operator structure for S1 is:\n- `scene_director` -> OpenClaw operator\n- `tts_polish` -> OpenClaw operator\n\nThese operators communicate with the supervisor via explicit file contracts:\n- supervisor prepares input payload/file\n- operator reads input\n- operator writes output file\n- supervisor validates and decides next step\n\n---\n\n## Current deterministic skills owned by the supervisor\n\n### Implemented now\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n\n### Expected next skills\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n- `retry_planner`\n- `checkpoint_writer`\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\n\nThis list may evolve, but the supervisor should remain supervisory rather than mechanically overloaded.\n\n---\n\n## File contract principle\n\nThe supervisor must operate on persisted run artifacts.\n\nMinimum expected inputs before S1 begins:\n- `job.json`\n- `run_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_raw.txt`\n- `inputs/script/script_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_lock.json`\n- `checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json`\n\nMinimum expected outputs after S1 completes:\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay_validation.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/polish_validation.json`\n- `scene_bible.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step1_screenplay.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step2_screenplay_validated.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step3_tts_polished.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step4_polish_validated.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step5_scene_bible.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_complete.json`\n\n---\n\n## First implemented supervisor skill: `s1_preflight_checker`\n\n### Purpose\nValidate that a run is structurally ready to enter S1 before any operator or semantic step is invoked.\n\n### Scope\nChecks:\n- run root exists\n- required input files exist\n- `job.json` is readable and contains `job_id`, `account`, `language`\n- channel config exists at `accounts/{account}/{language}.yaml`\n- `script_raw.txt` is readable and not empty\n- `vo_script_ready` checkpoint exists\n- run state is minimally compatible with entering S1\n\n### Out of scope\n`s1_preflight_checker` does **not**:\n- create sector outputs\n- call operators\n- validate screenplay semantics\n- decide batching\n- modify the run\n\n### Input shape\n```json\n{\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\"\n}\n```\n\n### Output shape\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"job\": {\n    \"job_id\": \"2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n    \"account\": \"004\",\n    \"language\": \"fr\"\n  },\n  \"paths\": {\n    \"job_json\": \".../job.json\",\n    \"run_metadata\": \".../run_metadata.json\",\n    \"script_raw\": \".../inputs/script/script_raw.txt\",\n    \"script_metadata\": \".../inputs/script/script_metadata.json\",\n    \"script_lock\": \".../inputs/script/script_lock.json\",\n    \"vo_script_ready_checkpoint\": \".../checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json\",\n    \"channel_config\": \".../accounts/004/fr.yaml\"\n  },\n  \"script_stats\": {\n    \"char_count\": 0,\n    \"word_count\": 0\n  },\n  \"errors\": [],\n  \"warnings\": []\n}\n```\n\n### Error policy\nThe skill should collect all relevant failures and return them together.\nIt should not stop at the first missing file.\n\n### Warning policy\nExamples of warning-worthy but non-fatal conditions:\n- script very short\n- script very long\n- `b1_pre_production/` already exists but `b1_complete.json` does not\n\n### Fatal examples\n- missing `job.json`\n- missing `script_raw.txt`\n- unreadable or invalid `job.json`\n- missing channel config\n- missing `vo_script_ready.json`\n- empty script\n\n---\n\n## Naming convention\nThe canonical checkpoint and sector naming for Pre-Production is:\n- `b1_pre_production/`\n- `b1_*` checkpoints\n\nThe older `s1_*` naming should not be treated as canonical.\n\n---\n\n## Second implemented supervisor skill: `s1_paths_resolver`\n\n### Purpose\nResolve and centralize the canonical S1 paths for the run.\n\n### Scope\nResolves and optionally creates the directory structure for:\n- `b1_pre_production/`\n- `b1_pre_production/inputs/`\n- `b1_pre_production/intermediate/`\n- `inputs/scene_director/`\n- `inputs/tts_polish/`\n- `intermediate/scene_director/`\n- `intermediate/tts_polish/`\n- canonical output file paths\n- canonical `b1_*` checkpoint file paths\n\n### Out of scope\n`s1_paths_resolver` does **not**:\n- validate semantic readiness\n- call operators\n- inspect screenplay or polish content\n- perform batching\n\n### Input shape\n```json\n{\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"create_dirs\": true\n}\n```\n\n### Output shape\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"created_dirs\": true,\n  \"paths\": {\n    \"b1_root\": \".../b1_pre_production\",\n    \"inputs_root\": \".../b1_pre_production/inputs\",\n    \"intermediate_root\": \".../b1_pre_production/intermediate\",\n    \"screenplay_path\": \".../b1_pre_production/screenplay.json\",\n    \"tts_polished_path\": \".../b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json\",\n    \"scene_bible_path\": \".../scene_bible.json\",\n    \"b1_complete_checkpoint\": \".../checkpoints/b1_complete.json\"\n  },\n  \"errors\": [],\n  \"warnings\": []\n}\n```\n\n## Third implemented supervisor skill: `script_batch_planner`\n\n### Purpose\nSplit the raw script into manageable work batches for `scene_director` without turning the supervisor into a monolithic batching script.\n\n### Scope\n- receives raw script text or script file path\n- plans batches using target/min/max word budgets\n- prefers paragraph boundaries\n- falls back to sentence-based splitting for oversized paragraphs\n- preserves order and emits a stable `sd_###` batch sequence\n\n### Out of scope\n`script_batch_planner` does **not**:\n- divide the script into final scenes\n- call `scene_director`\n- perform semantic validation\n- merge operator outputs\n\n### Recommended v1 defaults\n- target words per batch: `750`\n- minimum words per batch: `450`\n- maximum words per batch: `950`\n\n### Output shape\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"total_words\": 3520,\n  \"batch_count\": 5,\n  \"target_words_per_batch\": 750,\n  \"min_words_per_batch\": 450,\n  \"max_words_per_batch\": 950,\n  \"batches\": [\n    {\n      \"batch_id\": \"sd_001\",\n      \"start_word\": 1,\n      \"end_word\": 742,\n      \"word_count\": 742,\n      \"text\": \"...\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"errors\": [],\n  \"warnings\": []\n}\n```\n\n## Fourth implemented supervisor skill: `scene_director_io_adapter`\n\n### Purpose\nPrepare the explicit input/output contract between the S1 Supervisor and the `scene_director` operator for each planned script batch.\n\n### Scope\n- receives run/job context\n- receives one script batch from `script_batch_planner`\n- injects `scene_words_range` from channel config\n- writes a deterministic payload file for the operator\n- declares the expected output path for the batch result\n\n### Out of scope\n`scene_director_io_adapter` does **not**:\n- run the operator\n- validate semantic quality\n- merge batch outputs\n- choose retry policy\n\n### Output contract principle\nEach batch payload should explicitly tell `scene_director`:\n- who the run/job is\n- what the batch text is\n- what scene structure is expected\n- where to write the result\n\n## Fifth implemented supervisor skill: `screenplay_merger`\n\n### Purpose\nMerge the batch outputs of `scene_director` into one canonical `screenplay.json` without forcing the supervisor itself to concatenate, validate, and reindex scene objects manually.\n\n### Scope\n- loads ordered batch output files\n- validates minimum required scene fields\n- concatenates scenes in batch order\n- reassigns canonical `scene_###` IDs globally\n- writes `screenplay.json`\n\n### Out of scope\n`screenplay_merger` does **not**:\n- perform semantic validation\n- decide retry policy\n- invoke operators\n- polish TTS text\n\n### Output contract principle\nThe merged screenplay should preserve order while normalizing scene IDs into one canonical sequence for the rest of S1.\n\n## Sixth implemented supervisor skill: `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n\n### Purpose\nPlan small, stable polish batches from the merged screenplay so that `tts_polish` receives manageable groups of scenes instead of the full screenplay at once.\n\n### Scope\n- receives `screenplay.json`\n- groups scenes by count and approximate word budget\n- preserves scene order\n- emits a stable `tp_###` batch sequence\n\n### Recommended v1 defaults\n- target scenes per batch: `5`\n- minimum scenes per batch: `3`\n- maximum scenes per batch: `6`\n- maximum words per batch: `350`\n\n### Out of scope\n`tts_polish_batch_planner` does **not**:\n- perform TTS polish\n- validate semantic quality\n- merge polish outputs\n- decide retry policy\n\n## Seventh implemented supervisor skill: `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n\n### Purpose\nPrepare the explicit input/output contract between the S1 Supervisor and the `tts_polish` operator for each planned polish batch.\n\n### Scope\n- receives run/job context\n- receives merged screenplay\n- receives one polish batch from `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- injects `tts_polish_rules` from channel config\n- writes a deterministic payload file for the operator\n- declares the expected output path for the batch result\n\n### Out of scope\n`tts_polish_io_adapter` does **not**:\n- run the operator\n- validate semantic quality\n- merge polish outputs\n- choose retry policy\n\n### Output contract principle\nEach polish batch payload should explicitly tell `tts_polish`:\n- which scenes belong to the batch\n- what the original narration is\n- what rules govern polish behavior\n- where to write the result\n\n## Current status summary\nAt this stage:\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\n- deterministic helper skills are being formalized\n- `s1_preflight_checker` is implemented as the entry gate for the sector\n- `s1_paths_resolver` is implemented as the canonical path/structure resolver for the sector\n- `script_batch_planner` is implemented as the first batching/planning skill for the sector\n- `scene_director_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `scene_director` operator\n- `screenplay_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch screenplay outputs\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner` is implemented as the batching/planning layer for `tts_polish`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `tts_polish` operator\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774907253610}}
{"type":"message","id":"ac9d39a5","parentId":"d2d63610","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:47:33.854Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_yxLvJoNt2lQ8OSc9T6pptteJ|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caef75dd308195bad6a042929dad22","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\ndef build_tts_polish_payload(\n    *,\n    run_root: str | Path,\n    job: dict[str, Any],\n    screenplay: dict[str, Any],\n    batch: dict[str, Any],\n    channel_config: dict[str, Any],\n    output_path: str | Path,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    run_root = Path(run_root)\n    output_path = Path(output_path)\n\n    scene_ids = batch.get(\"scene_ids\", [])\n    scene_map = {\n        scene.get(\"scene_id\"): scene\n        for scene in screenplay.get(\"scenes\", [])\n        if isinstance(scene, dict) and scene.get(\"scene_id\")\n    }\n    scenes = [scene_map[scene_id] for scene_id in scene_ids if scene_id in scene_map]\n\n    payload = {\n        \"job_id\": job.get(\"job_id\"),\n        \"account\": job.get(\"account\"),\n        \"language\": job.get(\"language\"),\n        \"run_root\": str(run_root),\n        \"batch\": {\n            \"batch_id\": batch.get(\"batch_id\"),\n            \"scene_ids\": scene_ids,\n            \"scene_count\": batch.get(\"scene_count\"),\n            \"word_count\": batch.get(\"word_count\"),\n        },\n        \"tts_polish_rules\": channel_config.get(\"tts_polish_rules\", []),\n        \"style_context\": {\n            \"channel_name\": job.get(\"channel_name\"),\n            \"reason\": job.get(\"reason\"),\n        },\n        \"instructions\": {\n            \"task\": \"Polish the narration text for TTS without changing meaning.\",\n            \"requirements\": [\n                \"Preserve scene order and scene IDs.\",\n                \"Do not remove the original narration layer.\",\n                \"Return narration_tts for each scene.\",\n                \"Keep meaning intact while improving speakability.\",\n                \"Return changes metadata for each scene when possible.\",\n            ],\n        },\n        \"scenes\": scenes,\n        \"output_path\": str(output_path),\n    }\n\n    return payload\n\n\ndef write_tts_polish_payload(\n    *,\n    run_root: str | Path,\n    job: dict[str, Any],\n    screenplay: dict[str, Any],\n    batch: dict[str, Any],\n    channel_config: dict[str, Any],\n    input_path: str | Path,\n    output_path: str | Path,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    input_path = Path(input_path)\n    output_path = Path(output_path)\n    input_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    output_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n    payload = build_tts_polish_payload(\n        run_root=run_root,\n        job=job,\n        screenplay=screenplay,\n        batch=batch,\n        channel_config=channel_config,\n        output_path=output_path,\n    )\n\n    input_path.write_text(json.dumps(payload, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n    return {\n        \"ok\": True,\n        \"input_path\": str(input_path),\n        \"output_path\": str(output_path),\n        \"batch_id\": batch.get(\"batch_id\"),\n        \"payload\": payload,\n        \"errors\": [],\n        \"warnings\": [],\n    }\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774907253729}}
{"type":"message","id":"f4e3f189","parentId":"ac9d39a5","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:48:17.384Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_1VPLaOSzj2GjiIuHiZwiEsKD|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caefa2177c81958a3fff9511eba3c7","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\tts_polish_merger.py","content":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\nREQUIRED_POLISH_FIELDS = {\n    \"scene_id\",\n    \"narration_original\",\n    \"narration_tts\",\n}\n\n\ndef merge_tts_polish_batches(\n    batch_files: list[str | Path],\n    *,\n    screenplay: dict[str, Any],\n    output_path: str | Path | None = None,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    errors: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n    warnings: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n    ordered_files = sorted([Path(p) for p in batch_files], key=lambda p: p.name)\n\n    scenes = screenplay.get(\"scenes\", []) if isinstance(screenplay, dict) else []\n    ordered_scene_ids = [scene.get(\"scene_id\") for scene in scenes if isinstance(scene, dict) and scene.get(\"scene_id\")]\n\n    if not ordered_files:\n        return {\n            \"ok\": False,\n            \"scene_count\": 0,\n            \"tts_polished\": {\"scenes\": []},\n            \"errors\": [{\"code\": \"no_batch_files\", \"message\": \"No tts_polish batch files provided\"}],\n            \"warnings\": [],\n        }\n\n    polish_map: dict[str, dict[str, Any]] = {}\n    loaded_batches: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n\n    for file_path in ordered_files:\n        if not file_path.exists():\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"missing_batch_file\",\n                \"message\": f\"Polish batch file not found: {file_path}\",\n            })\n            continue\n\n        try:\n            payload = json.loads(file_path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\n        except Exception as exc:  # noqa: BLE001\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"invalid_batch_json\",\n                \"message\": f\"Failed to parse polish batch file {file_path}: {exc}\",\n            })\n            continue\n\n        batch_id = payload.get(\"batch_id\")\n        batch_scenes = payload.get(\"scenes\", [])\n        if not isinstance(batch_scenes, list):\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"invalid_batch_scenes\",\n                \"message\": f\"Polish batch file {file_path} has invalid 'scenes' payload\",\n            })\n            continue\n\n        if not batch_scenes:\n            warnings.append({\n                \"code\": \"empty_polish_batch\",\n                \"message\": f\"Polish batch file {file_path} produced zero scenes\",\n            })\n\n        loaded_batches.append(\n            {\n                \"batch_id\": batch_id,\n                \"file_path\": str(file_path),\n                \"scene_count\": len(batch_scenes),\n            }\n        )\n\n        for scene in batch_scenes:\n            if not isinstance(scene, dict):\n                errors.append({\n                    \"code\": \"invalid_scene_payload\",\n                    \"message\": f\"Polish batch {batch_id or file_path.name} contains a non-object scene entry\",\n                })\n                continue\n\n            missing_fields = sorted(REQUIRED_POLISH_FIELDS - set(scene.keys()))\n            if missing_fields:\n                errors.append({\n                    \"code\": \"missing_polish_fields\",\n                    \"message\": (\n                        f\"Polish batch {batch_id or file_path.name} scene is missing required fields: \"\n                        f\"{', '.join(missing_fields)}\"\n                    ),\n                })\n                continue\n\n            scene_id = scene.get(\"scene_id\")\n            if scene_id in polish_map:\n                warnings.append({\n                    \"code\": \"duplicate_scene_polish\",\n                    \"message\": f\"Scene {scene_id} appeared more than once across polish batches; latest entry kept\",\n                })\n            polish_map[scene_id] = scene\n\n    merged_scenes: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n    for scene_id in ordered_scene_ids:\n        polished_scene = polish_map.get(scene_id)\n        if not polished_scene:\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"missing_polish_scene\",\n                \"message\": f\"No polish output found for screenplay scene {scene_id}\",\n            })\n            continue\n        merged_scenes.append(polished_scene)\n\n    tts_polished = {\n        \"scene_count\": len(merged_scenes),\n        \"scenes\": merged_scenes,\n    }\n\n    if output_path is not None:\n        output_path = Path(output_path)\n        output_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n        output_path.write_text(json.dumps(tts_polished, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n    return {\n        \"ok\": len(errors) == 0,\n        \"scene_count\": len(merged_scenes),\n        \"batch_count\": len(loaded_batches),\n        \"tts_polished\": tts_polished,\n        \"loaded_batches\": loaded_batches,\n        \"output_path\": str(output_path) if output_path is not None else None,\n        \"errors\": errors,\n        \"warnings\": warnings,\n    }\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\supervisor_skills\\\\tts_polish_merger.py\",\"content\":\"from __future__ import annotations\\n\\nimport json\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\nfrom typing import Any\\n\\n\\nREQUIRED_POLISH_FIELDS = {\\n    \\\"scene_id\\\",\\n    \\\"narration_original\\\",\\n    \\\"narration_tts\\\",\\n}\\n\\n\\ndef merge_tts_polish_batches(\\n    batch_files: list[str | Path],\\n    *,\\n    screenplay: dict[str, Any],\\n    output_path: str | Path | None = None,\\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\\n    errors: list[dict[str, str]] = []\\n    warnings: list[dict[str, str]] = []\\n    ordered_files = sorted([Path(p) for p in batch_files], key=lambda p: p.name)\\n\\n    scenes = screenplay.get(\\\"scenes\\\", []) if isinstance(screenplay, dict) else []\\n    ordered_scene_ids = [scene.get(\\\"scene_id\\\") for scene in scenes if isinstance(scene, dict) and scene.get(\\\"scene_id\\\")]\\n\\n    if not ordered_files:\\n        return {\\n            \\\"ok\\\": False,\\n            \\\"scene_count\\\": 0,\\n            \\\"tts_polished\\\": {\\\"scenes\\\": []},\\n            \\\"errors\\\": [{\\\"code\\\": \\\"no_batch_files\\\", \\\"message\\\": \\\"No tts_polish batch files provided\\\"}],\\n            \\\"warnings\\\": [],\\n        }\\n\\n    polish_map: dict[str, dict[str, Any]] = {}\\n    loaded_batches: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\\n\\n    for file_path in ordered_files:\\n        if not file_path.exists():\\n            errors.append({\\n                \\\"code\\\": \\\"missing_batch_file\\\",\\n                \\\"message\\\": f\\\"Polish batch file not found: {file_path}\\\",\\n            })\\n            continue\\n\\n        try:\\n            payload = json.loads(file_path.read_text(encoding=\\\"utf-8\\\"))\\n        except Exception as exc:  # noqa: BLE001\\n            errors.append({\\n                \\\"code\\\": \\\"invalid_batch_json\\\",\\n                \\\"message\\\": f\\\"Failed to parse polish batch file {file_path}: {exc}\\\",\\n            })\\n            continue\\n\\n        batch_id = payload.get(\\\"batch_id\\\")\\n        batch_scenes = payload.get(\\\"scenes\\\", [])\\n        if not isinstance(batch_scenes, list):\\n            errors.append({\\n                \\\"code\\\": \\\"invalid_batch_scenes\\\",\\n                \\\"message\\\": f\\\"Polish batch file {file_path} has invalid 'scenes' payload\\\",\\n            })\\n            continue\\n\\n        if not batch_scenes:\\n            warnings.append({\\n                \\\"code\\\": \\\"empty_polish_batch\\\",\\n                \\\"message\\\": f\\\"Polish batch file {file_path} produced zero scenes\\\",\\n            })\\n\\n        loaded_batches.append(\\n            {\\n                \\\"batch_id\\\": batch_id,\\n                \\\"file_path\\\": str(file_path),\\n                \\\"scene_count\\\": len(batch_scenes),\\n            }\\n        )\\n\\n        for scene in batch_scenes:\\n            if not isinstance(scene, dict):\\n                errors.append({\\n                    \\\"code\\\": \\\"invalid_scene_payload\\\",\\n                    \\\"message\\\": f\\\"Polish batch {batch_id or file_path.name} contains a non-object scene entry\\\",\\n                })\\n                continue\\n\\n            missing_fields = sorted(REQUIRED_POLISH_FIELDS - set(scene.keys()))\\n            if missing_fields:\\n                errors.append({\\n                    \\\"code\\\": \\\"missing_polish_fields\\\",\\n                    \\\"message\\\": (\\n                        f\\\"Polish batch {batch_id or file_path.name} scene is missing required fields: \\\"\\n                        f\\\"{', '.join(missing_fields)}\\\"\\n                    ),\\n                })\\n                continue\\n\\n            scene_id = scene.get(\\\"scene_id\\\")\\n            if scene_id in polish_map:\\n                warnings.append({\\n                    \\\"code\\\": \\\"duplicate_scene_polish\\\",\\n                    \\\"message\\\": f\\\"Scene {scene_id} appeared more than once across polish batches; latest entry kept\\\",\\n                })\\n            polish_map[scene_id] = scene\\n\\n    merged_scenes: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\\n    for scene_id in ordered_scene_ids:\\n        polished_scene = polish_map.get(scene_id)\\n        if not polished_scene:\\n            errors.append({\\n                \\\"code\\\": \\\"missing_polish_scene\\\",\\n                \\\"message\\\": f\\\"No polish output found for screenplay scene {scene_id}\\\",\\n            })\\n            continue\\n        merged_scenes.append(polished_scene)\\n\\n    tts_polished = {\\n        \\\"scene_count\\\": len(merged_scenes),\\n        \\\"scenes\\\": merged_scenes,\\n    }\\n\\n    if output_path is not None:\\n        output_path = Path(output_path)\\n        output_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\\n        output_path.write_text(json.dumps(tts_polished, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False), encoding=\\\"utf-8\\\")\\n\\n    return {\\n        \\\"ok\\\": len(errors) == 0,\\n        \\\"scene_count\\\": len(merged_scenes),\\n        \\\"batch_count\\\": len(loaded_batches),\\n        \\\"tts_polished\\\": tts_polished,\\n        \\\"loaded_batches\\\": loaded_batches,\\n        \\\"output_path\\\": str(output_path) if output_path is not None else None,\\n        \\\"errors\\\": errors,\\n        \\\"warnings\\\": warnings,\\n    }\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6exXwWnqZuOpYgGCB4cUVXge|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caefa217948195a94f0d0d3d9d7ebd","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1_supervisor_contract.md","oldText":"### Implemented now\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n","newText":"### Implemented now\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1_supervisor_contract.md\",\"oldText\":\"### Implemented now\\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\\n- `script_batch_planner`\\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\\n- `screenplay_merger`\\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\\n\",\"newText\":\"### Implemented now\\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\\n- `script_batch_planner`\\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\\n- `screenplay_merger`\\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\\n- `tts_polish_merger`\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_SVEDtO1hQ2x488pTCXHnpSlV|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caefa217a08195bac91606dbded536","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1_supervisor_contract.md","oldText":"### Expected next skills\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n- `retry_planner`\n","newText":"### Expected next skills\n- `retry_planner`\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1_supervisor_contract.md\",\"oldText\":\"### Expected next skills\\n- `tts_polish_merger`\\n- `retry_planner`\\n\",\"newText\":\"### Expected next skills\\n- `retry_planner`\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_Q77GQMZJVDfh0Y4Vt8gmlCkD|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caefa217ac819594e5a91c83bfeabb","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1_supervisor_contract.md","oldText":"## Current status summary\nAt this stage:\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\n- deterministic helper skills are being formalized\n- `s1_preflight_checker` is implemented as the entry gate for the sector\n- `s1_paths_resolver` is implemented as the canonical path/structure resolver for the sector\n- `script_batch_planner` is implemented as the first batching/planning skill for the sector\n- `scene_director_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `scene_director` operator\n- `screenplay_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch screenplay outputs\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner` is implemented as the batching/planning layer for `tts_polish`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `tts_polish` operator\n","newText":"## Eighth implemented supervisor skill: `tts_polish_merger`\n\n### Purpose\nMerge the batch outputs of `tts_polish` into one canonical `tts_polished.json` while preserving screenplay order and preserving the distinction between original narration and TTS-polished narration.\n\n### Scope\n- loads ordered polish batch files\n- validates minimum required polish scene fields\n- rebuilds one ordered `tts_polished.json`\n- uses screenplay order as the canonical scene sequence\n\n### Out of scope\n`tts_polish_merger` does **not**:\n- validate semantic quality of the polish\n- decide retry policy\n- invoke operators\n- overwrite the original screenplay artifact\n\n### Output contract principle\nThe merged polish output should preserve:\n- `scene_id`\n- `narration_original`\n- `narration_tts`\n\nwithout destroying the original screenplay layer.\n\n## Current status summary\nAt this stage:\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\n- deterministic helper skills are being formalized\n- `s1_preflight_checker` is implemented as the entry gate for the sector\n- `s1_paths_resolver` is implemented as the canonical path/structure resolver for the sector\n- `script_batch_planner` is implemented as the first batching/planning skill for the sector\n- `scene_director_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `scene_director` operator\n- `screenplay_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch screenplay outputs\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner` is implemented as the batching/planning layer for `tts_polish`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `tts_polish` operator\n- `tts_polish_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch polish outputs\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1_supervisor_contract.md\",\"oldText\":\"## Current status summary\\nAt this stage:\\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\\n- deterministic helper skills are being formalized\\n- `s1_preflight_checker` is implemented as the entry gate for the sector\\n- `s1_paths_resolver` is implemented as the canonical path/structure resolver for the sector\\n- `script_batch_planner` is implemented as the first batching/planning skill for the sector\\n- `scene_director_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `scene_director` operator\\n- `screenplay_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch screenplay outputs\\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner` is implemented as the batching/planning layer for `tts_polish`\\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `tts_polish` operator\\n\",\"newText\":\"## Eighth implemented supervisor skill: `tts_polish_merger`\\n\\n### Purpose\\nMerge the batch outputs of `tts_polish` into one canonical `tts_polished.json` while preserving screenplay order and preserving the distinction between original narration and TTS-polished narration.\\n\\n### Scope\\n- loads ordered polish batch files\\n- validates minimum required polish scene fields\\n- rebuilds one ordered `tts_polished.json`\\n- uses screenplay order as the canonical scene sequence\\n\\n### Out of scope\\n`tts_polish_merger` does **not**:\\n- validate semantic quality of the polish\\n- decide retry policy\\n- invoke operators\\n- overwrite the original screenplay artifact\\n\\n### Output contract principle\\nThe merged polish output should preserve:\\n- `scene_id`\\n- `narration_original`\\n- `narration_tts`\\n\\nwithout destroying the original screenplay layer.\\n\\n## Current status summary\\nAt this stage:\\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\\n- deterministic helper skills are being formalized\\n- `s1_preflight_checker` is implemented as the entry gate for the sector\\n- `s1_paths_resolver` is implemented as the canonical path/structure resolver for the sector\\n- `script_batch_planner` is implemented as the first batching/planning skill for the sector\\n- `scene_director_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `scene_director` operator\\n- `screenplay_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch screenplay outputs\\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner` is implemented as the batching/planning layer for `tts_polish`\\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `tts_polish` operator\\n- `tts_polish_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch polish outputs\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":101108,"output":2166,"cacheRead":83456,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":186730,"cost":{"input":0.25277,"output":0.03249,"cacheRead":0.020864,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.306124}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774907254510,"responseId":"resp_0047bd771936d8e20169caef7834f08195b0de41d8ebe1e8af"}}
