{"type":"message","id":"82095ff6","parentId":"d08f92da","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:48:18.826Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_Q77GQMZJVDfh0Y4Vt8gmlCkD|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caefa217ac819594e5a91c83bfeabb","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1_supervisor_contract.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 400 - what the original narration is\n 401 - what rules govern polish behavior\n 402 - where to write the result\n 403 \n+404 ## Eighth implemented supervisor skill: `tts_polish_merger`\n+405 \n+406 ### Purpose\n+407 Merge the batch outputs of `tts_polish` into one canonical `tts_polished.json` while preserving screenplay order and preserving the distinction between original narration and TTS-polished narration.\n+408 \n+409 ### Scope\n+410 - loads ordered polish batch files\n+411 - validates minimum required polish scene fields\n+412 - rebuilds one ordered `tts_polished.json`\n+413 - uses screenplay order as the canonical scene sequence\n+414 \n+415 ### Out of scope\n+416 `tts_polish_merger` does **not**:\n+417 - validate semantic quality of the polish\n+418 - decide retry policy\n+419 - invoke operators\n+420 - overwrite the original screenplay artifact\n+421 \n+422 ### Output contract principle\n+423 The merged polish output should preserve:\n+424 - `scene_id`\n+425 - `narration_original`\n+426 - `narration_tts`\n+427 \n+428 without destroying the original screenplay layer.\n+429 \n 404 ## Current status summary\n 405 At this stage:\n 406 - the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\n 407 - deterministic helper skills are being formalized\n     ...\n 411 - `scene_director_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `scene_director` operator\n 412 - `screenplay_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch screenplay outputs\n 413 - `tts_polish_batch_planner` is implemented as the batching/planning layer for `tts_polish`\n 414 - `tts_polish_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `tts_polish` operator\n+441 - `tts_polish_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch polish outputs","firstChangedLine":404},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774907298696}}
{"type":"message","id":"d691b4b4","parentId":"82095ff6","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:48:33.968Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Feito.\n\n## O que criei agora\n\n### Skill nova\nCriei:\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\tts_polish_merger.py`\n\n---\n\n## O que ela faz\nEla fecha a recomposição do segundo operator e gera o:\n## `tts_polished.json` canónico\n\n### Função implementada\n- `merge_tts_polish_batches(batch_files, screenplay, output_path=None)`\n\n### O que ela faz concretamente\n- recebe os batch files do `tts_polish`\n- ordena os ficheiros\n- lê o JSON de cada batch\n- extrai as cenas polidas\n- valida campos mínimos obrigatórios:\n  - `scene_id`\n  - `narration_original`\n  - `narration_tts`\n- usa a ordem do `screenplay` como ordem canónica\n- reconstrói um `tts_polished.json` único\n- **preserva a distinção** entre:\n  - texto original da cena\n  - texto polido para TTS\n- escreve o output final se `output_path` for fornecido\n\n### Também trata problemas\n- ficheiro batch ausente\n- JSON inválido\n- `scenes` malformado\n- campos obrigatórios ausentes\n- cena duplicada em batches\n- cena do screenplay sem correspondente no polish output\n\n---\n\n## Ponto importante\nAqui a regra que discutimos ficou materializada:\n### o polish **não sobrescreve** o screenplay\nEle recompõe uma camada separada com:\n- `narration_original`\n- `narration_tts`\n\n---\n\n## Doc central actualizado\nTambém actualizei:\n- `docs/contracts/s1_supervisor_contract.md`\n\nAgora ele já reflecte como implementadas:\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n\n---\n\n# Onde estamos agora\nA espinha dorsal batchada do Supervisor do S1 está muito mais concreta.\n\n## Lado `scene_director`\n- preflight\n- paths\n- batching\n- IO adapter\n- merge\n\n## Lado `tts_polish`\n- batching\n- IO adapter\n- merge\n\nOu seja:\n## já temos a mecânica principal dos dois operators bem menos dependente de improviso do supervisor\n\n---\n\n# Próximo passo mais lógico\nAgora o próximo componente natural é:\n\n## `retry_planner`\n\nPorque:\n- já temos a espinha dorsal do fluxo\n- falta a peça que ajuda o supervisor a decidir:\n  - repetir step?\n  - repetir batches?\n  - falhar?\n  - seguir?\n\nSe quiseres, eu sigo já nele.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0047bd771936d8e20169caefa864748195bb820c8ea2e31758\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":94580,"output":608,"cacheRead":85504,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":180692,"cost":{"input":0.23645000000000002,"output":0.00912,"cacheRead":0.021376,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.266946}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774907299441,"responseId":"resp_0047bd771936d8e20169caefa58a3c8195a6b33728fbb18351"}}
{"type":"message","id":"4a343903","parentId":"d691b4b4","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:49:07.951Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Mon 2026-03-30 18:49 GMT-3] Que ffalhas poderiam ser essas? Só asism pra entender o que d3eve ser feito caso alguma ocorra ne"}],"timestamp":1774907347866}}
{"type":"message","id":"a6e686b3","parentId":"4a343903","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:49:48.172Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Boa. Essa é exactamente a pergunta certa antes de criar o `retry_planner`.\n\nPorque o `retry_planner` não deve existir como algo abstrato.  \nEle só faz sentido se soubermos:\n## **que tipos de falha realmente podem acontecer**\ne\n## **o que fazer em cada uma**\n\nVou organizar por tipo de falha.\n\n---\n\n# 1. Falhas de preflight\nEstas acontecem **antes** do setor começar de verdade.\n\n## Exemplos\n- `job.json` ausente\n- `script_raw.txt` ausente\n- config do canal ausente\n- `vo_script_ready.json` ausente\n- script vazio\n- `b1_complete.json` já existe\n\n## O que fazer\n### Não retryar automaticamente.\nEstas falhas são:\n## **estruturais**\nnão transitórias.\n\n### Resposta correcta\n- abortar cedo\n- devolver erro claro\n- pedir correção estrutural\n\n### Então:\n`retry_planner` nem devia entrar muito aqui.\nIsto é mais:\n## fail-fast\n\n---\n\n# 2. Falhas do `scene_director`\nAqui começa o retry real.\n\nEstas podem acontecer em 3 camadas.\n\n---\n\n## 2A. Falha de execução do operator\nExemplos:\n- agent não respondeu\n- timeout\n- output file não foi escrito\n- output JSON inválido\n- output vazio\n- batch incompleto\n\n## O que fazer\n### Retry do batch específico\nnão do setor inteiro.\n\n### Política provável\n- retry do mesmo batch\n- até 3 vezes\n- depois escalar\n\n### Porque\nIsto é falha operacional de execução,\nnão necessariamente falha semântica do setor inteiro.\n\n---\n\n## 2B. Falha estrutural do output do `scene_director`\nExemplos:\n- cena sem `narration_original`\n- sem `visual_direction`\n- sem `mood`\n- sem `duration_estimate`\n- shape errado do JSON\n\n## O que fazer\n### Retry do batch específico\n\nPorque:\n- o batch output veio mal formado\n- dá para pedir regeneração daquele pedaço\n\n---\n\n## 2C. Falha semântica detectada pelo `screenplay_validator`\nExemplos:\n- coverage baixo\n- missing words\n- extra words\n- duplicação entre cenas\n- chunking sem preservar bem o sentido\n\n## O que fazer\nAqui há nuance.\n\n### v1 simples\nRetry do **step de screenplay**\nou dos **batches afectados**, se conseguirmos mapear.\n\n### ideal futuro\nRetry cirúrgico só nos batches/cenas que causaram o problema.\n\n### Então o `retry_planner` aqui precisa decidir:\n- step inteiro?\n- subset de batches?\n- fail?\n\n---\n\n# 3. Falhas do `tts_polish`\nTambém se dividem em 3 camadas.\n\n---\n\n## 3A. Falha de execução do operator\nExemplos:\n- agent não respondeu\n- timeout\n- output file não escrito\n- JSON inválido\n- batch vazio\n\n## O que fazer\n### Retry do batch específico\n\n---\n\n## 3B. Falha estrutural do output do polish\nExemplos:\n- sem `scene_id`\n- sem `narration_original`\n- sem `narration_tts`\n- cenas faltando no batch\n\n## O que fazer\n### Retry do batch específico\n\n---\n\n## 3C. Falha semântica detectada pelo `polish_validator`\nExemplos:\n- palavras comidas\n- adições indevidas\n- meaning drift\n- polish piorou demais o texto\n\n## O que fazer\n### Retry do batch específico\nIsto é ainda mais claramente batchável do que o screenplay.\n\nPorque:\n- polish já está por grupos pequenos de cenas\n- o problema tende a estar localizado\n\n---\n\n# 4. Falhas de merge\nEstas são importantes e às vezes esquecidas.\n\n---\n\n## 4A. Falha no `screenplay_merger`\nExemplos:\n- falta um batch file\n- batches fora de ordem\n- IDs duplicados\n- uma cena veio inválida e foi descartada\n- scene_count final estranho\n\n## O que fazer\n### Não retryar o merger por si só de forma cega\n\nPrimeiro precisa diagnosticar:\n- o problema é no merger?\n- ou no output dos batches?\n\n### Em geral\nO retry deve voltar para:\n- batch(es) problemáticos\nnão\n- reexecutar merger infinitamente\n\n---\n\n## 4B. Falha no `tts_polish_merger`\nExemplos:\n- batch faltando\n- `scene_id` sem polish correspondente\n- duplicatas\n- ordem quebrada\n\n## O que fazer\nMesma lógica:\n### retry do batch problemático\nnão retry cego do merger\n\n---\n\n# 5. Falhas do `scene_bible_builder`\nExemplos:\n- `scene_bible.json` não escrito\n- shape errado\n- campos reservados ausentes\n- schema inválido\n\n## O que fazer\nAqui depende do tipo de falha.\n\n### Se for falha estrutural do builder\n- retry do step `scene_bible_builder`\n\n### Se for falha causada por input inconsistente\n- talvez voltar antes\n\nMas em v1:\n### retry do step do builder faz sentido\n\n---\n\n# 6. Falhas de infraestrutura\nEssas são diferentes das semânticas.\n\n## Exemplos\n- filesystem permission error\n- path inexistente\n- write falhou\n- disco cheio\n- input file corrompido\n\n## O que fazer\n### normalmente não retryar cego muitas vezes\n\nTalvez:\n- 1 retry curto\n- se repetir, falha explícita\n\nPorque isso tende a não ser erro “regenerável” por LLM.\n\n---\n\n# 7. Então o `retry_planner` deve basicamente distinguir:\n\n## Tipo A — falha estrutural de preflight\n### ação:\n**abort**\n\n---\n\n## Tipo B — falha operacional/transitória de operator\n### ação:\n**retry batch**\n\n---\n\n## Tipo C — falha semântica localizada\n### ação:\n**retry batch ou subset**\n\n---\n\n## Tipo D — falha semântica difusa/global\n### ação:\n**retry do step inteiro**\nou\n**fail**, se já repetiu demais\n\n---\n\n## Tipo E — falha de infra\n### ação:\n**1 retry curto ou fail-fast**\n\n---\n\n# 8. Política v1 que eu recomendaria\nPara não complicar demais logo de cara:\n\n## `s1_preflight_checker`\n- sem retry\n- fail direto\n\n## `scene_director`\n- retry por batch até 3x\n\n## `screenplay_validator`\n- se falhar:\n  - retry step/batches até 3x\n  - depois fail\n\n## `tts_polish`\n- retry por batch até 3x\n\n## `polish_validator`\n- se falhar:\n  - retry batches afectados até 3x\n  - depois fail\n\n## `scene_bible_builder`\n- retry do step até 2–3x\n- depois fail\n\n---\n\n# 9. O que o `retry_planner` precisa receber\nPara decidir, ele deve receber algo como:\n\n- `step_name`\n- `failure_type`\n- `validation_result`\n- `retry_count`\n- `batch_manifest`\n- `affected_batches` ou `affected_scenes`, se houver\n\n---\n\n# 10. O que ele deve devolver\nAlgo nesta linha:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"retry\": true,\n  \"retry_mode\": \"batch_subset\",\n  \"targets\": [\"tp_003\", \"tp_004\"],\n  \"reason\": \"polish validation failed for scenes in these batches\",\n  \"next_action\": \"rerun_tts_polish_batches\"\n}\n```\n\nou\n\n```json\n{\n  \"retry\": false,\n  \"retry_mode\": \"abort\",\n  \"targets\": [],\n  \"reason\": \"preflight structural failure\",\n  \"next_action\": \"fail_sector\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n# 11. Em uma frase\nO `retry_planner` existe para responder:\n\n## **“esta falha deve abortar, repetir o step inteiro, ou repetir só parte dele?”**\n\n---\n\n# 12. Minha conclusão\nEntão as falhas que importam para ele são principalmente:\n\n### no `scene_director`\n- timeout / no output / malformed output / semantic coverage fail\n\n### no `tts_polish`\n- timeout / no output / malformed output / semantic polish fail\n\n### nos mergers\n- batch faltando / output inconsistente\n\n### no builder\n- scene bible inválida\n\n### e ele deve transformar isso em:\n- abort\n- retry step\n- retry specific batches\n\n---\n\nSe quiseres, agora faz total sentido eu criar o `retry_planner` já com esta lógica v1.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0047bd771936d8e20169caefdbba788195a7dc98a56846d384\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":167,"output":1843,"cacheRead":180608,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":182618,"cost":{"input":0.0004175,"output":0.027645,"cacheRead":0.045152,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0732145}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774907349025,"responseId":"resp_0047bd771936d8e20169caefd9daa481959ee02541bffa38f5"}}
{"type":"message","id":"2e76393d","parentId":"a6e686b3","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:51:51.528Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Mon 2026-03-30 18:51 GMT-3] fechou concordo com a lógica sim pode criar"}],"timestamp":1774907511445}}
{"type":"message","id":"0229556c","parentId":"2e76393d","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:51:57.446Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Vou criar o `retry_planner` com essa lógica v1 que alinhámos: distinguir fail-fast estrutural, retry por batch/step e abortar quando exceder limites.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0047bd771936d8e20169caf07b7bc881959fdb7a8cf6cb3522\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_2iOPQ7Pb51MUwNgtcQMBMsPZ|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caf07e55d88195b3e87f19707e66bf","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1_supervisor_contract.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1_supervisor_contract.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_FFFnS7l8wIG0NwJkHyDXgNLY|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caf07e58088195bf5e3cdb06bbb994","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\tts_polish_merger.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\supervisor_skills\\\\tts_polish_merger.py\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":158,"output":149,"cacheRead":182528,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":182835,"cost":{"input":0.000395,"output":0.002235,"cacheRead":0.045632,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.048262}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774907512515,"responseId":"resp_0047bd771936d8e20169caf07a2d508195873627b07012af85"}}
{"type":"message","id":"b53d366e","parentId":"0229556c","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:51:58.137Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_2iOPQ7Pb51MUwNgtcQMBMsPZ|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caf07e55d88195b3e87f19707e66bf","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# S1 Supervisor Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the role, boundaries, and first deterministic skill of the S1 (Pre-Production) Supervisor._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-30_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe S1 Supervisor is the supervisory layer for Pre-Production.\n\nIts job is to take a run that is `ready_for_s1` and coordinate the sector until it produces:\n- `screenplay.json`\n- `screenplay_validation.json`\n- `tts_polished.json`\n- `polish_validation.json`\n- `scene_bible.json`\n- `b1_*` checkpoints\n\nThe supervisor is an **OpenClaw LLM supervisor**, not a purely conversational helper and not a monolithic Python script that absorbs all work itself.\n\nIt should supervise using:\n- deterministic Python skills\n- specialized operators/sub-agents\n- explicit file contracts\n\n---\n\n## Core principle\n\n### Supervisor = brain\n### Skills = hands\n### Operators = specialists\n\nThe S1 Supervisor should:\n- decide the order of operations\n- decide when to call an operator vs a deterministic skill\n- interpret validation results\n- decide retry / fail / continue\n- write or trigger checkpoints\n\nThe S1 Supervisor should **not** directly absorb:\n- semantic scene generation\n- TTS polish generation\n- low-level file/path mechanics\n- deterministic validation logic\n- JSON merge/reindex mechanics\n\nThose belong to:\n- S1 operators (`scene_director`, `tts_polish`)\n- deterministic supervisor skills\n\n---\n\n## Current operator model\n\nThe current intended operator structure for S1 is:\n- `scene_director` -> OpenClaw operator\n- `tts_polish` -> OpenClaw operator\n\nThese operators communicate with the supervisor via explicit file contracts:\n- supervisor prepares input payload/file\n- operator reads input\n- operator writes output file\n- supervisor validates and decides next step\n\n---\n\n## Current deterministic skills owned by the supervisor\n\n### Implemented now\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n\n### Expected next skills\n- `retry_planner`\n- `checkpoint_writer`\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\n\nThis list may evolve, but the supervisor should remain supervisory rather than mechanically overloaded.\n\n---\n\n## File contract principle\n\nThe supervisor must operate on persisted run artifacts.\n\nMinimum expected inputs before S1 begins:\n- `job.json`\n- `run_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_raw.txt`\n- `inputs/script/script_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_lock.json`\n- `checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json`\n\nMinimum expected outputs after S1 completes:\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay_validation.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/polish_validation.json`\n- `scene_bible.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step1_screenplay.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step2_screenplay_validated.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step3_tts_polished.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step4_polish_validated.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step5_scene_bible.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_complete.json`\n\n---\n\n## First implemented supervisor skill: `s1_preflight_checker`\n\n### Purpose\nValidate that a run is structurally ready to enter S1 before any operator or semantic step is invoked.\n\n### Scope\nChecks:\n- run root exists\n- required input files exist\n- `job.json` is readable and contains `job_id`, `account`, `language`\n- channel config exists at `accounts/{account}/{language}.yaml`\n- `script_raw.txt` is readable and not empty\n- `vo_script_ready` checkpoint exists\n- run state is minimally compatible with entering S1\n\n### Out of scope\n`s1_preflight_checker` does **not**:\n- create sector outputs\n- call operators\n- validate screenplay semantics\n- decide batching\n- modify the run\n\n### Input shape\n```json\n{\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\"\n}\n```\n\n### Output shape\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"job\": {\n    \"job_id\": \"2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n    \"account\": \"004\",\n    \"language\": \"fr\"\n  },\n  \"paths\": {\n    \"job_json\": \".../job.json\",\n    \"run_metadata\": \".../run_metadata.json\",\n    \"script_raw\": \".../inputs/script/script_raw.txt\",\n    \"script_metadata\": \".../inputs/script/script_metadata.json\",\n    \"script_lock\": \".../inputs/script/script_lock.json\",\n    \"vo_script_ready_checkpoint\": \".../checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json\",\n    \"channel_config\": \".../accounts/004/fr.yaml\"\n  },\n  \"script_stats\": {\n    \"char_count\": 0,\n    \"word_count\": 0\n  },\n  \"errors\": [],\n  \"warnings\": []\n}\n```\n\n### Error policy\nThe skill should collect all relevant failures and return them together.\nIt should not stop at the first missing file.\n\n### Warning policy\nExamples of warning-worthy but non-fatal conditions:\n- script very short\n- script very long\n- `b1_pre_production/` already exists but `b1_complete.json` does not\n\n### Fatal examples\n- missing `job.json`\n- missing `script_raw.txt`\n- unreadable or invalid `job.json`\n- missing channel config\n- missing `vo_script_ready.json`\n- empty script\n\n---\n\n## Naming convention\nThe canonical checkpoint and sector naming for Pre-Production is:\n- `b1_pre_production/`\n- `b1_*` checkpoints\n\nThe older `s1_*` naming should not be treated as canonical.\n\n---\n\n## Second implemented supervisor skill: `s1_paths_resolver`\n\n### Purpose\nResolve and centralize the canonical S1 paths for the run.\n\n### Scope\nResolves and optionally creates the directory structure for:\n- `b1_pre_production/`\n- `b1_pre_production/inputs/`\n- `b1_pre_production/intermediate/`\n- `inputs/scene_director/`\n- `inputs/tts_polish/`\n- `intermediate/scene_director/`\n- `intermediate/tts_polish/`\n- canonical output file paths\n- canonical `b1_*` checkpoint file paths\n\n### Out of scope\n`s1_paths_resolver` does **not**:\n- validate semantic readiness\n- call operators\n- inspect screenplay or polish content\n- perform batching\n\n### Input shape\n```json\n{\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"create_dirs\": true\n}\n```\n\n### Output shape\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"created_dirs\": true,\n  \"paths\": {\n    \"b1_root\": \".../b1_pre_production\",\n    \"inputs_root\": \".../b1_pre_production/inputs\",\n    \"intermediate_root\": \".../b1_pre_production/intermediate\",\n    \"screenplay_path\": \".../b1_pre_production/screenplay.json\",\n    \"tts_polished_path\": \".../b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json\",\n    \"scene_bible_path\": \".../scene_bible.json\",\n    \"b1_complete_checkpoint\": \".../checkpoints/b1_complete.json\"\n  },\n  \"errors\": [],\n  \"warnings\": []\n}\n```\n\n## Third implemented supervisor skill: `script_batch_planner`\n\n### Purpose\nSplit the raw script into manageable work batches for `scene_director` without turning the supervisor into a monolithic batching script.\n\n### Scope\n- receives raw script text or script file path\n- plans batches using target/min/max word budgets\n- prefers paragraph boundaries\n- falls back to sentence-based splitting for oversized paragraphs\n- preserves order and emits a stable `sd_###` batch sequence\n\n### Out of scope\n`script_batch_planner` does **not**:\n- divide the script into final scenes\n- call `scene_director`\n- perform semantic validation\n- merge operator outputs\n\n### Recommended v1 defaults\n- target words per batch: `750`\n- minimum words per batch: `450`\n- maximum words per batch: `950`\n\n### Output shape\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"total_words\": 3520,\n  \"batch_count\": 5,\n  \"target_words_per_batch\": 750,\n  \"min_words_per_batch\": 450,\n  \"max_words_per_batch\": 950,\n  \"batches\": [\n    {\n      \"batch_id\": \"sd_001\",\n      \"start_word\": 1,\n      \"end_word\": 742,\n      \"word_count\": 742,\n      \"text\": \"...\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"errors\": [],\n  \"warnings\": []\n}\n```\n\n## Fourth implemented supervisor skill: `scene_director_io_adapter`\n\n### Purpose\nPrepare the explicit input/output contract between the S1 Supervisor and the `scene_director` operator for each planned script batch.\n\n### Scope\n- receives run/job context\n- receives one script batch from `script_batch_planner`\n- injects `scene_words_range` from channel config\n- writes a deterministic payload file for the operator\n- declares the expected output path for the batch result\n\n### Out of scope\n`scene_director_io_adapter` does **not**:\n- run the operator\n- validate semantic quality\n- merge batch outputs\n- choose retry policy\n\n### Output contract principle\nEach batch payload should explicitly tell `scene_director`:\n- who the run/job is\n- what the batch text is\n- what scene structure is expected\n- where to write the result\n\n## Fifth implemented supervisor skill: `screenplay_merger`\n\n### Purpose\nMerge the batch outputs of `scene_director` into one canonical `screenplay.json` without forcing the supervisor itself to concatenate, validate, and reindex scene objects manually.\n\n### Scope\n- loads ordered batch output files\n- validates minimum required scene fields\n- concatenates scenes in batch order\n- reassigns canonical `scene_###` IDs globally\n- writes `screenplay.json`\n\n### Out of scope\n`screenplay_merger` does **not**:\n- perform semantic validation\n- decide retry policy\n- invoke operators\n- polish TTS text\n\n### Output contract principle\nThe merged screenplay should preserve order while normalizing scene IDs into one canonical sequence for the rest of S1.\n\n## Sixth implemented supervisor skill: `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n\n### Purpose\nPlan small, stable polish batches from the merged screenplay so that `tts_polish` receives manageable groups of scenes instead of the full screenplay at once.\n\n### Scope\n- receives `screenplay.json`\n- groups scenes by count and approximate word budget\n- preserves scene order\n- emits a stable `tp_###` batch sequence\n\n### Recommended v1 defaults\n- target scenes per batch: `5`\n- minimum scenes per batch: `3`\n- maximum scenes per batch: `6`\n- maximum words per batch: `350`\n\n### Out of scope\n`tts_polish_batch_planner` does **not**:\n- perform TTS polish\n- validate semantic quality\n- merge polish outputs\n- decide retry policy\n\n## Seventh implemented supervisor skill: `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n\n### Purpose\nPrepare the explicit input/output contract between the S1 Supervisor and the `tts_polish` operator for each planned polish batch.\n\n### Scope\n- receives run/job context\n- receives merged screenplay\n- receives one polish batch from `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- injects `tts_polish_rules` from channel config\n- writes a deterministic payload file for the operator\n- declares the expected output path for the batch result\n\n### Out of scope\n`tts_polish_io_adapter` does **not**:\n- run the operator\n- validate semantic quality\n- merge polish outputs\n- choose retry policy\n\n### Output contract principle\nEach polish batch payload should explicitly tell `tts_polish`:\n- which scenes belong to the batch\n- what the original narration is\n- what rules govern polish behavior\n- where to write the result\n\n## Eighth implemented supervisor skill: `tts_polish_merger`\n\n### Purpose\nMerge the batch outputs of `tts_polish` into one canonical `tts_polished.json` while preserving screenplay order and preserving the distinction between original narration and TTS-polished narration.\n\n### Scope\n- loads ordered polish batch files\n- validates minimum required polish scene fields\n- rebuilds one ordered `tts_polished.json`\n- uses screenplay order as the canonical scene sequence\n\n### Out of scope\n`tts_polish_merger` does **not**:\n- validate semantic quality of the polish\n- decide retry policy\n- invoke operators\n- overwrite the original screenplay artifact\n\n### Output contract principle\nThe merged polish output should preserve:\n- `scene_id`\n- `narration_original`\n- `narration_tts`\n\nwithout destroying the original screenplay layer.\n\n## Current status summary\nAt this stage:\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\n- deterministic helper skills are being formalized\n- `s1_preflight_checker` is implemented as the entry gate for the sector\n- `s1_paths_resolver` is implemented as the canonical path/structure resolver for the sector\n- `script_batch_planner` is implemented as the first batching/planning skill for the sector\n- `scene_director_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `scene_director` operator\n- `screenplay_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch screenplay outputs\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner` is implemented as the batching/planning layer for `tts_polish`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `tts_polish` operator\n- `tts_polish_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch polish outputs\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774907518014}}
{"type":"message","id":"79ebf3ee","parentId":"b53d366e","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:51:58.292Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_FFFnS7l8wIG0NwJkHyDXgNLY|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caf07e58088195bf5e3cdb06bbb994","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\nREQUIRED_POLISH_FIELDS = {\n    \"scene_id\",\n    \"narration_original\",\n    \"narration_tts\",\n}\n\n\ndef merge_tts_polish_batches(\n    batch_files: list[str | Path],\n    *,\n    screenplay: dict[str, Any],\n    output_path: str | Path | None = None,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    errors: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n    warnings: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n    ordered_files = sorted([Path(p) for p in batch_files], key=lambda p: p.name)\n\n    scenes = screenplay.get(\"scenes\", []) if isinstance(screenplay, dict) else []\n    ordered_scene_ids = [scene.get(\"scene_id\") for scene in scenes if isinstance(scene, dict) and scene.get(\"scene_id\")]\n\n    if not ordered_files:\n        return {\n            \"ok\": False,\n            \"scene_count\": 0,\n            \"tts_polished\": {\"scenes\": []},\n            \"errors\": [{\"code\": \"no_batch_files\", \"message\": \"No tts_polish batch files provided\"}],\n            \"warnings\": [],\n        }\n\n    polish_map: dict[str, dict[str, Any]] = {}\n    loaded_batches: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n\n    for file_path in ordered_files:\n        if not file_path.exists():\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"missing_batch_file\",\n                \"message\": f\"Polish batch file not found: {file_path}\",\n            })\n            continue\n\n        try:\n            payload = json.loads(file_path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\n        except Exception as exc:  # noqa: BLE001\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"invalid_batch_json\",\n                \"message\": f\"Failed to parse polish batch file {file_path}: {exc}\",\n            })\n            continue\n\n        batch_id = payload.get(\"batch_id\")\n        batch_scenes = payload.get(\"scenes\", [])\n        if not isinstance(batch_scenes, list):\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"invalid_batch_scenes\",\n                \"message\": f\"Polish batch file {file_path} has invalid 'scenes' payload\",\n            })\n            continue\n\n        if not batch_scenes:\n            warnings.append({\n                \"code\": \"empty_polish_batch\",\n                \"message\": f\"Polish batch file {file_path} produced zero scenes\",\n            })\n\n        loaded_batches.append(\n            {\n                \"batch_id\": batch_id,\n                \"file_path\": str(file_path),\n                \"scene_count\": len(batch_scenes),\n            }\n        )\n\n        for scene in batch_scenes:\n            if not isinstance(scene, dict):\n                errors.append({\n                    \"code\": \"invalid_scene_payload\",\n                    \"message\": f\"Polish batch {batch_id or file_path.name} contains a non-object scene entry\",\n                })\n                continue\n\n            missing_fields = sorted(REQUIRED_POLISH_FIELDS - set(scene.keys()))\n            if missing_fields:\n                errors.append({\n                    \"code\": \"missing_polish_fields\",\n                    \"message\": (\n                        f\"Polish batch {batch_id or file_path.name} scene is missing required fields: \"\n                        f\"{', '.join(missing_fields)}\"\n                    ),\n                })\n                continue\n\n            scene_id = scene.get(\"scene_id\")\n            if scene_id in polish_map:\n                warnings.append({\n                    \"code\": \"duplicate_scene_polish\",\n                    \"message\": f\"Scene {scene_id} appeared more than once across polish batches; latest entry kept\",\n                })\n            polish_map[scene_id] = scene\n\n    merged_scenes: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n    for scene_id in ordered_scene_ids:\n        polished_scene = polish_map.get(scene_id)\n        if not polished_scene:\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"missing_polish_scene\",\n                \"message\": f\"No polish output found for screenplay scene {scene_id}\",\n            })\n            continue\n        merged_scenes.append(polished_scene)\n\n    tts_polished = {\n        \"scene_count\": len(merged_scenes),\n        \"scenes\": merged_scenes,\n    }\n\n    if output_path is not None:\n        output_path = Path(output_path)\n        output_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n        output_path.write_text(json.dumps(tts_polished, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n    return {\n        \"ok\": len(errors) == 0,\n        \"scene_count\": len(merged_scenes),\n        \"batch_count\": len(loaded_batches),\n        \"tts_polished\": tts_polished,\n        \"loaded_batches\": loaded_batches,\n        \"output_path\": str(output_path) if output_path is not None else None,\n        \"errors\": errors,\n        \"warnings\": warnings,\n    }\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774907518138}}
{"type":"message","id":"7ba85273","parentId":"79ebf3ee","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:52:45.955Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_0cG4B3MGecQnmoF6eTELiYQS|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caf0aed5908195b5968a027c4238d1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\retry_planner.py","content":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\nMAX_RETRIES_DEFAULT = 3\n\n\nFAIL_FAST_TYPES = {\n    \"preflight_structural_failure\",\n    \"missing_required_input\",\n    \"invalid_job_json\",\n    \"invalid_pipeline_state\",\n    \"empty_script\",\n    \"b1_already_complete\",\n}\n\nOPERATOR_RETRYABLE_TYPES = {\n    \"operator_timeout\",\n    \"operator_no_output\",\n    \"operator_output_missing\",\n    \"operator_invalid_json\",\n    \"operator_empty_output\",\n    \"operator_malformed_output\",\n}\n\nMERGE_RECOVERY_TYPES = {\n    \"missing_batch_file\",\n    \"invalid_batch_json\",\n    \"invalid_batch_scenes\",\n    \"missing_scene_fields\",\n    \"missing_polish_fields\",\n    \"missing_polish_scene\",\n}\n\nSEMANTIC_SCREENPLAY_TYPES = {\n    \"screenplay_validation_failed\",\n    \"coverage_too_low\",\n    \"missing_words_detected\",\n    \"extra_words_detected\",\n    \"duplicate_scene_content\",\n}\n\nSEMANTIC_POLISH_TYPES = {\n    \"polish_validation_failed\",\n    \"words_eaten\",\n    \"meaning_drift\",\n    \"unauthorized_additions\",\n}\n\nBUILDER_RETRYABLE_TYPES = {\n    \"scene_bible_write_failed\",\n    \"scene_bible_schema_invalid\",\n    \"scene_bible_builder_failed\",\n}\n\nINFRA_FAILURE_TYPES = {\n    \"filesystem_write_error\",\n    \"permission_error\",\n    \"disk_full\",\n}\n\n\ndef plan_retry(\n    *,\n    step_name: str,\n    failure_type: str,\n    retry_count: int,\n    affected_batches: list[str] | None = None,\n    affected_scenes: list[str] | None = None,\n    max_retries: int = MAX_RETRIES_DEFAULT,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    affected_batches = affected_batches or []\n    affected_scenes = affected_scenes or []\n\n    if retry_count >= max_retries:\n        return _decision(\n            retry=False,\n            retry_mode=\"abort\",\n            targets=[],\n            reason=f\"Retry limit reached for step '{step_name}' ({retry_count}/{max_retries})\",\n            next_action=\"fail_sector\",\n        )\n\n    if failure_type in FAIL_FAST_TYPES:\n        return _decision(\n            retry=False,\n            retry_mode=\"abort\",\n            targets=[],\n            reason=f\"Structural failure '{failure_type}' should fail fast\",\n            next_action=\"fail_sector\",\n        )\n\n    if failure_type in OPERATOR_RETRYABLE_TYPES:\n        if affected_batches:\n            return _decision(\n                retry=True,\n                retry_mode=\"batch_subset\",\n                targets=affected_batches,\n                reason=f\"Operator execution failure '{failure_type}' — rerun affected batches\",\n                next_action=f\"rerun_{step_name}_batches\",\n            )\n        return _decision(\n            retry=True,\n            retry_mode=\"step\",\n            targets=[step_name],\n            reason=f\"Operator execution failure '{failure_type}' — rerun step\",\n            next_action=f\"rerun_{step_name}\",\n        )\n\n    if failure_type in MERGE_RECOVERY_TYPES:\n        if affected_batches:\n            return _decision(\n                retry=True,\n                retry_mode=\"batch_subset\",\n                targets=affected_batches,\n                reason=f\"Merge issue '{failure_type}' traced to missing/invalid batch outputs\",\n                next_action=\"rerun_affected_batches_then_merge\",\n            )\n        return _decision(\n            retry=False,\n            retry_mode=\"abort\",\n            targets=[],\n            reason=f\"Merge failure '{failure_type}' cannot be safely retried without affected batch mapping\",\n            next_action=\"fail_sector\",\n        )\n\n    if failure_type in SEMANTIC_SCREENPLAY_TYPES:\n        if affected_batches:\n            return _decision(\n                retry=True,\n                retry_mode=\"batch_subset\",\n                targets=affected_batches,\n                reason=f\"Screenplay semantic failure '{failure_type}' — rerun affected screenplay batches\",\n                next_action=\"rerun_scene_director_batches\",\n            )\n        return _decision(\n            retry=True,\n            retry_mode=\"step\",\n            targets=[\"scene_director\"],\n            reason=f\"Screenplay semantic failure '{failure_type}' — rerun screenplay step\",\n            next_action=\"rerun_scene_director_step\",\n        )\n\n    if failure_type in SEMANTIC_POLISH_TYPES:\n        if affected_batches:\n            return _decision(\n                retry=True,\n                retry_mode=\"batch_subset\",\n                targets=affected_batches,\n                reason=f\"Polish semantic failure '{failure_type}' — rerun affected polish batches\",\n                next_action=\"rerun_tts_polish_batches\",\n            )\n        return _decision(\n            retry=True,\n            retry_mode=\"step\",\n            targets=[\"tts_polish\"],\n            reason=f\"Polish semantic failure '{failure_type}' — rerun TTS polish step\",\n            next_action=\"rerun_tts_polish_step\",\n        )\n\n    if failure_type in BUILDER_RETRYABLE_TYPES:\n        return _decision(\n            retry=True,\n            retry_mode=\"step\",\n            targets=[\"scene_bible_builder\"],\n            reason=f\"Scene bible build failure '{failure_type}' — rerun builder step\",\n            next_action=\"rerun_scene_bible_builder\",\n        )\n\n    if failure_type in INFRA_FAILURE_TYPES:\n        return _decision(\n            retry=True,\n            retry_mode=\"step\",\n            targets=[step_name],\n            reason=f\"Infrastructure failure '{failure_type}' — allow one more controlled retry\",\n            next_action=f\"rerun_{step_name}\",\n        )\n\n    return _decision(\n        retry=False,\n        retry_mode=\"abort\",\n        targets=[],\n        reason=f\"Unknown failure type '{failure_type}' — abort by default for safety\",\n        next_action=\"fail_sector\",\n    )\n\n\ndef _decision(\n    *,\n    retry: bool,\n    retry_mode: str,\n    targets: list[str],\n    reason: str,\n    next_action: str,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    return {\n        \"retry\": retry,\n        \"retry_mode\": retry_mode,\n        \"targets\": targets,\n        \"reason\": reason,\n        \"next_action\": next_action,\n    }\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\supervisor_skills\\\\retry_planner.py\",\"content\":\"from __future__ import annotations\\n\\nfrom typing import Any\\n\\n\\nMAX_RETRIES_DEFAULT = 3\\n\\n\\nFAIL_FAST_TYPES = {\\n    \\\"preflight_structural_failure\\\",\\n    \\\"missing_required_input\\\",\\n    \\\"invalid_job_json\\\",\\n    \\\"invalid_pipeline_state\\\",\\n    \\\"empty_script\\\",\\n    \\\"b1_already_complete\\\",\\n}\\n\\nOPERATOR_RETRYABLE_TYPES = {\\n    \\\"operator_timeout\\\",\\n    \\\"operator_no_output\\\",\\n    \\\"operator_output_missing\\\",\\n    \\\"operator_invalid_json\\\",\\n    \\\"operator_empty_output\\\",\\n    \\\"operator_malformed_output\\\",\\n}\\n\\nMERGE_RECOVERY_TYPES = {\\n    \\\"missing_batch_file\\\",\\n    \\\"invalid_batch_json\\\",\\n    \\\"invalid_batch_scenes\\\",\\n    \\\"missing_scene_fields\\\",\\n    \\\"missing_polish_fields\\\",\\n    \\\"missing_polish_scene\\\",\\n}\\n\\nSEMANTIC_SCREENPLAY_TYPES = {\\n    \\\"screenplay_validation_failed\\\",\\n    \\\"coverage_too_low\\\",\\n    \\\"missing_words_detected\\\",\\n    \\\"extra_words_detected\\\",\\n    \\\"duplicate_scene_content\\\",\\n}\\n\\nSEMANTIC_POLISH_TYPES = {\\n    \\\"polish_validation_failed\\\",\\n    \\\"words_eaten\\\",\\n    \\\"meaning_drift\\\",\\n    \\\"unauthorized_additions\\\",\\n}\\n\\nBUILDER_RETRYABLE_TYPES = {\\n    \\\"scene_bible_write_failed\\\",\\n    \\\"scene_bible_schema_invalid\\\",\\n    \\\"scene_bible_builder_failed\\\",\\n}\\n\\nINFRA_FAILURE_TYPES = {\\n    \\\"filesystem_write_error\\\",\\n    \\\"permission_error\\\",\\n    \\\"disk_full\\\",\\n}\\n\\n\\ndef plan_retry(\\n    *,\\n    step_name: str,\\n    failure_type: str,\\n    retry_count: int,\\n    affected_batches: list[str] | None = None,\\n    affected_scenes: list[str] | None = None,\\n    max_retries: int = MAX_RETRIES_DEFAULT,\\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\\n    affected_batches = affected_batches or []\\n    affected_scenes = affected_scenes or []\\n\\n    if retry_count >= max_retries:\\n        return _decision(\\n            retry=False,\\n            retry_mode=\\\"abort\\\",\\n            targets=[],\\n            reason=f\\\"Retry limit reached for step '{step_name}' ({retry_count}/{max_retries})\\\",\\n            next_action=\\\"fail_sector\\\",\\n        )\\n\\n    if failure_type in FAIL_FAST_TYPES:\\n        return _decision(\\n            retry=False,\\n            retry_mode=\\\"abort\\\",\\n            targets=[],\\n            reason=f\\\"Structural failure '{failure_type}' should fail fast\\\",\\n            next_action=\\\"fail_sector\\\",\\n        )\\n\\n    if failure_type in OPERATOR_RETRYABLE_TYPES:\\n        if affected_batches:\\n            return _decision(\\n                retry=True,\\n                retry_mode=\\\"batch_subset\\\",\\n                targets=affected_batches,\\n                reason=f\\\"Operator execution failure '{failure_type}' — rerun affected batches\\\",\\n                next_action=f\\\"rerun_{step_name}_batches\\\",\\n            )\\n        return _decision(\\n            retry=True,\\n            retry_mode=\\\"step\\\",\\n            targets=[step_name],\\n            reason=f\\\"Operator execution failure '{failure_type}' — rerun step\\\",\\n            next_action=f\\\"rerun_{step_name}\\\",\\n        )\\n\\n    if failure_type in MERGE_RECOVERY_TYPES:\\n        if affected_batches:\\n            return _decision(\\n                retry=True,\\n                retry_mode=\\\"batch_subset\\\",\\n                targets=affected_batches,\\n                reason=f\\\"Merge issue '{failure_type}' traced to missing/invalid batch outputs\\\",\\n                next_action=\\\"rerun_affected_batches_then_merge\\\",\\n            )\\n        return _decision(\\n            retry=False,\\n            retry_mode=\\\"abort\\\",\\n            targets=[],\\n            reason=f\\\"Merge failure '{failure_type}' cannot be safely retried without affected batch mapping\\\",\\n            next_action=\\\"fail_sector\\\",\\n        )\\n\\n    if failure_type in SEMANTIC_SCREENPLAY_TYPES:\\n        if affected_batches:\\n            return _decision(\\n                retry=True,\\n                retry_mode=\\\"batch_subset\\\",\\n                targets=affected_batches,\\n                reason=f\\\"Screenplay semantic failure '{failure_type}' — rerun affected screenplay batches\\\",\\n                next_action=\\\"rerun_scene_director_batches\\\",\\n            )\\n        return _decision(\\n            retry=True,\\n            retry_mode=\\\"step\\\",\\n            targets=[\\\"scene_director\\\"],\\n            reason=f\\\"Screenplay semantic failure '{failure_type}' — rerun screenplay step\\\",\\n            next_action=\\\"rerun_scene_director_step\\\",\\n        )\\n\\n    if failure_type in SEMANTIC_POLISH_TYPES:\\n        if affected_batches:\\n            return _decision(\\n                retry=True,\\n                retry_mode=\\\"batch_subset\\\",\\n                targets=affected_batches,\\n                reason=f\\\"Polish semantic failure '{failure_type}' — rerun affected polish batches\\\",\\n                next_action=\\\"rerun_tts_polish_batches\\\",\\n            )\\n        return _decision(\\n            retry=True,\\n            retry_mode=\\\"step\\\",\\n            targets=[\\\"tts_polish\\\"],\\n            reason=f\\\"Polish semantic failure '{failure_type}' — rerun TTS polish step\\\",\\n            next_action=\\\"rerun_tts_polish_step\\\",\\n        )\\n\\n    if failure_type in BUILDER_RETRYABLE_TYPES:\\n        return _decision(\\n            retry=True,\\n            retry_mode=\\\"step\\\",\\n            targets=[\\\"scene_bible_builder\\\"],\\n            reason=f\\\"Scene bible build failure '{failure_type}' — rerun builder step\\\",\\n            next_action=\\\"rerun_scene_bible_builder\\\",\\n        )\\n\\n    if failure_type in INFRA_FAILURE_TYPES:\\n        return _decision(\\n            retry=True,\\n            retry_mode=\\\"step\\\",\\n            targets=[step_name],\\n            reason=f\\\"Infrastructure failure '{failure_type}' — allow one more controlled retry\\\",\\n            next_action=f\\\"rerun_{step_name}\\\",\\n        )\\n\\n    return _decision(\\n        retry=False,\\n        retry_mode=\\\"abort\\\",\\n        targets=[],\\n        reason=f\\\"Unknown failure type '{failure_type}' — abort by default for safety\\\",\\n        next_action=\\\"fail_sector\\\",\\n    )\\n\\n\\ndef _decision(\\n    *,\\n    retry: bool,\\n    retry_mode: str,\\n    targets: list[str],\\n    reason: str,\\n    next_action: str,\\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\\n    return {\\n        \\\"retry\\\": retry,\\n        \\\"retry_mode\\\": retry_mode,\\n        \\\"targets\\\": targets,\\n        \\\"reason\\\": reason,\\n        \\\"next_action\\\": next_action,\\n    }\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_lPLfgET1TshzQVr828C486qu|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caf0aed59c819594a4c9dcdb485911","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1_supervisor_contract.md","oldText":"### Implemented now\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n","newText":"### Implemented now\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n- `retry_planner`\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1_supervisor_contract.md\",\"oldText\":\"### Implemented now\\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\\n- `script_batch_planner`\\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\\n- `screenplay_merger`\\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\\n- `tts_polish_merger`\\n\",\"newText\":\"### Implemented now\\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\\n- `script_batch_planner`\\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\\n- `screenplay_merger`\\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\\n- `tts_polish_merger`\\n- `retry_planner`\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_2EusQZ0cG67S7nkhyszInYl1|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caf0aed5a48195835bcf8d9a126b84","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1_supervisor_contract.md","oldText":"### Expected next skills\n- `retry_planner`\n- `checkpoint_writer`\n","newText":"### Expected next skills\n- `checkpoint_writer`\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1_supervisor_contract.md\",\"oldText\":\"### Expected next skills\\n- `retry_planner`\\n- `checkpoint_writer`\\n\",\"newText\":\"### Expected next skills\\n- `checkpoint_writer`\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_O7wgohfDCbiPnm3AWODIxsBX|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caf0aed5ac8195a301d26334aedf2a","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1_supervisor_contract.md","oldText":"## Current status summary\nAt this stage:\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\n- deterministic helper skills are being formalized\n- `s1_preflight_checker` is implemented as the entry gate for the sector\n- `s1_paths_resolver` is implemented as the canonical path/structure resolver for the sector\n- `script_batch_planner` is implemented as the first batching/planning skill for the sector\n- `scene_director_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `scene_director` operator\n- `screenplay_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch screenplay outputs\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner` is implemented as the batching/planning layer for `tts_polish`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `tts_polish` operator\n- `tts_polish_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch polish outputs\n","newText":"## Ninth implemented supervisor skill: `retry_planner`\n\n### Purpose\nTurn observed failures into explicit retry decisions so the S1 Supervisor can decide whether to abort, rerun a whole step, or rerun only affected batches.\n\n### Scope\n- classifies failure types into retry strategies\n- enforces retry limits\n- supports fail-fast structural errors\n- supports batch-subset retries for localized operator/semantic failures\n- supports step-level retries when failures are broader\n\n### Out of scope\n`retry_planner` does **not**:\n- run retries itself\n- inspect semantic payloads deeply\n- invoke operators or validators\n- write checkpoints\n\n### Decision categories in v1\n- `abort`\n- `step`\n- `batch_subset`\n\n## Current status summary\nAt this stage:\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\n- deterministic helper skills are being formalized\n- `s1_preflight_checker` is implemented as the entry gate for the sector\n- `s1_paths_resolver` is implemented as the canonical path/structure resolver for the sector\n- `script_batch_planner` is implemented as the first batching/planning skill for the sector\n- `scene_director_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `scene_director` operator\n- `screenplay_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch screenplay outputs\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner` is implemented as the batching/planning layer for `tts_polish`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `tts_polish` operator\n- `tts_polish_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch polish outputs\n- `retry_planner` is implemented as the retry decision layer for the supervisor\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1_supervisor_contract.md\",\"oldText\":\"## Current status summary\\nAt this stage:\\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\\n- deterministic helper skills are being formalized\\n- `s1_preflight_checker` is implemented as the entry gate for the sector\\n- `s1_paths_resolver` is implemented as the canonical path/structure resolver for the sector\\n- `script_batch_planner` is implemented as the first batching/planning skill for the sector\\n- `scene_director_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `scene_director` operator\\n- `screenplay_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch screenplay outputs\\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner` is implemented as the batching/planning layer for `tts_polish`\\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `tts_polish` operator\\n- `tts_polish_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch polish outputs\\n\",\"newText\":\"## Ninth implemented supervisor skill: `retry_planner`\\n\\n### Purpose\\nTurn observed failures into explicit retry decisions so the S1 Supervisor can decide whether to abort, rerun a whole step, or rerun only affected batches.\\n\\n### Scope\\n- classifies failure types into retry strategies\\n- enforces retry limits\\n- supports fail-fast structural errors\\n- supports batch-subset retries for localized operator/semantic failures\\n- supports step-level retries when failures are broader\\n\\n### Out of scope\\n`retry_planner` does **not**:\\n- run retries itself\\n- inspect semantic payloads deeply\\n- invoke operators or validators\\n- write checkpoints\\n\\n### Decision categories in v1\\n- `abort`\\n- `step`\\n- `batch_subset`\\n\\n## Current status summary\\nAt this stage:\\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\\n- deterministic helper skills are being formalized\\n- `s1_preflight_checker` is implemented as the entry gate for the sector\\n- `s1_paths_resolver` is implemented as the canonical path/structure resolver for the sector\\n- `script_batch_planner` is implemented as the first batching/planning skill for the sector\\n- `scene_director_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `scene_director` operator\\n- `screenplay_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch screenplay outputs\\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner` is implemented as the batching/planning layer for `tts_polish`\\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `tts_polish` operator\\n- `tts_polish_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch polish outputs\\n- `retry_planner` is implemented as the retry decision layer for the supervisor\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":97136,"output":2463,"cacheRead":85504,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":185103,"cost":{"input":0.24284000000000003,"outpu