{"type":"message","id":"5cf8f679","parentId":"3eceab47","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:52:47.369Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_O7wgohfDCbiPnm3AWODIxsBX|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caf0aed5ac8195a301d26334aedf2a","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1_supervisor_contract.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 426 - `narration_tts`\n 427 \n 428 without destroying the original screenplay layer.\n 429 \n+430 ## Ninth implemented supervisor skill: `retry_planner`\n+431 \n+432 ### Purpose\n+433 Turn observed failures into explicit retry decisions so the S1 Supervisor can decide whether to abort, rerun a whole step, or rerun only affected batches.\n+434 \n+435 ### Scope\n+436 - classifies failure types into retry strategies\n+437 - enforces retry limits\n+438 - supports fail-fast structural errors\n+439 - supports batch-subset retries for localized operator/semantic failures\n+440 - supports step-level retries when failures are broader\n+441 \n+442 ### Out of scope\n+443 `retry_planner` does **not**:\n+444 - run retries itself\n+445 - inspect semantic payloads deeply\n+446 - invoke operators or validators\n+447 - write checkpoints\n+448 \n+449 ### Decision categories in v1\n+450 - `abort`\n+451 - `step`\n+452 - `batch_subset`\n+453 \n 430 ## Current status summary\n 431 At this stage:\n 432 - the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\n 433 - deterministic helper skills are being formalized\n     ...\n 438 - `screenplay_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch screenplay outputs\n 439 - `tts_polish_batch_planner` is implemented as the batching/planning layer for `tts_polish`\n 440 - `tts_polish_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `tts_polish` operator\n 441 - `tts_polish_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch polish outputs\n+466 - `retry_planner` is implemented as the retry decision layer for the supervisor","firstChangedLine":430},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774907567219}}
{"type":"message","id":"7b52e096","parentId":"5cf8f679","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:53:07.402Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Feito.\n\n## O que criei agora\n\n### Skill nova\nCriei:\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\retry_planner.py`\n\n---\n\n## O que ela faz\nEla transforma falhas do S1 em uma decisão explícita de retry.\n\n### Função implementada\n- `plan_retry(...)`\n\n### O que ela já distingue na v1\n#### Fail-fast estrutural\nExemplos:\n- `preflight_structural_failure`\n- `missing_required_input`\n- `invalid_job_json`\n- `invalid_pipeline_state`\n- `empty_script`\n- `b1_already_complete`\n\n→ decisão:\n### `abort`\n\n---\n\n#### Falhas retryáveis de operator\nExemplos:\n- `operator_timeout`\n- `operator_no_output`\n- `operator_output_missing`\n- `operator_invalid_json`\n- `operator_empty_output`\n- `operator_malformed_output`\n\n→ decisão:\n### `batch_subset` se houver batches afectados  \nou  \n### `step` se não houver\n\n---\n\n#### Falhas de merge recuperáveis\nExemplos:\n- `missing_batch_file`\n- `invalid_batch_json`\n- `invalid_batch_scenes`\n- `missing_scene_fields`\n- `missing_polish_fields`\n- `missing_polish_scene`\n\n→ decisão:\n### `batch_subset` se houver mapping dos batches afectados  \nsenão  \n### `abort`\n\n---\n\n#### Falhas semânticas de screenplay\nExemplos:\n- `screenplay_validation_failed`\n- `coverage_too_low`\n- `missing_words_detected`\n- `extra_words_detected`\n- `duplicate_scene_content`\n\n→ decisão:\n### `batch_subset` se houver batches afectados  \nou  \n### `step` do `scene_director`\n\n---\n\n#### Falhas semânticas de polish\nExemplos:\n- `polish_validation_failed`\n- `words_eaten`\n- `meaning_drift`\n- `unauthorized_additions`\n\n→ decisão:\n### `batch_subset` se houver batches afectados  \nou  \n### `step` do `tts_polish`\n\n---\n\n#### Falhas do builder / schema\nExemplos:\n- `scene_bible_write_failed`\n- `scene_bible_schema_invalid`\n- `scene_bible_builder_failed`\n\n→ decisão:\n### `step` do `scene_bible_builder`\n\n---\n\n#### Falhas de infra\nExemplos:\n- `filesystem_write_error`\n- `permission_error`\n- `disk_full`\n\n→ decisão:\n### `step` com retry controlado\n\n---\n\n### Também já respeita limite de retries\nSe `retry_count >= max_retries`\n→ decisão:\n### `abort`\n\n---\n\n## Shape do output\nA skill devolve algo como:\n- `retry`\n- `retry_mode`\n- `targets`\n- `reason`\n- `next_action`\n\nOu seja, já dá ao Supervisor um contrato claro de decisão.\n\n---\n\n## Doc central actualizado\nTambém actualizei:\n- `docs/contracts/s1_supervisor_contract.md`\n\nAgora ele já reflecte como implementadas:\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n- `retry_planner`\n\n---\n\n# Onde estamos agora\nO Supervisor do S1 já tem praticamente toda a sua espinha dorsal mecânica principal.\n\n## Já implementado\n1. `s1_preflight_checker`\n2. `s1_paths_resolver`\n3. `script_batch_planner`\n4. `scene_director_io_adapter`\n5. `screenplay_merger`\n6. `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n7. `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n8. `tts_polish_merger`\n9. `retry_planner`\n\nOu seja:\n- entrada\n- estrutura\n- batching dos dois operators\n- IO dos dois operators\n- merge dos dois operators\n- decisão de retry\n\nIsso é bastante coisa.\n\n---\n\n# Próximo passo mais lógico\nAgora os dois componentes mais naturais restantes são:\n\n## 1. `checkpoint_writer`\nou  \n## 2. `s1_result_summarizer`\n\n### Minha recomendação\nEu faria primeiro:\n## `checkpoint_writer`\n\nPorque ele faz parte do fluxo vivo do supervisor durante toda a execução,\nenquanto o `s1_result_summarizer` é mais fecho/finalização.\n\nSe quiseres, sigo já no `checkpoint_writer`.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0047bd771936d8e20169caf0b2cfdc8195903b9ce25862229a\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":307,"output":947,"cacheRead":184960,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":186214,"cost":{"input":0.0007675000000000001,"output":0.014205,"cacheRead":0.046239999999999996,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.061212499999999996}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774907567924,"responseId":"resp_0047bd771936d8e20169caf0b1bed081959dedaf1df33edb4e"}}
