{"type":"message","id":"bf97ee47","parentId":"6946bb77","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:59:57.292Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Vou formalizar o paralelismo controlado no contrato do Supervisor do S1 e criar a nova skill `operator_batch_scheduler` para o supervisor lançar batches com concurrency caps sem virar caos.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0047bd771936d8e20169caf2578ee88195a7027f677ac3056b\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_CSDjpb3mx5UXHHVIo1P3x1hs|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caf259a1308195827d9abee269a98f","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1_supervisor_contract.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1_supervisor_contract.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_CQJXoRR6upyNiLiszsoq2VxY|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caf259a144819590cb5ffb3812f2d4","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\retry_planner.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\supervisor_skills\\\\retry_planner.py\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":101884,"output":149,"cacheRead":90624,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":192657,"cost":{"input":0.25471000000000005,"output":0.002235,"cacheRead":0.022656,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.27960100000000004}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774907986135,"responseId":"resp_0047bd771936d8e20169caf25442348195aee3e3715031cbdc"}}
{"type":"message","id":"9c6bbdc8","parentId":"bf97ee47","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:59:57.971Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_CSDjpb3mx5UXHHVIo1P3x1hs|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caf259a1308195827d9abee269a98f","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# S1 Supervisor Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the role, boundaries, and first deterministic skill of the S1 (Pre-Production) Supervisor._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-30_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe S1 Supervisor is the supervisory layer for Pre-Production.\n\nIts job is to take a run that is `ready_for_s1` and coordinate the sector until it produces:\n- `screenplay.json`\n- `screenplay_validation.json`\n- `tts_polished.json`\n- `polish_validation.json`\n- `scene_bible.json`\n- `b1_*` checkpoints\n\nThe supervisor is an **OpenClaw LLM supervisor**, not a purely conversational helper and not a monolithic Python script that absorbs all work itself.\n\nIt should supervise using:\n- deterministic Python skills\n- specialized operators/sub-agents\n- explicit file contracts\n\n---\n\n## Core principle\n\n### Supervisor = brain\n### Skills = hands\n### Operators = specialists\n\nThe S1 Supervisor should:\n- decide the order of operations\n- decide when to call an operator vs a deterministic skill\n- interpret validation results\n- decide retry / fail / continue\n- write or trigger checkpoints\n\nThe S1 Supervisor should **not** directly absorb:\n- semantic scene generation\n- TTS polish generation\n- low-level file/path mechanics\n- deterministic validation logic\n- JSON merge/reindex mechanics\n\nThose belong to:\n- S1 operators (`scene_director`, `tts_polish`)\n- deterministic supervisor skills\n\n---\n\n## Current operator model\n\nThe current intended operator structure for S1 is:\n- `scene_director` -> OpenClaw operator\n- `tts_polish` -> OpenClaw operator\n\nThese operators communicate with the supervisor via explicit file contracts:\n- supervisor prepares input payload/file\n- operator reads input\n- operator writes output file\n- supervisor validates and decides next step\n\n---\n\n## Current deterministic skills owned by the supervisor\n\n### Implemented now\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n- `retry_planner`\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\n\n### Expected next skills\n- `checkpoint_writer` (already exists in `runtime/s1/checkpoint_writer.py`, pending light alignment audit only)\n\nThis list may evolve, but the supervisor should remain supervisory rather than mechanically overloaded.\n\n---\n\n## File contract principle\n\nThe supervisor must operate on persisted run artifacts.\n\nMinimum expected inputs before S1 begins:\n- `job.json`\n- `run_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_raw.txt`\n- `inputs/script/script_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_lock.json`\n- `checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json`\n\nMinimum expected outputs after S1 completes:\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay_validation.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/polish_validation.json`\n- `scene_bible.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step1_screenplay.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step2_screenplay_validated.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step3_tts_polished.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step4_polish_validated.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step5_scene_bible.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_complete.json`\n\n---\n\n## First implemented supervisor skill: `s1_preflight_checker`\n\n### Purpose\nValidate that a run is structurally ready to enter S1 before any operator or semantic step is invoked.\n\n### Scope\nChecks:\n- run root exists\n- required input files exist\n- `job.json` is readable and contains `job_id`, `account`, `language`\n- channel config exists at `accounts/{account}/{language}.yaml`\n- `script_raw.txt` is readable and not empty\n- `vo_script_ready` checkpoint exists\n- run state is minimally compatible with entering S1\n\n### Out of scope\n`s1_preflight_checker` does **not**:\n- create sector outputs\n- call operators\n- validate screenplay semantics\n- decide batching\n- modify the run\n\n### Input shape\n```json\n{\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\"\n}\n```\n\n### Output shape\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"job\": {\n    \"job_id\": \"2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n    \"account\": \"004\",\n    \"language\": \"fr\"\n  },\n  \"paths\": {\n    \"job_json\": \".../job.json\",\n    \"run_metadata\": \".../run_metadata.json\",\n    \"script_raw\": \".../inputs/script/script_raw.txt\",\n    \"script_metadata\": \".../inputs/script/script_metadata.json\",\n    \"script_lock\": \".../inputs/script/script_lock.json\",\n    \"vo_script_ready_checkpoint\": \".../checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json\",\n    \"channel_config\": \".../accounts/004/fr.yaml\"\n  },\n  \"script_stats\": {\n    \"char_count\": 0,\n    \"word_count\": 0\n  },\n  \"errors\": [],\n  \"warnings\": []\n}\n```\n\n### Error policy\nThe skill should collect all relevant failures and return them together.\nIt should not stop at the first missing file.\n\n### Warning policy\nExamples of warning-worthy but non-fatal conditions:\n- script very short\n- script very long\n- `b1_pre_production/` already exists but `b1_complete.json` does not\n\n### Fatal examples\n- missing `job.json`\n- missing `script_raw.txt`\n- unreadable or invalid `job.json`\n- missing channel config\n- missing `vo_script_ready.json`\n- empty script\n\n---\n\n## Naming convention\nThe canonical checkpoint and sector naming for Pre-Production is:\n- `b1_pre_production/`\n- `b1_*` checkpoints\n\nThe older `s1_*` naming should not be treated as canonical.\n\n---\n\n## Second implemented supervisor skill: `s1_paths_resolver`\n\n### Purpose\nResolve and centralize the canonical S1 paths for the run.\n\n### Scope\nResolves and optionally creates the directory structure for:\n- `b1_pre_production/`\n- `b1_pre_production/inputs/`\n- `b1_pre_production/intermediate/`\n- `inputs/scene_director/`\n- `inputs/tts_polish/`\n- `intermediate/scene_director/`\n- `intermediate/tts_polish/`\n- canonical output file paths\n- canonical `b1_*` checkpoint file paths\n\n### Out of scope\n`s1_paths_resolver` does **not**:\n- validate semantic readiness\n- call operators\n- inspect screenplay or polish content\n- perform batching\n\n### Input shape\n```json\n{\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"create_dirs\": true\n}\n```\n\n### Output shape\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"run_root\": \"C:/.../production/004_fr/2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"created_dirs\": true,\n  \"paths\": {\n    \"b1_root\": \".../b1_pre_production\",\n    \"inputs_root\": \".../b1_pre_production/inputs\",\n    \"intermediate_root\": \".../b1_pre_production/intermediate\",\n    \"screenplay_path\": \".../b1_pre_production/screenplay.json\",\n    \"tts_polished_path\": \".../b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json\",\n    \"scene_bible_path\": \".../scene_bible.json\",\n    \"b1_complete_checkpoint\": \".../checkpoints/b1_complete.json\"\n  },\n  \"errors\": [],\n  \"warnings\": []\n}\n```\n\n## Third implemented supervisor skill: `script_batch_planner`\n\n### Purpose\nSplit the raw script into manageable work batches for `scene_director` without turning the supervisor into a monolithic batching script.\n\n### Scope\n- receives raw script text or script file path\n- plans batches using target/min/max word budgets\n- prefers paragraph boundaries\n- falls back to sentence-based splitting for oversized paragraphs\n- preserves order and emits a stable `sd_###` batch sequence\n\n### Out of scope\n`script_batch_planner` does **not**:\n- divide the script into final scenes\n- call `scene_director`\n- perform semantic validation\n- merge operator outputs\n\n### Recommended v1 defaults\n- target words per batch: `750`\n- minimum words per batch: `450`\n- maximum words per batch: `950`\n\n### Output shape\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"total_words\": 3520,\n  \"batch_count\": 5,\n  \"target_words_per_batch\": 750,\n  \"min_words_per_batch\": 450,\n  \"max_words_per_batch\": 950,\n  \"batches\": [\n    {\n      \"batch_id\": \"sd_001\",\n      \"start_word\": 1,\n      \"end_word\": 742,\n      \"word_count\": 742,\n      \"text\": \"...\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"errors\": [],\n  \"warnings\": []\n}\n```\n\n## Fourth implemented supervisor skill: `scene_director_io_adapter`\n\n### Purpose\nPrepare the explicit input/output contract between the S1 Supervisor and the `scene_director` operator for each planned script batch.\n\n### Scope\n- receives run/job context\n- receives one script batch from `script_batch_planner`\n- injects `scene_words_range` from channel config\n- writes a deterministic payload file for the operator\n- declares the expected output path for the batch result\n\n### Out of scope\n`scene_director_io_adapter` does **not**:\n- run the operator\n- validate semantic quality\n- merge batch outputs\n- choose retry policy\n\n### Output contract principle\nEach batch payload should explicitly tell `scene_director`:\n- who the run/job is\n- what the batch text is\n- what scene structure is expected\n- where to write the result\n\n## Fifth implemented supervisor skill: `screenplay_merger`\n\n### Purpose\nMerge the batch outputs of `scene_director` into one canonical `screenplay.json` without forcing the supervisor itself to concatenate, validate, and reindex scene objects manually.\n\n### Scope\n- loads ordered batch output files\n- validates minimum required scene fields\n- concatenates scenes in batch order\n- reassigns canonical `scene_###` IDs globally\n- writes `screenplay.json`\n\n### Out of scope\n`screenplay_merger` does **not**:\n- perform semantic validation\n- decide retry policy\n- invoke operators\n- polish TTS text\n\n### Output contract principle\nThe merged screenplay should preserve order while normalizing scene IDs into one canonical sequence for the rest of S1.\n\n## Sixth implemented supervisor skill: `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n\n### Purpose\nPlan small, stable polish batches from the merged screenplay so that `tts_polish` receives manageable groups of scenes instead of the full screenplay at once.\n\n### Scope\n- receives `screenplay.json`\n- groups scenes by count and approximate word budget\n- preserves scene order\n- emits a stable `tp_###` batch sequence\n\n### Recommended v1 defaults\n- target scenes per batch: `5`\n- minimum scenes per batch: `3`\n- maximum scenes per batch: `6`\n- maximum words per batch: `350`\n\n### Out of scope\n`tts_polish_batch_planner` does **not**:\n- perform TTS polish\n- validate semantic quality\n- merge polish outputs\n- decide retry policy\n\n## Seventh implemented supervisor skill: `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n\n### Purpose\nPrepare the explicit input/output contract between the S1 Supervisor and the `tts_polish` operator for each planned polish batch.\n\n### Scope\n- receives run/job context\n- receives merged screenplay\n- receives one polish batch from `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- injects `tts_polish_rules` from channel config\n- writes a deterministic payload file for the operator\n- declares the expected output path for the batch result\n\n### Out of scope\n`tts_polish_io_adapter` does **not**:\n- run the operator\n- validate semantic quality\n- merge polish outputs\n- choose retry policy\n\n### Output contract principle\nEach polish batch payload should explicitly tell `tts_polish`:\n- which scenes belong to the batch\n- what the original narration is\n- what rules govern polish behavior\n- where to write the result\n\n## Eighth implemented supervisor skill: `tts_polish_merger`\n\n### Purpose\nMerge the batch outputs of `tts_polish` into one canonical `tts_polished.json` while preserving screenplay order and preserving the distinction between original narration and TTS-polished narration.\n\n### Scope\n- loads ordered polish batch files\n- validates minimum required polish scene fields\n- rebuilds one ordered `tts_polished.json`\n- uses screenplay order as the canonical scene sequence\n\n### Out of scope\n`tts_polish_merger` does **not**:\n- validate semantic quality of the polish\n- decide retry policy\n- invoke operators\n- overwrite the original screenplay artifact\n\n### Output contract principle\nThe merged polish output should preserve:\n- `scene_id`\n- `narration_original`\n- `narration_tts`\n\nwithout destroying the original screenplay layer.\n\n## Ninth implemented supervisor skill: `retry_planner`\n\n### Purpose\nTurn observed failures into explicit retry decisions so the S1 Supervisor can decide whether to abort, rerun a whole step, or rerun only affected batches.\n\n### Scope\n- classifies failure types into retry strategies\n- enforces retry limits\n- supports fail-fast structural errors\n- supports batch-subset retries for localized operator/semantic failures\n- supports step-level retries when failures are broader\n\n### Out of scope\n`retry_planner` does **not**:\n- run retries itself\n- inspect semantic payloads deeply\n- invoke operators or validators\n- write checkpoints\n\n### Decision categories in v1\n- `abort`\n- `step`\n- `batch_subset`\n\n## Tenth implemented supervisor skill: `s1_result_summarizer`\n\n### Purpose\nProduce the final structured sector result that the S1 Supervisor can return upward after the sector finishes or fails.\n\n### Scope\n- aggregates scene counts\n- aggregates batch counts\n- exposes `scene_bible_path`\n- exposes checkpoint list\n- determines final `status` / `next_step`\n- preserves warnings/errors in one final result object\n\n### Out of scope\n`s1_result_summarizer` does **not**:\n- run the sector\n- write checkpoints\n- validate semantic correctness\n- call operators or skills\n\n## Current status summary\nAt this stage:\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\n- deterministic helper skills are being formalized\n- `s1_preflight_checker` is implemented as the entry gate for the sector\n- `s1_paths_resolver` is implemented as the canonical path/structure resolver for the sector\n- `script_batch_planner` is implemented as the first batching/planning skill for the sector\n- `scene_director_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `scene_director` operator\n- `screenplay_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch screenplay outputs\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner` is implemented as the batching/planning layer for `tts_polish`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `tts_polish` operator\n- `tts_polish_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch polish outputs\n- `retry_planner` is implemented as the retry decision layer for the supervisor\n- `s1_result_summarizer` is implemented as the final sector result aggregation layer\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774907997852}}
{"type":"message","id":"fc0b6124","parentId":"9c6bbdc8","timestamp":"2026-03-30T21:59:58.095Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_CQJXoRR6upyNiLiszsoq2VxY|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caf259a144819590cb5ffb3812f2d4","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\nMAX_RETRIES_DEFAULT = 3\n\n\nFAIL_FAST_TYPES = {\n    \"preflight_structural_failure\",\n    \"missing_required_input\",\n    \"invalid_job_json\",\n    \"invalid_pipeline_state\",\n    \"empty_script\",\n    \"b1_already_complete\",\n}\n\nOPERATOR_RETRYABLE_TYPES = {\n    \"operator_timeout\",\n    \"operator_no_output\",\n    \"operator_output_missing\",\n    \"operator_invalid_json\",\n    \"operator_empty_output\",\n    \"operator_malformed_output\",\n}\n\nMERGE_RECOVERY_TYPES = {\n    \"missing_batch_file\",\n    \"invalid_batch_json\",\n    \"invalid_batch_scenes\",\n    \"missing_scene_fields\",\n    \"missing_polish_fields\",\n    \"missing_polish_scene\",\n}\n\nSEMANTIC_SCREENPLAY_TYPES = {\n    \"screenplay_validation_failed\",\n    \"coverage_too_low\",\n    \"missing_words_detected\",\n    \"extra_words_detected\",\n    \"duplicate_scene_content\",\n}\n\nSEMANTIC_POLISH_TYPES = {\n    \"polish_validation_failed\",\n    \"words_eaten\",\n    \"meaning_drift\",\n    \"unauthorized_additions\",\n}\n\nBUILDER_RETRYABLE_TYPES = {\n    \"scene_bible_write_failed\",\n    \"scene_bible_schema_invalid\",\n    \"scene_bible_builder_failed\",\n}\n\nINFRA_FAILURE_TYPES = {\n    \"filesystem_write_error\",\n    \"permission_error\",\n    \"disk_full\",\n}\n\n\ndef plan_retry(\n    *,\n    step_name: str,\n    failure_type: str,\n    retry_count: int,\n    affected_batches: list[str] | None = None,\n    affected_scenes: list[str] | None = None,\n    max_retries: int = MAX_RETRIES_DEFAULT,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    affected_batches = affected_batches or []\n    affected_scenes = affected_scenes or []\n\n    if retry_count >= max_retries:\n        return _decision(\n            retry=False,\n            retry_mode=\"abort\",\n            targets=[],\n            reason=f\"Retry limit reached for step '{step_name}' ({retry_count}/{max_retries})\",\n            next_action=\"fail_sector\",\n        )\n\n    if failure_type in FAIL_FAST_TYPES:\n        return _decision(\n            retry=False,\n            retry_mode=\"abort\",\n            targets=[],\n            reason=f\"Structural failure '{failure_type}' should fail fast\",\n            next_action=\"fail_sector\",\n        )\n\n    if failure_type in OPERATOR_RETRYABLE_TYPES:\n        if affected_batches:\n            return _decision(\n                retry=True,\n                retry_mode=\"batch_subset\",\n                targets=affected_batches,\n                reason=f\"Operator execution failure '{failure_type}' — rerun affected batches\",\n                next_action=f\"rerun_{step_name}_batches\",\n            )\n        return _decision(\n            retry=True,\n            retry_mode=\"step\",\n            targets=[step_name],\n            reason=f\"Operator execution failure '{failure_type}' — rerun step\",\n            next_action=f\"rerun_{step_name}\",\n        )\n\n    if failure_type in MERGE_RECOVERY_TYPES:\n        if affected_batches:\n            return _decision(\n                retry=True,\n                retry_mode=\"batch_subset\",\n                targets=affected_batches,\n                reason=f\"Merge issue '{failure_type}' traced to missing/invalid batch outputs\",\n                next_action=\"rerun_affected_batches_then_merge\",\n            )\n        return _decision(\n            retry=False,\n            retry_mode=\"abort\",\n            targets=[],\n            reason=f\"Merge failure '{failure_type}' cannot be safely retried without affected batch mapping\",\n            next_action=\"fail_sector\",\n        )\n\n    if failure_type in SEMANTIC_SCREENPLAY_TYPES:\n        if affected_batches:\n            return _decision(\n                retry=True,\n                retry_mode=\"batch_subset\",\n                targets=affected_batches,\n                reason=f\"Screenplay semantic failure '{failure_type}' — rerun affected screenplay batches\",\n                next_action=\"rerun_scene_director_batches\",\n            )\n        return _decision(\n            retry=True,\n            retry_mode=\"step\",\n            targets=[\"scene_director\"],\n            reason=f\"Screenplay semantic failure '{failure_type}' — rerun screenplay step\",\n            next_action=\"rerun_scene_director_step\",\n        )\n\n    if failure_type in SEMANTIC_POLISH_TYPES:\n        if affected_batches:\n            return _decision(\n                retry=True,\n                retry_mode=\"batch_subset\",\n                targets=affected_batches,\n                reason=f\"Polish semantic failure '{failure_type}' — rerun affected polish batches\",\n                next_action=\"rerun_tts_polish_batches\",\n            )\n        return _decision(\n            retry=True,\n            retry_mode=\"step\",\n            targets=[\"tts_polish\"],\n            reason=f\"Polish semantic failure '{failure_type}' — rerun TTS polish step\",\n            next_action=\"rerun_tts_polish_step\",\n        )\n\n    if failure_type in BUILDER_RETRYABLE_TYPES:\n        return _decision(\n            retry=True,\n            retry_mode=\"step\",\n            targets=[\"scene_bible_builder\"],\n            reason=f\"Scene bible build failure '{failure_type}' — rerun builder step\",\n            next_action=\"rerun_scene_bible_builder\",\n        )\n\n    if failure_type in INFRA_FAILURE_TYPES:\n        return _decision(\n            retry=True,\n            retry_mode=\"step\",\n            targets=[step_name],\n            reason=f\"Infrastructure failure '{failure_type}' — allow one more controlled retry\",\n            next_action=f\"rerun_{step_name}\",\n        )\n\n    return _decision(\n        retry=False,\n        retry_mode=\"abort\",\n        targets=[],\n        reason=f\"Unknown failure type '{failure_type}' — abort by default for safety\",\n        next_action=\"fail_sector\",\n    )\n\n\ndef _decision(\n    *,\n    retry: bool,\n    retry_mode: str,\n    targets: list[str],\n    reason: str,\n    next_action: str,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    return {\n        \"retry\": retry,\n        \"retry_mode\": retry_mode,\n        \"targets\": targets,\n        \"reason\": reason,\n        \"next_action\": next_action,\n    }\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774907997972}}
{"type":"message","id":"7158ac5b","parentId":"fc0b6124","timestamp":"2026-03-30T22:00:46.320Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_X5Q6cTHlsqlAl0qSPsMCDCsq|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caf28ec8208195a354f395e49789cd","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\operator_batch_scheduler.py","content":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\ndef build_batch_schedule(\n    *,\n    operator_name: str,\n    batches: list[dict[str, Any]],\n    concurrency_cap: int,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    if concurrency_cap < 1:\n        return {\n            \"ok\": False,\n            \"operator\": operator_name,\n            \"errors\": [{\"code\": \"invalid_concurrency_cap\", \"message\": \"concurrency_cap must be >= 1\"}],\n            \"warnings\": [],\n        }\n\n    normalized_batches: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n    for batch in batches:\n        normalized_batches.append(\n            {\n                \"batch_id\": batch.get(\"batch_id\"),\n                \"input_path\": batch.get(\"input_path\"),\n                \"output_path\": batch.get(\"output_path\"),\n                \"status\": batch.get(\"status\", \"queued\"),\n            }\n        )\n\n    waves: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n    for i in range(0, len(normalized_batches), concurrency_cap):\n        wave_batches = normalized_batches[i : i + concurrency_cap]\n        waves.append(\n            {\n                \"wave_index\": len(waves) + 1,\n                \"batch_ids\": [b.get(\"batch_id\") for b in wave_batches],\n                \"batch_count\": len(wave_batches),\n                \"batches\": wave_batches,\n            }\n        )\n\n    return {\n        \"ok\": True,\n        \"operator\": operator_name,\n        \"concurrency_cap\": concurrency_cap,\n        \"total_batches\": len(normalized_batches),\n        \"wave_count\": len(waves),\n        \"waves\": waves,\n        \"errors\": [],\n        \"warnings\": [],\n    }\n\n\ndef summarize_batch_execution(\n    *,\n    operator_name: str,\n    concurrency_cap: int,\n    execution_results: list[dict[str, Any]],\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    completed_batches: list[str] = []\n    failed_batches: list[str] = []\n    pending_batches: list[str] = []\n    output_files: list[str] = []\n    errors: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n    warnings: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n\n    for result in execution_results:\n        batch_id = result.get(\"batch_id\")\n        status = result.get(\"status\", \"unknown\")\n\n        if status == \"completed\":\n            completed_batches.append(batch_id)\n            if result.get(\"output_path\"):\n                output_files.append(result[\"output_path\"])\n        elif status == \"failed\":\n            failed_batches.append(batch_id)\n        else:\n            pending_batches.append(batch_id)\n\n        for error in result.get(\"errors\", []) or []:\n            if isinstance(error, dict):\n                errors.append(error)\n        for warning in result.get(\"warnings\", []) or []:\n            if isinstance(warning, dict):\n                warnings.append(warning)\n\n    return {\n        \"ok\": len(failed_batches) == 0,\n        \"operator\": operator_name,\n        \"concurrency_cap\": concurrency_cap,\n        \"total_batches\": len(execution_results),\n        \"completed_batches\": completed_batches,\n        \"failed_batches\": failed_batches,\n        \"pending_batches\": pending_batches,\n        \"output_files\": output_files,\n        \"errors\": errors,\n        \"warnings\": warnings,\n    }\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\supervisor_skills\\\\operator_batch_scheduler.py\",\"content\":\"from __future__ import annotations\\n\\nfrom typing import Any\\n\\n\\ndef build_batch_schedule(\\n    *,\\n    operator_name: str,\\n    batches: list[dict[str, Any]],\\n    concurrency_cap: int,\\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\\n    if concurrency_cap < 1:\\n        return {\\n            \\\"ok\\\": False,\\n            \\\"operator\\\": operator_name,\\n            \\\"errors\\\": [{\\\"code\\\": \\\"invalid_concurrency_cap\\\", \\\"message\\\": \\\"concurrency_cap must be >= 1\\\"}],\\n            \\\"warnings\\\": [],\\n        }\\n\\n    normalized_batches: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\\n    for batch in batches:\\n        normalized_batches.append(\\n            {\\n                \\\"batch_id\\\": batch.get(\\\"batch_id\\\"),\\n                \\\"input_path\\\": batch.get(\\\"input_path\\\"),\\n                \\\"output_path\\\": batch.get(\\\"output_path\\\"),\\n                \\\"status\\\": batch.get(\\\"status\\\", \\\"queued\\\"),\\n            }\\n        )\\n\\n    waves: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\\n    for i in range(0, len(normalized_batches), concurrency_cap):\\n        wave_batches = normalized_batches[i : i + concurrency_cap]\\n        waves.append(\\n            {\\n                \\\"wave_index\\\": len(waves) + 1,\\n                \\\"batch_ids\\\": [b.get(\\\"batch_id\\\") for b in wave_batches],\\n                \\\"batch_count\\\": len(wave_batches),\\n                \\\"batches\\\": wave_batches,\\n            }\\n        )\\n\\n    return {\\n        \\\"ok\\\": True,\\n        \\\"operator\\\": operator_name,\\n        \\\"concurrency_cap\\\": concurrency_cap,\\n        \\\"total_batches\\\": len(normalized_batches),\\n        \\\"wave_count\\\": len(waves),\\n        \\\"waves\\\": waves,\\n        \\\"errors\\\": [],\\n        \\\"warnings\\\": [],\\n    }\\n\\n\\ndef summarize_batch_execution(\\n    *,\\n    operator_name: str,\\n    concurrency_cap: int,\\n    execution_results: list[dict[str, Any]],\\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\\n    completed_batches: list[str] = []\\n    failed_batches: list[str] = []\\n    pending_batches: list[str] = []\\n    output_files: list[str] = []\\n    errors: list[dict[str, str]] = []\\n    warnings: list[dict[str, str]] = []\\n\\n    for result in execution_results:\\n        batch_id = result.get(\\\"batch_id\\\")\\n        status = result.get(\\\"status\\\", \\\"unknown\\\")\\n\\n        if status == \\\"completed\\\":\\n            completed_batches.append(batch_id)\\n            if result.get(\\\"output_path\\\"):\\n                output_files.append(result[\\\"output_path\\\"])\\n        elif status == \\\"failed\\\":\\n            failed_batches.append(batch_id)\\n        else:\\n            pending_batches.append(batch_id)\\n\\n        for error in result.get(\\\"errors\\\", []) or []:\\n            if isinstance(error, dict):\\n                errors.append(error)\\n        for warning in result.get(\\\"warnings\\\", []) or []:\\n            if isinstance(warning, dict):\\n                warnings.append(warning)\\n\\n    return {\\n        \\\"ok\\\": len(failed_batches) == 0,\\n        \\\"operator\\\": operator_name,\\n        \\\"concurrency_cap\\\": concurrency_cap,\\n        \\\"total_batches\\\": len(execution_results),\\n        \\\"completed_batches\\\": completed_batches,\\n        \\\"failed_batches\\\": failed_batches,\\n        \\\"pending_batches\\\": pending_batches,\\n        \\\"output_files\\\": output_files,\\n        \\\"errors\\\": errors,\\n        \\\"warnings\\\": warnings,\\n    }\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_HDDcR776VpNBVNouzwIxKQI7|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caf28ec83c8195a27cbf46974383af","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1_supervisor_contract.md","oldText":"### Implemented now\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n- `retry_planner`\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\n","newText":"### Implemented now\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n- `retry_planner`\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\n- `operator_batch_scheduler`\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1_supervisor_contract.md\",\"oldText\":\"### Implemented now\\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\\n- `script_batch_planner`\\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\\n- `screenplay_merger`\\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\\n- `tts_polish_merger`\\n- `retry_planner`\\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\\n\",\"newText\":\"### Implemented now\\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\\n- `script_batch_planner`\\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\\n- `screenplay_merger`\\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\\n- `tts_polish_merger`\\n- `retry_planner`\\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\\n- `operator_batch_scheduler`\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_jGdQftUtDqHlotWr4pld9Tgz|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caf28ec85c81959d790d27f4f93ffc","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1_supervisor_contract.md","oldText":"## Current operator model\n\nThe current intended operator structure for S1 is:\n- `scene_director` -> OpenClaw operator\n- `tts_polish` -> OpenClaw operator\n\nThese operators communicate with the supervisor via explicit file contracts:\n- supervisor prepares input payload/file\n- operator reads input\n- operator writes output file\n- supervisor validates and decides next step\n","newText":"## Current operator model\n\nThe current intended operator structure for S1 is:\n- `scene_director` -> OpenClaw operator\n- `tts_polish` -> OpenClaw operator\n\nThese operators communicate with the supervisor via explicit file contracts:\n- supervisor prepares input payload/file\n- operator reads input\n- operator writes output file\n- supervisor validates and decides next step\n\n## Controlled parallelism policy\n\nThe S1 Supervisor should support controlled parallelism for batchable operators.\n\n### Initial recommended concurrency caps\n- `scene_director_concurrency_cap = 2`\n- `tts_polish_concurrency_cap = 4`\n\n### Parallelism rules\n- only batchable operators should be parallelized\n- validators, mergers, builders, and preflight remain sequential/deterministic\n- the supervisor should not launch all batches at once without a cap\n- batches should be processed in controlled waves/windows\n- failed batches should be retried selectively when possible via `retry_planner`\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1_supervisor_contract.md\",\"oldText\":\"## Current operator model\\n\\nThe current intended operator structure for S1 is:\\n- `scene_director` -> OpenClaw operator\\n- `tts_polish` -> OpenClaw operator\\n\\nThese operators communicate with the supervisor via explicit file contracts:\\n- supervisor prepares input payload/file\\n- operator reads input\\n- operator writes output file\\n- supervisor validates and decides next step\\n\",\"newText\":\"## Current operator model\\n\\nThe current intended operator structure for S1 is:\\n- `scene_director` -> OpenClaw operator\\n- `tts_polish` -> OpenClaw operator\\n\\nThese operators communicate with the supervisor via explicit file contracts:\\n- supervisor prepares input payload/file\\n- operator reads input\\n- operator writes output file\\n- supervisor validates and decides next step\\n\\n## Controlled parallelism policy\\n\\nThe S1 Supervisor should support controlled parallelism for batchable operators.\\n\\n### Initial recommended concurrency caps\\n- `scene_director_concurrency_cap = 2`\\n- `tts_polish_concurrency_cap = 4`\\n\\n### Parallelism rules\\n- only batchable operators should be parallelized\\n- validators, mergers, builders, and preflight remain sequential/deterministic\\n- the supervisor should not launch all batches at once without a cap\\n- batches should be processed in controlled waves/windows\\n- failed batches should be retried selectively when possible via `retry_planner`\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_T9AoKWeSDqzime3yN8SVNpfq|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caf28ec86c81958d35cb23a5b49d0f","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1_supervisor_contract.md","oldText":"## Tenth implemented supervisor skill: `s1_result_summarizer`\n\n### Purpose\nProduce the final structured sector result that the S1 Supervisor can return upward after the sector finishes or fails.\n\n### Scope\n- aggregates scene counts\n- aggregates batch counts\n- exposes `scene_bible_path`\n- exposes checkpoint list\n- determines final `status` / `next_step`\n- preserves warnings/errors in one final result object\n\n### Out of scope\n`s1_result_summarizer` does **not**:\n- run the sector\n- write checkpoints\n- validate semantic correctness\n- call operators or skills\n\n## Current status summary\nAt this stage:\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\n- deterministic helper skills are being formalized\n- `s1_preflight_checker` is implemented as the entry gate for the sector\n- `s1_paths_resolver` is implemented as the canonical path/structure resolver for the sector\n- `script_batch_planner` is implemented as the first batching/planning skill for the sector\n- `scene_director_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `scene_director` operator\n- `screenplay_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch screenplay outputs\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner` is implemented as the batching/planning layer for `tts_polish`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `tts_polish` operator\n- `tts_polish_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch polish outputs\n- `retry_planner` is implemented as the retry decision layer for the supervisor\n- `s1_result_summarizer` is implemented as the final sector result aggregation layer\n","newText":"## Tenth implemented supervisor skill: `s1_result_summarizer`\n\n### Purpose\nProduce the final structured sector result that the S1 Supervisor can return upward after the sector finishes or fails.\n\n### Scope\n- aggregates scene counts\n- aggregates batch counts\n- exposes `scene_bible_path`\n- exposes checkpoint list\n- determines final `status` / `next_step`\n- preserves warnings/errors in one final result object\n\n### Out of scope\n`s1_result_summarizer` does **not**:\n- run the sector\n- write checkpoints\n- validate semantic correctness\n- call operators or skills\n\n## Eleventh implemented supervisor skill: `operator_batch_scheduler`\n\n### Purpose\nProvide the controlled parallelism layer for batchable operators so the supervisor can launch work in capped waves instead of all-at-once or fully sequentially.\n\n### Scope\n- receives operator batches\n- applies a concurrency cap\n- groups batches into execution waves\n- summarizes execution outcomes into completed / failed / pending sets\n\n### Initial supported operators\n- `scene_director`\n- `tts_polish`\n\n### Out of scope\n`operator_batch_scheduler` does **not**:\n- invoke OpenClaw operators by itself yet\n- decide semantic retry logic\n- merge outputs\n- validate content\n\n## Current status summary\nAt this stage:\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\n- deterministic helper skills are being formalized\n- `s1_preflight_checker` is implemented as the entry gate for the sector\n- `s1_paths_resolver` is implemented as the canonical path/structure resolver for the sector\n- `script_batch_planner` is implemented as the first batching/planning skill for the sector\n- `scene_director_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `scene_director` operator\n- `screenplay_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch screenplay outputs\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner` is implemented as the batching/planning layer for `tts_polish`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `tts_polish` operator\n- `tts_polish_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch polish outputs\n- `retry_planner` is implemented as the retry decision layer for the supervisor\n- `s1_result_summarizer` is implemented as the final sector result aggregation layer\n- `operator_batch_scheduler` is implemented as the controlled parallel scheduling layer for batchable operators\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1_supervisor_contract.md\",\"oldText\":\"## Tenth implemented supervisor skill: `s1_result_summarizer`\\n\\n### Purpose\\nProduce the final structured sector result that the S1 Supervisor can return upward after the sector finishes or fails.\\n\\n### Scope\\n- aggregates scene counts\\n- aggregates batch counts\\n- exposes `scene_bible_path`\\n- exposes checkpoint list\\n- determines final `status` / `next_step`\\n- preserves warnings/errors in one final result object\\n\\n### Out of scope\\n`s1_result_summarizer` does **not**:\\n- run the sector\\n- write checkpoints\\n- validate semantic correctness\\n- call operators or skills\\n\\n## Current status summary\\nAt this stage:\\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\\n- deterministic helper skills are being formalized\\n- `s1_preflight_checker` is implemented as the entry gate for the sector\\n- `s1_paths_resolver` is implemented as the canonical path/structure resolver for the sector\\n- `script_batch_planner` is implemented as the first batching/planning skill for the sector\\n- `scene_director_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `scene_director` operator\\n- `screenplay_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch screenplay outputs\\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner` is implemented as the batching/planning layer for `tts_polish`\\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `tts_polish` operator\\n- `tts_polish_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch polish outputs\\n- `retry_planner` is implemented as the retry decision layer for the supervisor\\n- `s1_result_summarizer` is implemented as the final sector result aggregation layer\\n\",\"newText\":\"## Tenth implemented supervisor skill: `s1_result_summarizer`\\n\\n### Purpose\\nProduce the final structured sector result that the S1 Supervisor can return upward after the sector finishes or fails.\\n\\n### Scope\\n- aggregates scene counts\\n- aggregates batch counts\\n- exposes `scene_bible_path`\\n- exposes checkpoint list\\n- determines final `status` / `next_step`\\n- preserves warnings/errors in one final result object\\n\\n### Out of scope\\n`s1_result_summarizer` does **not**:\\n- run the sector\\n- write checkpoints\\n- validate semantic correctness\\n- call operators or skills\\n\\n## Eleventh implemented supervisor skill: `operator_batch_scheduler`\\n\\n### Purpose\\nProvide the controlled parallelism layer for batchable operators so the supervisor can launch work in capped waves instead of all-at-once or fully sequentially.\\n\\n### Scope\\n- receives operator batches\\n- applies a concurrency cap\\n- groups batches into execution waves\\n- summarizes execution outcomes into completed / failed / pending sets\\n\\n### Initial supported operators\\n- `scene_director`\\n- `tts_polish`\\n\\n### Out of scope\\n`operator_batch_scheduler` does **not**:\\n- invoke OpenClaw operators by itself yet\\n- decide semantic retry logic\\n- merge outputs\\n- validate content\\n\\n## Current status summary\\nAt this stage:\\n- the S1 Supervisor is defined as an OpenClaw LLM supervisor\\n- deterministic helper skills are being formalized\\n- `s1_preflight_checker` is implemented as the entry gate for the sector\\n- `s1_paths_resolver` is implemented as the canonical path/structure resolver for the sector\\n- `script_batch_planner` is implemented as the first batching/planning skill for the sector\\n- `scene_director_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `scene_director` operator\\n- `screenplay_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch screenplay outputs\\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner` is implemented as the batching/planning layer for `tts_polish`\\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter` is implemented as the explicit batch contract bridge to the `tts_polish` operator\\n- `tts_polish_merger` is implemented as the deterministic recomposition layer for batch polish outputs\\n- `retry_planner` is implemented as the retry decision layer for the supervisor\\n- `s1_result_summarizer` is implemented as the final sector result aggregation layer\\n- `operator_batch_scheduler` is implemented as the controlled parallel scheduling layer for batchable operators\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":64083,"output":2414,"cacheRead":129536,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":196033,"cost":{"input":0.1602075,"output":0.03621,"cacheRead":0.032383999999999996,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.2288015}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774907998567,"responseId":"resp_0047bd771936d8e20169caf26034108195bdc284e20ec40330"}}
