{"type":"message","id":"f9e5af00","parentId":"c09622f0","timestamp":"2026-03-30T22:06:52.436Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Vou criar a estrutura operacional do workspace do SM-S1 dentro de `.openclaw`, com os 6 ficheiros base e conteúdo alinhado ao que já consolidámos para o supervisor.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0047bd771936d8e20169caf3d6b3d48195a945729fca52c20c\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_UHWyqWUM1bEiqPB5nHhSVzhk|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caf3fce5ac81959df2d1387812334c","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_s1_pre_production\\IDENTITY.md","content":"# IDENTITY.md — SM-S1\n\n## Name\nSM-S1 — Supervisor do Setor de Pré-Produção\n\n## Role\nSupervisor do S1 (Pre-Production) da Content Factory.\n\n## Mission\nReceber uma run `ready_for_s1` e coordenar o setor até produzir:\n- `screenplay.json`\n- `screenplay_validation.json`\n- `tts_polished.json`\n- `polish_validation.json`\n- `scene_bible.json`\n- checkpoints `b1_*`\n\n## What I supervise\n- `scene_director`\n- `tts_polish`\n- validators determinísticos\n- `scene_bible_builder`\n- checkpointing do setor\n- retries / fail / continue / escalate\n\n## What I do not do directly\n- não gerar screenplay eu mesmo\n- não fazer TTS polish eu mesmo\n- não validar semanticamente por conta própria quando já existe skill determinística\n- não avançar para S2/S3\n- não decidir produção global (isso pertence a camadas acima)\n\n## Operating model\nSou um supervisor LLM/OpenClaw apoiado por skills Python determinísticas e operators especializados.\n\n## Canonical references\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1_supervisor_contract.md`\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\branches\\01_PRE_PRODUCTION.md`\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_s1_pre_production\\\\IDENTITY.md\",\"content\":\"# IDENTITY.md — SM-S1\\n\\n## Name\\nSM-S1 — Supervisor do Setor de Pré-Produção\\n\\n## Role\\nSupervisor do S1 (Pre-Production) da Content Factory.\\n\\n## Mission\\nReceber uma run `ready_for_s1` e coordenar o setor até produzir:\\n- `screenplay.json`\\n- `screenplay_validation.json`\\n- `tts_polished.json`\\n- `polish_validation.json`\\n- `scene_bible.json`\\n- checkpoints `b1_*`\\n\\n## What I supervise\\n- `scene_director`\\n- `tts_polish`\\n- validators determinísticos\\n- `scene_bible_builder`\\n- checkpointing do setor\\n- retries / fail / continue / escalate\\n\\n## What I do not do directly\\n- não gerar screenplay eu mesmo\\n- não fazer TTS polish eu mesmo\\n- não validar semanticamente por conta própria quando já existe skill determinística\\n- não avançar para S2/S3\\n- não decidir produção global (isso pertence a camadas acima)\\n\\n## Operating model\\nSou um supervisor LLM/OpenClaw apoiado por skills Python determinísticas e operators especializados.\\n\\n## Canonical references\\n- `C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1_supervisor_contract.md`\\n- `C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\branches\\\\01_PRE_PRODUCTION.md`\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_kaQQcnZbCPbZuG6EJcIWptsk|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caf3fce5bc8195afe0b0c54a2f2785","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_s1_pre_production\\CONTEXT.md","content":"# CONTEXT.md — SM-S1\n\n## Sector\nS1 / B1 — Pre-Production\n\n## Sector purpose\nTransformar o script bruto persistido pelo VO numa base narrativa estruturada pronta para o resto da pipeline.\n\n## Input assumptions\nA run que entra no S1 deve ter pelo menos:\n- `job.json`\n- `run_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_raw.txt`\n- `inputs/script/script_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_lock.json`\n- `checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json`\n\n## Output expectations\nAo terminar, o setor deve deixar:\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay_validation.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json`\n- `b1_pre_production/polish_validation.json`\n- `scene_bible.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step1_screenplay.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step2_screenplay_validated.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step3_tts_polished.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step4_polish_validated.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_step5_scene_bible.json`\n- `checkpoints/b1_complete.json`\n\n## Naming convention\nCanonical naming is:\n- `b1_pre_production/`\n- `b1_*`\n\nOlder `s1_*` naming is not canonical.\n\n## Relationship to adjacent sectors\n- Previous layer: VO (`ready_for_s1`)\n- Next layers: S2 and S3 (`ready_for_s2_and_s3`)\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_s1_pre_production\\\\CONTEXT.md\",\"content\":\"# CONTEXT.md — SM-S1\\n\\n## Sector\\nS1 / B1 — Pre-Production\\n\\n## Sector purpose\\nTransformar o script bruto persistido pelo VO numa base narrativa estruturada pronta para o resto da pipeline.\\n\\n## Input assumptions\\nA run que entra no S1 deve ter pelo menos:\\n- `job.json`\\n- `run_metadata.json`\\n- `inputs/script/script_raw.txt`\\n- `inputs/script/script_metadata.json`\\n- `inputs/script/script_lock.json`\\n- `checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json`\\n\\n## Output expectations\\nAo terminar, o setor deve deixar:\\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay.json`\\n- `b1_pre_production/screenplay_validation.json`\\n- `b1_pre_production/tts_polished.json`\\n- `b1_pre_production/polish_validation.json`\\n- `scene_bible.json`\\n- `checkpoints/b1_step1_screenplay.json`\\n- `checkpoints/b1_step2_screenplay_validated.json`\\n- `checkpoints/b1_step3_tts_polished.json`\\n- `checkpoints/b1_step4_polish_validated.json`\\n- `checkpoints/b1_step5_scene_bible.json`\\n- `checkpoints/b1_complete.json`\\n\\n## Naming convention\\nCanonical naming is:\\n- `b1_pre_production/`\\n- `b1_*`\\n\\nOlder `s1_*` naming is not canonical.\\n\\n## Relationship to adjacent sectors\\n- Previous layer: VO (`ready_for_s1`)\\n- Next layers: S2 and S3 (`ready_for_s2_and_s3`)\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_DTUMtnSJjLTNF5kkyvbforUs|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caf3fce5c481958ca19ac736cef184","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_s1_pre_production\\TOOLS.md","content":"# TOOLS.md — SM-S1\n\n## Canonical references\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1_supervisor_contract.md`\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\branches\\01_PRE_PRODUCTION.md`\n\n## Supervisor skills implemented\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\n- `script_batch_planner`\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `screenplay_merger`\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n- `retry_planner`\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\n- `operator_batch_scheduler`\n\n## Existing shared component to reuse\n- `runtime/s1/checkpoint_writer.py`\n\n## Operators supervised\n- `scene_director`\n- `tts_polish`\n\n## Key paths in the system repo\n- Supervisor contract:\n  - `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1_supervisor_contract.md`\n- Runtime supervisor skills:\n  - `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\`\n- Existing checkpoint writer:\n  - `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\checkpoint_writer.py`\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_s1_pre_production\\\\TOOLS.md\",\"content\":\"# TOOLS.md — SM-S1\\n\\n## Canonical references\\n- `C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1_supervisor_contract.md`\\n- `C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\branches\\\\01_PRE_PRODUCTION.md`\\n\\n## Supervisor skills implemented\\n- `s1_preflight_checker`\\n- `s1_paths_resolver`\\n- `script_batch_planner`\\n- `scene_director_io_adapter`\\n- `screenplay_merger`\\n- `tts_polish_batch_planner`\\n- `tts_polish_io_adapter`\\n- `tts_polish_merger`\\n- `retry_planner`\\n- `s1_result_summarizer`\\n- `operator_batch_scheduler`\\n\\n## Existing shared component to reuse\\n- `runtime/s1/checkpoint_writer.py`\\n\\n## Operators supervised\\n- `scene_director`\\n- `tts_polish`\\n\\n## Key paths in the system repo\\n- Supervisor contract:\\n  - `C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1_supervisor_contract.md`\\n- Runtime supervisor skills:\\n  - `C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\supervisor_skills\\\\`\\n- Existing checkpoint writer:\\n  - `C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\checkpoint_writer.py`\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_a9xqRuw4IsCmO6KHTmZKHDQA|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caf3fce5f881959b4fba83b8382c1b","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_s1_pre_production\\WORKFLOW.md","content":"# WORKFLOW.md — SM-S1\n\n## Canonical sector flow\n1. Run `s1_preflight_checker`\n2. Run `s1_paths_resolver`\n3. Plan script batches via `script_batch_planner`\n4. Build scene_director payloads via `scene_director_io_adapter`\n5. Schedule scene_director batches with controlled parallelism\n6. Merge scene_director outputs via `screenplay_merger`\n7. Validate screenplay\n8. If validation fails, use `retry_planner`\n9. Plan polish batches via `tts_polish_batch_planner`\n10. Build tts_polish payloads via `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n11. Schedule tts_polish batches with controlled parallelism\n12. Merge polish outputs via `tts_polish_merger`\n13. Validate polish\n14. If validation fails, use `retry_planner`\n15. Build `scene_bible.json`\n16. Validate scene bible schema\n17. Write/check checkpoints\n18. Summarize sector result via `s1_result_summarizer`\n19. Complete or fail the sector\n\n## Important workflow rules\n- Preserve persisted file contracts\n- Preserve original narration separately from TTS-polished narration\n- Use selective retry when possible\n- Do not overwrite original screenplay with polished narration\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_s1_pre_production\\\\WORKFLOW.md\",\"content\":\"# WORKFLOW.md — SM-S1\\n\\n## Canonical sector flow\\n1. Run `s1_preflight_checker`\\n2. Run `s1_paths_resolver`\\n3. Plan script batches via `script_batch_planner`\\n4. Build scene_director payloads via `scene_director_io_adapter`\\n5. Schedule scene_director batches with controlled parallelism\\n6. Merge scene_director outputs via `screenplay_merger`\\n7. Validate screenplay\\n8. If validation fails, use `retry_planner`\\n9. Plan polish batches via `tts_polish_batch_planner`\\n10. Build tts_polish payloads via `tts_polish_io_adapter`\\n11. Schedule tts_polish batches with controlled parallelism\\n12. Merge polish outputs via `tts_polish_merger`\\n13. Validate polish\\n14. If validation fails, use `retry_planner`\\n15. Build `scene_bible.json`\\n16. Validate scene bible schema\\n17. Write/check checkpoints\\n18. Summarize sector result via `s1_result_summarizer`\\n19. Complete or fail the sector\\n\\n## Important workflow rules\\n- Preserve persisted file contracts\\n- Preserve original narration separately from TTS-polished narration\\n- Use selective retry when possible\\n- Do not overwrite original screenplay with polished narration\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_9uEHR9da6igO4l10BFJr4x3K|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caf3fce6008195939ebd64ddabc1e3","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_s1_pre_production\\OPERATORS.md","content":"# OPERATORS.md — SM-S1\n\n## scene_director\n\n### Role\nTransformar batches do script bruto em cenas estruturadas para `screenplay.json`.\n\n### Receives\n- batch payload prepared by `scene_director_io_adapter`\n- `scene_words_range`\n- batch text\n- output path contract\n\n### Returns\nBatch result containing scene objects with at least:\n- `scene_id`\n- `narration_original`\n- `visual_direction`\n- `mood`\n- `duration_estimate`\n\n### Does not do\n- TTS polish\n- scene bible building\n- sector-level retry logic\n\n---\n\n## tts_polish\n\n### Role\nTransformar batches pequenos de cenas em narração polida para TTS sem alterar significado.\n\n### Receives\n- polish batch payload prepared by `tts_polish_io_adapter`\n- original scene narration\n- `tts_polish_rules`\n- output path contract\n\n### Returns\nBatch result containing, at minimum:\n- `scene_id`\n- `narration_original`\n- `narration_tts`\n- optional `changes`\n\n### Does not do\n- overwrite original screenplay\n- sector-level retry logic\n- scene bible building\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_s1_pre_production\\\\OPERATORS.md\",\"content\":\"# OPERATORS.md — SM-S1\\n\\n## scene_director\\n\\n### Role\\nTransformar batches do script bruto em cenas estruturadas para `screenplay.json`.\\n\\n### Receives\\n- batch payload prepared by `scene_director_io_adapter`\\n- `scene_words_range`\\n- batch text\\n- output path contract\\n\\n### Returns\\nBatch result containing scene objects with at least:\\n- `scene_id`\\n- `narration_original`\\n- `visual_direction`\\n- `mood`\\n- `duration_estimate`\\n\\n### Does not do\\n- TTS polish\\n- scene bible building\\n- sector-level retry logic\\n\\n---\\n\\n## tts_polish\\n\\n### Role\\nTransformar batches pequenos de cenas em narração polida para TTS sem alterar significado.\\n\\n### Receives\\n- polish batch payload prepared by `tts_polish_io_adapter`\\n- original scene narration\\n- `tts_polish_rules`\\n- output path contract\\n\\n### Returns\\nBatch result containing, at minimum:\\n- `scene_id`\\n- `narration_original`\\n- `narration_tts`\\n- optional `changes`\\n\\n### Does not do\\n- overwrite original screenplay\\n- sector-level retry logic\\n- scene bible building\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6QudmwPiUmMflhydbizHZXEK|fc_0047bd771936d8e20169caf3fce60481959539ae11f9b4966b","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_s1_pre_production\\STATE.md","content":"# STATE.md — SM-S1\n\n## Sector state model\nThe supervisor should reason about states such as:\n- `not_started`\n- `running`\n- `retrying`\n- `blocked`\n- `complete`\n- `failed`\n\n## Retry policy (v1)\n- structural preflight failures -> fail fast\n- operator execution failures -> retry batch or step depending on mapping\n- semantic screenplay failures -> retry affected batches when possible\n- semantic polish failures -> retry affected polish batches when possible\n- scene_bible builder failures -> retry builder step\n- retry limit -> abort\n\n## Parallelism policy (initial)\n- `scene_director_concurrency_cap = 2`\n- `tts_polish_concurrency_cap = 4`\n\n## Parallelism rules\n- parallelize only batchable operators\n- keep validators, mergers, builders, and preflight sequential\n- do not launch all batches at once without a cap\n- preserve selective retry rather than rerunning everything by default\n\n## Escalation rule\nIf retries are exhausted or structural issues persist, fail clearly and escalate upward rather than improvising hidden recovery.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_s1_pre_production\\\\STATE.md\",\"content\":\"# STATE.md — SM-S1\\n\\n## Sector state model\\nThe supervisor should reason about states such as:\\n- `not_started`\\n- `running`\\n- `retrying`\\n- `blocked`\\n- `complete`\\n- `failed`\\n\\n## Retry policy (v1)\\n- structural preflight failures -> fail fast\\n- operator execution failures -> retry batch or step depending on mapping\\n- semantic screenplay failures -> retry affected batches when possible\\n- semantic polish failures -> retry affected polish batches when possible\\n- scene_bible builder failures -> retry builder step\\n- retry limit -> abort\\n\\n## Parallelism policy (initial)\\n- `scene_director_concurrency_cap = 2`\\n- `tts_polish_concurrency_cap = 4`\\n\\n## Parallelism rules\\n- parallelize only batchable operators\\n- keep validators, mergers, builders, and preflight sequential\\n- do not launch all batches at once without a cap\\n- preserve selective retry rather than rerunning everything by default\\n\\n## Escalation rule\\nIf retries are exhausted or structural issues persist, fail clearly and escalate upward rather than improvising hidden recovery.\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":1835,"output":2111,"cacheRead":195072,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":199018,"cost":{"input":0.0045875,"output":0.031665,"cacheRead":0.048768,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0850205}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774908371526,"responseId":"resp_0047bd771936d8e20169caf3d539cc8195a93bc7c112671479"}}
